[  99.982][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [759] #elif PS == 3
[  99.982][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [760] #define FOR_PATCH(p) S_DIAMOND(p,hp,PINCR(p,y,1))
[  99.982][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [761] const int p_area = P_AREA(S_DIAMOND_A(hp,P)); 
[  99.982][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [762] #elif PS == 2
[  99.982][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [763] #define FOR_PATCH(p) S_VERTICAL(p,hp,PINCR(p,y,1))
[  99.982][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [764] const int p_area = P_AREA(P); 
[  99.982][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [765] #elif PS == 1
[  99.982][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [766] #define FOR_PATCH(p) S_HORIZONTAL(p,hp,PINCR(p,x,1))
[  99.982][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [767] const int p_area = P_AREA(P); 
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [768] #elif PS == 0
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [769] #define FOR_PATCH(p) S_SQUARE(p,hp,PINCR(p,y,1))
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [770] const int p_area = P_AREA(P*P); 
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [771] #endif
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [772] 
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [773] const float r_scale = 1.0/r_area; 
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [774] const float r1_scale = 1.0/(r_area+1); 
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [775] const float p_scale = 1.0/p_area; 
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [776] const float hr_scale = 1.0/hr; 
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [777] 
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [778] #if SAMPLE == 0
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [779] #define sample(tex, pos, size, pt, off) tex((pos) + (pt) * (vec2(off) + 0.5 - fract((pos) * (size))))
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [780] #else
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [781] #define sample(tex, pos, size, pt, off) tex((pos) + (pt) * vec2(off))
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [782] #endif
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [783] 
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [784] /* Guide images are bound through the G (luma) GC (chroma, or non-luma) 
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [785]  * textures. When bound, these are where the weights are computed. Otherwise 
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [786]  * the weights are computed on the hooked texture.
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [787]  */
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [788] 
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [789] #if GI && defined(LUMA_raw)
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [790] #define GET_(off) sample(G_tex, G_pos, G_size, G_pt, off)
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [791] #elif GI
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [792] #define GET_(off) sample(GC_tex, GC_pos, GC_size, GC_pt, off)
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [793] #else
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [794] #define GET_(off) sample(HOOKED_tex, HOOKED_pos, HOOKED_size, HOOKED_pt, off)
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [795] #endif
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [796] 
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [797] #if defined(G_raw) && (defined(LUMA_raw) || D1W)
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [798] #define GET_GUIDE_(off) sample(G_tex, G_pos, G_size, G_pt, off)
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [799] #define gather_offs(off, off_arr) (G_mul * vec4(textureGatherOffsets(G_raw, G_pos + vec2(off) * G_pt, off_arr)))
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [800] #define gather(off) G_gather(G_pos + (off) * G_pt, 0)
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [801] #elif defined(GC_raw)
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [802] #define GET_GUIDE_(off) sample(GC_tex, GC_pos, GC_size, GC_pt, off)
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [803] #else
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [804] #define GET_GUIDE_(off) GET_(off)
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [805] #define gather_offs(off, off_arr) (HOOKED_mul * vec4(textureGatherOffsets(HOOKED_raw, HOOKED_pos + vec2(off) * HOOKED_pt, off_arr)))
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [806] #define gather(off) HOOKED_gather(HOOKED_pos + (off)*HOOKED_pt, 0)
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [807] #endif
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [808] 
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [809] #if T
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [810] val GET(vec3 off)
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [811] {
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [812] 	 switch (min(int(off.z), frame)) {
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [813] 	 case 0: return val_swizz(GET_(off)); 
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [814] 
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [815] 	 }
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [816] }
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [817] val GET_GUIDE(vec3 off)
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [818] {
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [819] 	 return off.z == 0 ? val_guide_swizz(GET_GUIDE_(off)) : GET(off); 
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [820] }
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [821] #else
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [822] #define GET(off) val_swizz(GET_(off))
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [823] #define GET_GUIDE(off) val_guide_swizz(GET_GUIDE_(off))
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [824] #endif
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [825] 
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [826] vec4 poi_ = GET_(vec3(0)); 
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [827] vec4 poi2_ = GET_GUIDE_(vec3(0)); 
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [828] val poi = val_swizz(poi_);  // pixel-of-interest
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [829] val_guide poi2 = val_guide_swizz(poi2_);  // guide pixel-of-interest
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [830] 
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [831] #if RI // rotation
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [832] vec2 rot(vec2 p, float d)
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [833] {
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [834] 	 return vec2(
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [835] 	 	 p.x * cos(radians(d)) - p.y * sin(radians(d)),
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [836] 	 	 p.y * sin(radians(d)) + p.x * cos(radians(d))
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [837] 	 ); 
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [838] }
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [839] #else
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [840] #define rot(p, d) (p)
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [841] #endif
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [842] 
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [843] #if RFI // reflection
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [844] vec2 ref(vec2 p, int d)
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [845] {
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [846] 	 switch (d) {
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [847] 	 case 0: return p; 
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [848] 	 case 1: return p * vec2(1, -1); 
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [849] 	 case 2: return p * vec2(-1, 1); 
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [850] 	 }
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [851] }
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [852] #else
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [853] #define ref(p, d) (p)
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [854] #endif
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [855] 
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [856] #if SST && R >= SST
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [857] float spatial_r(vec3 v)
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [858] {
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [859] 	 v.xy += 0.5 - fract(HOOKED_pos*HOOKED_size); 
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [860] 	 v.z *= TD; 
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [861] 	 return SK(length(v)*SS); 
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [862] }
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [863] #else
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [864] #define spatial_r(v) (1)
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [865] #endif
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [866] 
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [867] // 2D blur for sharpening
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [868] #if AS
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [869] float spatial_as(vec3 v)
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [870] {
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [871] 	 v.xy += 0.5 - fract(HOOKED_pos*HOOKED_size); 
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [872] 	 return ASK(length(v)*ASS) * int(v.z == 0); 
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [873] }
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [874] #endif
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [875] 
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [876] #if PST && P >= PST
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [877] #define spatial_p(v) PSK(length(v)*PSS)
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [878] #define normalize_p(x,expr) DIV((x), (expr))
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [879] #else
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [880] #define spatial_p(v) (1)
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [881] #define normalize_p(x,expr) ((x) * p_scale)
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [882] #endif
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [883] 
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [884] const float pdiff_scale = 1.0/max(EPSILON,POW2(S*0.013)); 
[  99.983][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [885] val_guide range(val_guide pdiff_sq)
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [886] {
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [887] 	 pdiff_sq = sqrt(abs(pdiff_sq - max(EPSILON, RO)) * pdiff_scale); 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [888] 	 return RK(pdiff_sq); 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [889] }
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [890] 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [891] #define GATHER (PD == 0 && NG == 0 && SAMPLE == 0) // never textureGather if any of these conditions are false
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [892] #define REGULAR_ROTATIONS (RI == 0 || RI == 1 || RI == 3 || RI == 7)
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [893] 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [894] #if (defined(LUMA_gather) || D1W) && ((PS == 0 || ((PS == 3 || PS == 7) && RI != 7) || PS == 8) && P == 3) && REGULAR_ROTATIONS && GATHER
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [895] // 3x3 diamond/plus or square patch_comparison_gather
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [896] const ivec2 offsets_adj[4] = { ivec2(0,-1), ivec2(1,0), ivec2(0,1), ivec2(-1,0) }; 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [897] const ivec2 offsets_adj_sf[4] = { ivec2(0,-1) * SF, ivec2(1,0) * SF, ivec2(0,1) * SF, ivec2(-1,0) * SF }; 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [898] vec4 poi_patch_adj = gather_offs(0, offsets_adj); 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [899] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [900] const ivec2 offsets_diag[4] = { ivec2(-1,-1), ivec2(1,-1), ivec2(1,1), ivec2(-1,1) }; 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [901] const ivec2 offsets_diag_sf[4] = { ivec2(-1,-1) * SF, ivec2(1,-1) * SF, ivec2(1,1) * SF, ivec2(-1,1) * SF }; 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [902] vec4 poi_patch_diag = gather_offs(0, offsets_diag); 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [903] #endif
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [904] float patch_comparison_gather(vec3 r)
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [905] {
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [906] 	 float min_rot = p_area - 1; 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [907] 	 vec4 transformer_adj = gather_offs(r, offsets_adj_sf); 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [908] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [909] 	 vec4 transformer_diag = gather_offs(r, offsets_diag_sf); 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [910] #endif
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [911] 	 FOR_ROTATION {
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [912] 	 	 FOR_REFLECTION {
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [913] #if RFI
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [914] 	 	 	 /* xxy
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [915] 	 	 	  * w y
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [916] 	 	 	  * wzz
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [917] 	 	 	  */
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [918] 	 	 	 switch(rfi) {
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [919] 	 	 	 case 1:
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [920] 	 	 	 	 transformer_adj = transformer_adj.zyxw; 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [921] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [922] 	 	 	 	 transformer_diag = transformer_diag.zyxw; 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [923] #endif
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [924] 	 	 	 	 break; 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [925] 	 	 	 case 2:
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [926] 	 	 	 	 transformer_adj = transformer_adj.xwzy; 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [927] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [928] 	 	 	 	 transformer_diag = transformer_diag.xwzy; 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [929] #endif
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [930] 	 	 	 	 break; 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [931] 	 	 	 }
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [932] #endif
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [933] 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [934] 	 	 	 vec4 pdiff_sq = POW2(poi_patch_adj - transformer_adj) * spatial_p(vec2(1,0)); 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [935] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [936] 	 	 	 pdiff_sq += POW2(poi_patch_diag - transformer_diag) * spatial_p(vec2(1,1)); 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [937] #endif
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [938] 	 	 	 min_rot = min(dot(pdiff_sq, vec4(1)), min_rot); 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [939] 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [940] // un-reflect
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [941] #if RFI
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [942] 	 	 	 switch(rfi) {
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [943] 	 	 	 case 1:
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [944] 	 	 	 	 transformer_adj = transformer_adj.zyxw; 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [945] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [946] 	 	 	 	 transformer_diag = transformer_diag.zyxw; 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [947] #endif
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [948] 	 	 	 	 break; 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [949] 	 	 	 case 2:
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [950] 	 	 	 	 transformer_adj = transformer_adj.xwzy; 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [951] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [952] 	 	 	 	 transformer_diag = transformer_diag.xwzy; 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [953] #endif
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [954] 	 	 	 	 break; 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [955] 	 	 	 }
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [956] #endif
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [957] 	 	 } // FOR_REFLECTION
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [958] #if RI == 7
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [959] 	 	 transformer_adj = transformer_adj.wxyz; 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [960] 	 	 // swap adjacents for diagonals
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [961] 	 	 transformer_adj += transformer_diag; 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [962] 	 	 transformer_diag = transformer_adj - transformer_diag; 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [963] 	 	 transformer_adj -= transformer_diag; 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [964] #elif RI == 3
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [965] 	 	 transformer_adj = transformer_adj.wxyz; 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [966] #elif RI == 1
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [967] 	 	 transformer_adj = transformer_adj.zwxy; 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [968] #endif
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [969] #if RI == 3 && (PS == 0 || PS == 8)
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [970] 	 	 transformer_diag = transformer_diag.wxyz; 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [971] #elif RI == 1 && (PS == 0 || PS == 8)
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [972] 	 	 transformer_diag = transformer_diag.zwxy; 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [973] #endif
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [974] 	 } // FOR_ROTATION
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [975] 	 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [976] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [977] 	 float total_weight = spatial_p(vec2(0,0)) + 4 * spatial_p(vec2(0,1)) + 4 * spatial_p(vec2(1,1)); 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [978] #else
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [979] 	 float total_weight = spatial_p(vec2(0,0)) + 4 * spatial_p(vec2(0,1)); 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [980] #endif
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [981] 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [982] 	 float center_diff = poi2.x - GET_GUIDE(r).x; 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [983] 	 return normalize_p(POW2(center_diff) + min_rot, max(EPSILON,total_weight)); 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [984] }
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [985] #elif (defined(LUMA_gather) || D1W) && PS == 4 && P == 3 && RI == 0 && RFI == 0 && GATHER
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [986] const ivec2 offsets[4] = { ivec2(0,-1), ivec2(-1,0), ivec2(0,0), ivec2(1,0) }; 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [987] const ivec2 offsets_sf[4] = { ivec2(0,-1) * SF, ivec2(-1,0) * SF, ivec2(0,0) * SF, ivec2(1,0) * SF }; 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [988] vec4 poi_patch = gather_offs(0, offsets); 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [989] vec4 spatial_p_weights = vec4(spatial_p(vec2(0,-1)), spatial_p(vec2(-1,0)), spatial_p(vec2(0,0)), spatial_p(vec2(1,0))); 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [990] float patch_comparison_gather(vec3 r)
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [991] {
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [992] 	 vec4 pdiff = poi_patch - gather_offs(r, offsets_sf); 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [993] 	 return normalize_p(
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [994] 	 	 dot(POW2(pdiff) * spatial_p_weights, vec4(1)),
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [995] 	 	 dot(spatial_p_weights, vec4(1))
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [996] 	 ); 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [997] }
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [998] #elif (defined(LUMA_gather) || D1W) && PS == 6 && RI == 0 && RFI == 0 && GATHER
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [999] // tiled even square patch_comparison_gather
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1000] // XXX extend to support odd square?
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1001] float patch_comparison_gather(vec3 r)
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1002] {
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1003] 	 /* gather order:
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1004] 	  * w z
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1005] 	  * x y
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1006] 	  */
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1007] 	 vec2 tile; 
[  99.984][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1008] 	 float pdiff_sq = 0; 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1009] 	 float total_weight = 0; 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1010] 	 for (tile.x = -hp;  tile.x < hp;  tile.x+=2) for (tile.y = -hp;  tile.y < hp;  tile.y+=2) {
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1011] 	 	 vec4 diff = gather(tile + r.xy) - gather(tile); 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1012] 	 	 vec4 weights = vec4(spatial_p(tile+vec2(0,1)), spatial_p(tile+vec2(1,1)), spatial_p(tile+vec2(1,0)), spatial_p(tile+vec2(0,0))); 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1013] 	 	 pdiff_sq += dot(POW2(diff) * weights, vec4(1)); 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1014] 	 	 total_weight += dot(weights, vec4(1)); 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1015] 	 }
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1016] 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1017] 	 return normalize_p(pdiff_sq, max(EPSILON,total_weight)); 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1018] }
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1019] #else
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1020] #define patch_comparison_gather patch_comparison
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1021] #define STORE_POI_PATCH 1
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1022] val_guide poi_patch[p_area]; 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1023] #endif
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1024] 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1025] val_guide patch_comparison(vec3 r)
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1026] {
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1027] 	 vec3 p; 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1028] 	 val_guide min_rot = val_guide(p_area); 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1029] 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1030] 	 FOR_ROTATION FOR_REFLECTION {
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1031] 	 	 val_guide pdiff_sq = val_guide(0); 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1032] 	 	 float total_weight = 0; 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1033] 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1034] 	 	 int p_index = 0; 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1035] 	 	 FOR_PATCH(p) {
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1036] #ifdef STORE_POI_PATCH
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1037] 	 	 	 val_guide poi_p = poi_patch[p_index++]; 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1038] #else
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1039] 	 	 	 val_guide poi_p = GET_GUIDE(p); 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1040] #endif
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1041] 	 	 	 vec3 transformed_p = SF * vec3(ref(rot(p.xy, ri), rfi), p.z); 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1042] 	 	 	 val_guide diff_sq = poi_p - GET_GUIDE(transformed_p + r); 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1043] 	 	 	 diff_sq *= diff_sq; 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1044] 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1045] 	 	 	 float weight = spatial_p(p.xy); 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1046] 	 	 	 pdiff_sq += diff_sq * weight; 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1047] 	 	 	 total_weight += weight; 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1048] 	 	 }
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1049] 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1050] 	 	 min_rot = min(min_rot, normalize_p(pdiff_sq, max(EPSILON,total_weight))); 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1051] 	 }
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1052] 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1053] 	 return min_rot; 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1054] }
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1055] 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1056] vec4 hook()
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1057] {
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1058] 	 val_guide total_weight = val_guide(0); 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1059] 	 val sum = val(0); 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1060] 	 val result = val(0); 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1061] 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1062] 	 vec3 r = vec3(0); 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1063] 	 vec3 me = vec3(0); 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1064] 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1065] 	 float sw = SW * spatial_r(vec3(0)); 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1066] 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1067] #if T && ME == 1 // temporal & motion estimation
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1068] 	 vec3 me_tmp = vec3(0); 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1069] 	 float maxweight = 0; 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1070] #elif T && ME == 2 // temporal & motion estimation
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1071] 	 vec3 me_sum = vec3(0); 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1072] 	 float me_weight = 0; 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1073] #endif
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1074] 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1075] #if AS
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1076] 	 float total_weight_as = 0; 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1077] 	 val sum_as = val(0); 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1078] #endif
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1079] 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1080] #if WD == 2 || V == 7 || C
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1081] #define STORE_WEIGHTS 1
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1082] #else
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1083] #define STORE_WEIGHTS 0
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1084] #endif
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1085] 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1086] #if STORE_WEIGHTS
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1087] 	 int r_index = 0; 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1088] 	 val_guide_packed all_weights[r_area]; 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1089] 	 val_packed all_pixels[r_area]; 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1090] #endif
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1091] 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1092] #ifdef STORE_POI_PATCH
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1093] 	 vec3 p; 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1094] 	 int p_index = 0; 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1095] 	 FOR_PATCH(p)
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1096] 	 	 poi_patch[p_index++] = GET_GUIDE(p); 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1097] #endif
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1098] 	 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1099] #if WD == 1 // weight discard (moving cumulative average)
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1100] 	 int r_iter = 1; 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1101] 	 val_guide wd_total_weight = val_guide(0); 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1102] 	 val wd_sum = val(0); 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1103] #endif
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1104] 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1105] #if V == 7
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1106] 	 vec2 v7cell = floor(HOOKED_size/R * HOOKED_pos) * R + hr; 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1107] 	 vec2 v7cell_off = floor(HOOKED_pos * HOOKED_size) - floor(v7cell); 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1108] #endif
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1109] 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1110] 	 FOR_FRAME(r) {
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1111] 	 // XXX ME is always a frame behind, should have the option to re-research after applying ME (could do it an arbitrary number of times per frame if desired)
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1112] #if T && ME == 1 // temporal & motion estimation max weight
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1113] 	 if (r.z > 0) {
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1114] 	 	 me += me_tmp * MEF; 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1115] 	 	 me_tmp = vec3(0); 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1116] 	 	 maxweight = 0; 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1117] 	 }
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1118] #elif T && ME == 2 // temporal & motion estimation weighted average
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1119] 	 if (r.z > 0) {
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1120] 	 	 me += round(DIV(me_sum, me_weight) * MEF); 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1121] 	 	 me_sum = vec3(0); 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1122] 	 	 me_weight = 0; 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1123] 	 }
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1124] #endif
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1125] 	 FOR_RESEARCH(r) {
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1126] #if V == 7
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1127] 	 	 r.xy += v7cell_off; 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1128] #endif
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1129] 
[  99.985][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1130] 	 	 // r coords with appropriate transformations applied
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1131] 	 	 vec3 tr = vec3(r.xy + floor(r.xy * RSF), r.z); 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1132] 	 	 tr.xy += me.xy; 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1133] 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1134] 	 	 val px = GET(tr); 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1135] 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1136] #if SKIP_PATCH
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1137] 	 	 val weight = val(1); 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1138] #else
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1139] 	 	 val_guide pdiff_sq = (r.z == 0) ? patch_comparison_gather(tr) : patch_comparison(tr); 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1140] 	 	 val_guide weight = range(pdiff_sq); 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1141] #endif
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1142] 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1143] #if T && ME == 1 // temporal & motion estimation max weight
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1144] 	 	 me_tmp = vec3(tr.xy,0) * step(maxweight, weight.x) + me_tmp * (1 - step(maxweight, weight.x)); 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1145] 	 	 maxweight = max(maxweight, weight.x); 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1146] #elif T && ME == 2 // temporal & motion estimation weighted average
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1147] 	 	 me_sum += vec3(tr.xy,0) * weight.x; 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1148] 	 	 me_weight += weight.x; 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1149] #endif
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1150] 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1151] 	 	 weight *= spatial_r(r); 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1152] 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1153] #if AS
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1154] 	 	 float spatial_as_weight = spatial_as(tr); 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1155] 	 	 sum_as += px * spatial_as_weight; 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1156] 	 	 total_weight_as += spatial_as_weight; 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1157] #endif
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1158] 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1159] #if WD == 1 // weight discard (moving cumulative average)
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1160] 	 	 float wd_scale = RECIPROCAL(r_iter); 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1161] 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1162] 	 	 val_guide below_threshold = WDS * abs(min(val_guide(0.0), weight - (total_weight * wd_scale * WDT * WD1TK(sqrt(wd_scale*WDP))))); 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1163] 	 	 val_guide wdkf = MAP_GUIDE(WDK, below_threshold); 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1164] 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1165] 	 	 wd_sum += px * weight * wdkf; 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1166] 	 	 wd_total_weight += weight * wdkf; 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1167] 	 	 r_iter++; 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1168] #if STORE_WEIGHTS
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1169] 	 	 all_weights[r_index] = val_guide_pack(weight * wdkf); 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1170] 	 	 all_pixels[r_index] = val_pack(px); 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1171] 	 	 r_index++; 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1172] #endif
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1173] #elif STORE_WEIGHTS
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1174] 	 	 all_weights[r_index] = val_guide_pack(weight); 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1175] 	 	 all_pixels[r_index] = val_pack(px); 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1176] 	 	 r_index++; 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1177] #endif
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1178] 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1179] #if V == 7
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1180] 	 	 r.xy -= v7cell_off; 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1181] #endif
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1182] 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1183] 	 	 sum += px * weight; 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1184] 	 	 total_weight += weight; 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1185] 	 } // FOR_RESEARCH
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1186] 	 } // FOR_FRAME
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1187] 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1188] 	 val_guide avg_weight = total_weight * r_scale; 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1189] 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1190] #if defined(LUMA_raw) && V == 4
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1191] 	 return unval_guide(avg_weight); 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1192] #elif defined(CHROMA_raw) && V == 4
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1193] 	 return vec4(0.5);  // XXX visualize for chroma
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1194] #endif
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1195] 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1196] #if C
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1197] 	 total_weight = val_guide(0); 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1198] 	 sum = val(0); 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1199] 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1200] 	 for (int c = 0;  c <= C;  c++) {
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1201] 	 	 val_guide_packed all_weights_update[r_area]; 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1202] 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1203] 	 	 r_index = 0; 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1204] 	 	 FOR_FRAME(r) FOR_RESEARCH(r) {
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1205] 	 	 	 val_guide c_sum = val_guide(0); 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1206] 	 	 	 vec3 r2 = vec3(0); 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1207] 	 	 	 int r2_index = 0; 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1208] 	 	 	 FOR_FRAME(r2) FOR_RESEARCH(r2)
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1209] 	 	 	 	 if (distance(r, r2) - sqrt(CD) <= FLT_EPSILON)
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1210] 	 	 	 	 	 c_sum += val_guide_unpack(all_weights[r2_index++]); 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1211] 	 	 	 if (length(r) - sqrt(CD) <= FLT_EPSILON)
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1212] 	 	 	 	 c_sum += sw; 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1213] 	 	 	 all_weights_update[r_index++] = val_guide_pack(c_sum); 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1214] 	 	 }
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1215] 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1216] 	 	 r_index = 0; 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1217] 	 	 FOR_FRAME(r) FOR_RESEARCH(r) {
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1218] 	 	 	 val_guide old_weight = val_guide_unpack(all_weights[r_index]); 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1219] 	 	 	 val_guide update = val_guide_unpack(all_weights_update[r_index]); 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1220] 	 	 	 val_guide weight = old_weight * RECIPROCAL(max(EPSILON,CS))
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1221] 	 	 	                  + old_weight * update * r1_scale * CS; 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1222] 	 	 	 all_weights[r_index] = val_guide_pack(weight); 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1223] 	 	 	 if (c == C) { // only need to update this stuff on the final C iteration
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1224] 	 	 	 	 val px = val_unpack(all_pixels[r_index]); 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1225] 	 	 	 	 sum += px * weight; 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1226] 	 	 	 	 total_weight += weight; 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1227] 	 	 	 	 all_pixels[r_index] = val_pack(px); 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1228] 	 	 	 }
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1229] 	 	 	 r_index++; 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1230] 	 	 }
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1231] 	 } // for C
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1232] #endif
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1233] 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1234] #if WD == 2 // weight discard (mean)
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1235] 	 total_weight = val_guide(0); 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1236] 	 sum = val(0); 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1237] 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1238] 	 r_index = 0; 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1239] 	 FOR_FRAME(r) FOR_RESEARCH(r) {
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1240] 	 	 val px = val_unpack(all_pixels[r_index]); 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1241] 	 	 val_guide weight = val_guide_unpack(all_weights[r_index]); 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1242] 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1243] 	 	 val_guide below_threshold = WDS * abs(min(val_guide(0.0), weight - (avg_weight * WDT))); 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1244] 	 	 weight *= MAP_GUIDE(WDK, below_threshold); 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1245] 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1246] 	 	 sum += px * weight; 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1247] 	 	 total_weight += weight; 
[  99.986][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1248] #if V == 7
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1249] 	 	 all_pixels[r_index] = val_pack(px); 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1250] 	 	 all_weights[r_index] = val_guide_pack(weight); 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1251] #endif
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1252] 	 	 r_index++; 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1253] 	 } // FOR_FRAME FOR_RESEARCH
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1254] #endif
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1255] 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1256] #if WD == 1 // weight discard (moving cumulative average)
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1257] 	 total_weight = wd_total_weight; 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1258] 	 sum = wd_sum; 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1259] #endif
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1260] 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1261] #if WD // weight discard
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1262] 	 avg_weight = total_weight * r_scale; 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1263] #endif
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1264] 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1265] 	 total_weight += sw; 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1266] 	 sum += poi * sw; 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1267] 	 result = MED_DIV(sum, max(val(EPSILON),val(total_weight))); 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1268] 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1269] 	 // store frames for temporal
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1270] #if T > 1
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1271] 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1272] #endif
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1273] #if T && TRF
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1274] 	 imageStore(PREV1, ivec2(HOOKED_pos*HOOKED_size), unval(result)); 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1275] #elif T
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1276] 	 imageStore(PREV1, ivec2(HOOKED_pos*HOOKED_size), unval_guide(poi2)); 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1277] #endif
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1278] 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1279] #if AS == 1 // sharpen+denoise
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1280] #define AS_base result
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1281] #elif AS == 2 // sharpen only
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1282] #define AS_base poi
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1283] #endif
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1284] 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1285] #if ASI == 0
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1286] #define AS_input result
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1287] #elif ASI == 1
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1288] #define AS_input poi
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1289] #endif
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1290] 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1291] #if AS // sharpening
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1292] 	 val usm = AS_input - MED_DIV(sum_as, max(EPSILON,total_weight_as)); 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1293] 	 usm = POW(usm, ASP); 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1294] 	 const float as_scale_15 = 1.0/1.5; 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1295] 	 usm *= ASAK(abs((AS_base + usm - 0.5) * as_scale_15) * ASA); 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1296] 	 usm *= ASF; 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1297] 	 result = AS_base + usm; 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1298] #endif
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1299] 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1300] #if EP // extremes preserve
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1301] 	 float luminance = EP_texOff(0).x; 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1302] 	 float ep_weight = POW(max(EPSILON, min(1-luminance, luminance)*2), (luminance < 0.5 ? DP : BP)); 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1303] 	 result = mix(poi, result, ep_weight); 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1304] #else
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1305] 	 float ep_weight = 0; 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1306] #endif
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1307] 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1308] #if V == 1
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1309] 	 result = clamp(pow(abs(poi - result), val(0.25)), 0.0, 1.0); 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1310] #elif V == 2
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1311] 	 result = (poi - result) * 0.5 + 0.5; 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1312] #elif V == 3
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1313] 	 result = val(avg_weight); 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1314] #elif V == 5
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1315] 	 result = 0.5 + usm; 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1316] #elif V == 6
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1317] 	 result = val(1 - ep_weight); 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1318] #elif V == 7
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1319] 	 result = val(0); 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1320] 	 r_index = 0; 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1321] 	 FOR_FRAME(r) FOR_RESEARCH(r) {
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1322] 	 	 if (v7cell_off == r.xy)
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1323] 	 	 	 result = val_guide_unpack(all_weights[r_index]); 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1324] 	 	 r_index++; 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1325] 	 }
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1326] 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1327] 	 if (v7cell_off == vec2(0,0))
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1328] 	 	 result = val(SW * spatial_r(vec3(0))); 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1329] #endif
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1330] 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1331] // XXX visualize chroma for these
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1332] #if defined(CHROMA_raw) && (V == 3 || V == 4 || V == 6 || V == 7)
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1333] 	 return vec4(0.5); 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1334] #endif
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1335] 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1336] 	 return unval(result); 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1337] }
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1338] 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1339] // End of source code injected from ./nlmeans_template 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1340] 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1341] //!HOOK LUMA
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1342] //!HOOK CHROMA
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1343] //!BIND G
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1344] //!WIDTH G.w
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1345] //!HEIGHT G.h
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1346] //!DESC Non-local means (Guide, share)
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1347] //!SAVE GC
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1348] 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1349] vec4 hook()
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1350] {
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1351] 	return G_texOff(0);
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1352] }
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1353] 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1354] //!HOOK LUMA
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1355] //!HOOK CHROMA
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1356] //!BIND HOOKED
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1357] //!BIND G
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1358] //!BIND GC
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1359] //!DESC Non-local means (nlmeans.glsl)
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1360] 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1361] 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1362] 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1363] // User variables
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1364] 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1365] // It is generally preferable to denoise luma and chroma differently, so the 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1366] // user variables for luma and chroma are split.
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1367] 
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1368] // Denoising factor (sigma, higher means more blur)
[  99.987][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1369] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1370] #define S 3.559719405746641
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1371] #else
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1372] #define S 0.644044031464058
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1373] #endif
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1374] 
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1375] /* Noise resistant adaptive sharpening
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1376]  *
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1377]  * AS:
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1378]  * 	- 0: disable
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1379]  * 	- 1: sharpen+denoise
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1380]  * 	- 2: sharpen only
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1381]  * ASF: Higher numbers make a sharper image
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1382]  * ASA: Anti-ringing, higher numbers increase strength
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1383]  * ASP: Power, lower numbers increase sharpening on lower frequency detail
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1384]  * ASS: Equivalent to SS but for ASK instead of SK
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1385]  * ASI:
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1386]  *  - 0: don't sharpen noise
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1387]  *  - 1: sharpen noise
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1388]  */
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1389] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1390] #define AS 0
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1391] #define ASF 0.0
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1392] #define ASA 0.0
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1393] #define ASP 0.0
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1394] #define ASS 0.0
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1395] #define ASI 0
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1396] #else
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1397] #define AS 0
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1398] #define ASF 0.0
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1399] #define ASA 0.0
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1400] #define ASP 0.0
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1401] #define ASS 0.0
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1402] #define ASI 0
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1403] #endif
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1404] 
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1405] /* Starting weight
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1406]  *
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1407]  * AKA the center weight, the weight of the pixel-of-interest.
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1408]  */
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1409] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1410] #define SW 0.5211292610050897
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1411] #else
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1412] #define SW 0.32722815587389364
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1413] #endif
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1414] 
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1415] /* Spatial kernel
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1416]  *
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1417]  * Increasing the spatial sigma (SS) reduces the weight of further 
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1418]  * pixels.
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1419]  *
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1420]  * The intra-patch variants might help with larger patch sizes.
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1421]  *
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1422]  * SST: enables spatial kernel if R>=PST, 0 fully disables
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1423]  * SS: spatial sigma
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1424]  * PSS: intra-patch spatial sigma
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1425]  * PST: enables intra-patch spatial kernel if P>=PST, 0 fully disables
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1426]  */
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1427] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1428] #define SST 1
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1429] #define SS 1.3662208603933492
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1430] #define PST 0
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1431] #define PSS 0.0
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1432] #else
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1433] #define SST 1
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1434] #define SS 0.07604576880459668
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1435] #define PST 0
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1436] #define PSS 0.0
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1437] #endif
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1438] 
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1439] /* Extremes preserve
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1440]  *
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1441]  * This setting is dependent on code generation from shader_cfg, so this 
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1442]  * setting can only be enabled via shader_cfg.
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1443]  *
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1444]  * Reduce denoising in very bright/dark areas.
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1445]  *
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1446]  * The downscaling factor of the EP shader stage affects the size of the area 
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1447]  * checked for luminance.
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1448]  *
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1449]  * This is incompatible with RGB. If you have RGB hooks enabled then you will 
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1450]  * have to delete the EP shader stage or specify EP=0 through shader_cfg.
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1451]  *
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1452]  * EP: 1 to enable, 0 to disable
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1453]  * DP: EP strength on dark areas, 0 to fully denoise
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1454]  * BP: EP strength on bright areas, 0 to fully denoise
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1455]  */
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1456] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1457] #define EP 0
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1458] #define BP 0.0
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1459] #define DP 0.0
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1460] #else
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1461] #define EP 0
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1462] #define BP 0.0
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1463] #define DP 0.0
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1464] #endif
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1465] 
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1466] /* ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS */
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1467] /* ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS */
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1468] /* ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS */
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1469] /* ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS */
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1470] /* ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS */
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1471] 
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1472] /* textureGather applicable configurations:
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1473]  *
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1474]  * - PS={0,3,7,8}:P=3:RI={0,1,3,7}:RFI={0,1,2}
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1475]  * - PS={0,8}:P=3:RI={0,1,3,7}:RFI={0,1,2}
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1476]  * - PS=4:P=3:PST=0:RI=0:RFI=0
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1477]  * - PS=6:RI=0:RFI=0
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1478]  *   - Currently the only scalable variant
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1479]  *
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1480]  * Options which always disable textureGather:
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1481]  * 	- NG
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1482]  * 	- SAMPLE
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1483]  * 	- PD
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1484]  *
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1485]  * Running without textureGather may be much slower.
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1486]  */
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1487] 
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1488] /* Patch & research sizes
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1489]  *
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1490]  * P should be an odd number. Higher values are slower and not always better.
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1491]  *
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1492]  * R should be an odd number greater than or equal to 3. Higher values are 
[  99.988][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1493]  * generally better, but slower.
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1494]  */
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1495] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1496] #define P 3
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1497] #define R 3
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1498] #else
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1499] #define P 3
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1500] #define R 5
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1501] #endif
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1502] 
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1503] /* Patch and research shapes
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1504]  *
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1505]  * Different shapes have different speed and quality characteristics. Every 
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1506]  * shape (besides square) is smaller than square.
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1507]  *
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1508]  * PS applies applies to patches, RS applies to research zones.
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1509]  *
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1510]  * 0: square (symmetrical)
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1511]  * 1: horizontal line (asymmetric)
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1512]  * 2: vertical line (asymmetric)
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1513]  * 3: diamond (symmetrical)
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1514]  * 4: triangle (asymmetric, pointing upward)
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1515]  * 5: truncated triangle (asymmetric on two axis, last row halved)
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1516]  * 6: even sized square (asymmetric on two axis)
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1517]  * 7: plus (symmetrical)
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1518]  * 8: plus X (symmetrical)
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1519]  */
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1520] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1521] #define RS 3
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1522] #define PS 3
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1523] #else
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1524] #define RS 3
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1525] #define PS 3
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1526] #endif
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1527] 
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1528] /* Weight discard
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1529]  *
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1530]  * Reduces weights that fall below a fraction of the average weight. This culls 
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1531]  * the most dissimilar samples from the blur, which can yield a better result, 
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1532]  * especially around edges.
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1533]  * 
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1534]  * WD:
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1535]  * 	- 2: Mean. Better quality, but slower and requires GLSL 4.0 or later
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1536]  * 	- 1: Moving cumulative average. Fast but inaccurate, blurs directionally.
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1537]  * 	- 0: Disable
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1538]  *
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1539]  * WDT: Threshold coefficient, higher numbers discard more
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1540]  * WDP (only for WD=1): Increasing reduces the threshold for small sample sizes
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1541]  * WDS (not for WDK=is_zero): Higher numbers are more eager to reduce weights
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1542]  */
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1543] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1544] #define WD 2
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1545] #define WDT 0.6302678350888067
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1546] #define WDP 0.0
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1547] #define WDS 1.0
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1548] #else
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1549] #define WD 0
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1550] #define WDT 0.0
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1551] #define WDP 0.0
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1552] #define WDS 1.0
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1553] #endif
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1554] 
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1555] /* Connectivity
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1556]  *
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1557]  * Increases weights that are near high weights, decreases weights that are 
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1558]  * near low weights.
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1559]  *
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1560]  * C: Number of passes to do, more increases the effect, 0 does nothing
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1561]  * CD: Distance between each pixel and its furthest neighbor
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1562]  * CS: Strength of effect, higher is more
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1563]  */
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1564] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1565] #define C 0
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1566] #define CD 1.0
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1567] #define CS 1.0
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1568] #else
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1569] #define C 0
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1570] #define CD 1.0
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1571] #define CS 1.0
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1572] #endif
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1573] 
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1574] /* Rotational/reflectional invariance
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1575]  *
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1576]  * Number of rotations/reflections to try for each patch comparison. Can be 
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1577]  * slow, but may improve feature preservation. More rotations/reflections gives 
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1578]  * diminishing returns. The most similar rotation/reflection is used.
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1579]  *
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1580]  * The angle in degrees of each rotation is 360/(RI+1), so RI=1 will do a 
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1581]  * single 180 degree rotation, RI=3 will do three 90 degree rotations, etc.
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1582]  *
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1583]  * Consider setting SAMPLE=1 if setting RI to a setting that would require 
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1584]  * sampling between pixels.
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1585]  *
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1586]  * RI: Rotational invariance
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1587]  * RFI (0 to 2): Reflectional invariance
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1588]  */
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1589] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1590] #define RI 0
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1591] #define RFI 2
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1592] #else
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1593] #define RI 0
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1594] #define RFI 0
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1595] #endif
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1596] 
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1597] /* Temporal denoising
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1598]  *
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1599]  * This setting is dependent on code generation from shader_cfg, so this 
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1600]  * setting can only be enabled via shader_cfg.
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1601]  *
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1602]  * Caveats:
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1603]  * 	- Slower:
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1604]  * 		- Gather optimizations only apply to the current frame
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1605]  * 	- Requires vo=gpu-next
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1606]  * 	- Luma-only (this is a bug)
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1607]  * 	- Buggy
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1608]  *
[  99.989][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1609]  * May cause motion blur and may struggle more with noise that persists across 
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1610]  * multiple frames (e.g., from compression or duplicate frames).
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1611]  *
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1612]  * Motion estimation (ME) should improve quality without impacting speed.
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1613]  *
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1614]  * Increasing temporal distortion (TD) can reduce motion blur.
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1615]  *
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1616]  * T: number of frames used
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1617]  * ME: motion estimation, 0 for none, 1 for max weight, 2 for weighted avg
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1618]  * MEF: estimate factor, compensates for ME being one frame behind
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1619]  * TRF: compare against the denoised frames
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1620]  * TD: temporal distortion, higher numbers give less weight to previous frames
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1621]  */
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1622] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1623] #define T 0
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1624] #define ME 1
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1625] #define MEF 2
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1626] #define TRF 0
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1627] #define TD 1.0
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1628] #else
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1629] #define T 0
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1630] #define ME 0
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1631] #define MEF 2
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1632] #define TRF 0
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1633] #define TD 1.0
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1634] #endif
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1635] 
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1636] /* Kernels
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1637]  *
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1638]  * SK: spatial kernel
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1639]  * RK: range kernel (takes patch differences)
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1640]  * ASK: adaptive sharpening kernel
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1641]  * PSK: intra-patch spatial kernel
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1642]  * WDK: weight discard kernel
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1643]  * WD1TK (WD=1 only): weight discard tolerance kernel
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1644]  *
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1645]  * List of available kernels:
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1646]  *
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1647]  * bicubic
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1648]  * cos
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1649]  * ffexp
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1650]  * gaussian
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1651]  * lanczos
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1652]  * quadratic
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1653]  * quadratic_ (unclamped)
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1654]  * sinc
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1655]  * sinc3
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1656]  * sinc_ (unclamped)
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1657]  * sphinx
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1658]  * sphinx_ (unclamped)
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1659]  * triangle
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1660]  * triangle_ (unclamped)
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1661]  */
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1662] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1663] #define SK gaussian
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1664] #define RK gaussian
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1665] #define ASK sinc
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1666] #define ASAK gaussian
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1667] #define PSK gaussian
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1668] #define WDK is_zero
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1669] #define WD1TK gaussian
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1670] #else
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1671] #define SK gaussian
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1672] #define RK gaussian
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1673] #define ASK sphinx_
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1674] #define ASAK gaussian
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1675] #define PSK gaussian
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1676] #define WDK is_zero
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1677] #define WD1TK gaussian
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1678] #endif
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1679] 
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1680] /* Kernel parameters
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1681]  *
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1682]  * The following kernels take parameters:
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1683]  *
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1684]  * ffexp: K0
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1685]  */
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1686] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1687] #define K0 1.0
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1688] #define K1 1.0
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1689] #else
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1690] #define K0 1.0
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1691] #define K1 1.0
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1692] #endif
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1693] 
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1694] /* Negative kernel parameter offsets
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1695]  *
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1696]  * Usually kernels go high -> low. These parameters allow for a kernel to go 
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1697]  * low -> high -> low.
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1698]  *
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1699]  * Values of 0.0 mean no effect, higher values increase the effect.
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1700]  *
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1701]  * RO: range kernel (takes patch differences)
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1702]  */
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1703] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1704] #define RO 9.4514748889311e-05
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1705] #else
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1706] #define RO 8.568093800527619e-05
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1707] #endif
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1708] 
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1709] /* Sampling method
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1710]  *
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1711]  * In most cases this shouldn't make any difference, only set to bilinear if 
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1712]  * it's necessary to sample between pixels (e.g., RI=2).
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1713]  *
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1714]  * 0: nearest neighbor
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1715]  * 1: bilinear
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1716]  */
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1717] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1718] #define SAMPLE 0
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1719] #else
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1720] #define SAMPLE 0
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1721] #endif
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1722] 
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1723] /* Research scaling factor
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1724]  *
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1725]  * Higher numbers sample more sparsely as the distance from the POI grows.
[  99.990][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1726]  */
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1727] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1728] #define RSF 0.0
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1729] #else
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1730] #define RSF 0.0
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1731] #endif
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1732] 
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1733] // Scaling factor (should match WIDTH/HEIGHT)
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1734] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1735] #define SF 1
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1736] #else
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1737] #define SF 1
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1738] #endif
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1739] 
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1740] // Use the guide image as the input image
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1741] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1742] #define GI 1
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1743] #else
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1744] #define GI 1
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1745] #endif
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1746] 
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1747] /* Visualization
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1748]  *
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1749]  * 0: off
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1750]  * 1: absolute difference between input/output to the power of 0.25
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1751]  * 2: difference between input/output centered on 0.5
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1752]  * 3: post-WD average weight map
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1753]  * 4: pre-WD average weight map
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1754]  * 5: unsharp mask
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1755]  * 6: EP
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1756]  * 7: celled weight map (incompatible with temporal)
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1757]  */
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1758] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1759] #define V 0
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1760] #else
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1761] #define V 0
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1762] #endif
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1763] 
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1764] // Fast approximate division
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1765] #ifdef LUMA_raw

[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1767] #else
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1768] #define FAST_DIV 0
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1769] #endif
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1770]

[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1785] // Duplicate 1st weight (for luma-guided-chroma)
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1786] #ifdef LUMA_raw

[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1798] 
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1799] // Shader code
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1800] 
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1801] #define EPSILON 1.2e-38
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1802] #define FLT_EPSILON 1.19209290E-07
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1803] #define M_PI 3.14159265358979323846
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1804] #define POW2(x) ((x)*(x))
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1805] #define POW3(x) ((x)*(x)*(x))
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1806] 
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1807] // pow() implementation that gives -pow() when x<0
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1808] // avoids actually calling pow() since apparently it's buggy on nvidia
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1809] #define POW(x,y) (exp(log(abs(x)) * y) * sign(x))
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1810] 
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1811] // boolean logic w/ vectors
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1812] // from hdeband
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1813] #define NOT(x) (1 - (x))
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1814] #define AND *
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1815] #define TERNARY(cond, x, y) ((x)*(cond) + (y)*NOT(cond))
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1816] 
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1817] // from FSR
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1818] #if FAST_DIV
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1819] #define RECIPROCAL(x) uintBitsToFloat(uint(0x7ef07ebb) - floatBitsToUint(x))
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1820] #define DIV(x,y) ((x) * RECIPROCAL(y))
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1821] #define MED_RCP_B(x) uintBitsToFloat(uint(0x7ef19fff) - floatBitsToUint(x))
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1822] #define MED_RECIPROCAL(x) (MED_RCP_B(x) * (-MED_RCP_B(x) * x + 2))
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1823] #define MED_DIV(x,y) ((x) * MED_RECIPROCAL(y))
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1824] #else
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1825] #define RECIPROCAL(x) (1.0/(x))
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1826] #define MED_RECIPROCAL(x) (1.0/(x))
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1827] #define DIV(x,y) ((x)/(y))
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1828] #define MED_DIV(x,y) ((x)/(y))
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1829] #endif
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1830] 
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1831] // XXX make kernel params capable of being set per-kernel, e.g., RK0, SK0...
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1832] 
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1833] // kernels
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1834] // XXX sinc & sphinx: 1e-3 was selected tentatively; not sure what the correct value should be (1e-8 is too low)
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1835] #define bicubic(x) bicubic_(clamp((x), 0.0, 2.0))
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1836] #define bicubic_(x) ((1.0/6.0) * (POW3((x)+2) - 4 * POW3((x)+1) + 6 * POW3(x) - 4 * POW3(max((x)-1, 0))))
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1837] #define ffexp(x) (POW(cos(max(EPSILON, clamp(x, 0.0, 1.0) * M_PI)), K0) * 0.5 + 0.5)
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1838] #define gaussian(x) exp(-1 * POW2(x))
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1839] #define is_zero(x) int(x == 0)
[  99.991][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1840] #define lanczos(x) (sinc3(x) * sinc(x))
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1841] #define quadratic(x) quadratic_(clamp((x), 0.0, 1.5))
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1842] #define quadratic_(x) TERNARY(step(x, 0.5), 0.75 - POW2(x), 0.5 * POW2((x) - 1.5))
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1843] #define sinc(x) sinc_(clamp((x), 0.0, 1.0))
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1844] #define sinc3(x) sinc_(clamp((x), 0.0, 3.0))
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1845] #define sinc_(x) TERNARY(step(x, 1e-3), 1.0, DIV(sin((x)*M_PI), ((x)*M_PI)))
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1846] #define sphinx(x) sphinx_(clamp((x), 0.0, 1.4302966531242027))
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1847] #define sphinx_(x) TERNARY(step(x, 1e-3), 1.0, DIV(3.0 * (sin((x)*M_PI) - (x)*M_PI * cos((x)*M_PI)), POW3((x)*M_PI)))
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1848] #define triangle(x) triangle_(clamp((x), 0.0, 1.0))
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1849] #define triangle_(x) (1 - (x))
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1850] 
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1851] #define MAP1(f,param) f(param)
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1852] #define MAP2(f,param) vec2(f(param.x), f(param.y))
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1853] #define MAP3(f,param) vec3(f(param.x), f(param.y), f(param.z))
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1854] 
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1855] #if defined(LUMA_raw)
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1856] #define val float
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1857] #define val_swizz(v) (v.x)
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1858] #define unval(v) vec4(v, 0, 0, poi_.a)
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1859] #define val_packed val
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1860] #define val_pack(v) (v)
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1861] #define val_unpack(v) (v)
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1862] #define MAP MAP1
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1863] #elif defined(CHROMA_raw)
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1864] #define val vec2
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1865] #define val_swizz(v) (v.xy)
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1866] #define unval(v) vec4(v.x, v.y, 0, poi_.a)
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1867] #define val_packed uint
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1868] #define val_pack(v) packUnorm2x16(v)
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1869] #define val_unpack(v) unpackUnorm2x16(v)
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1870] #define MAP MAP2
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1871] #else
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1872] #define val vec3
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1873] #define val_swizz(v) (v.xyz)
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1874] #define unval(v) vec4(v.x, v.y, v.z, poi_.a)
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1875] #define val_packed val
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1876] #define val_pack(v) (v)
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1877] #define val_unpack(v) (v)
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1878] #define MAP MAP3
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1879] #endif
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1880] 
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1881] #if D1W // float guide
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1882] #define val_guide float
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1883] #define val_guide_swizz(v) (v.x)
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1884] #define val_guide_packed float
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1885] #define val_guide_pack(v) (v)
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1886] #define val_guide_unpack(v) (v)
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1887] #define MAP_GUIDE MAP1
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1888] #define unval_guide(v) vec4(v, 0, 0, poi2_.a)
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1889] #else // val guide

[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1892] #define val_guide_packed val_packed

[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1895] #define MAP_GUIDE MAP
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1896] #if defined(LUMA_raw)
