[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1898] #elif defined(CHROMA_raw)
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1899] #define unval_guide(v) vec4(v.x, v.y, 0, poi2_.a)
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1900] #else
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1901] #define unval_guide(v) vec4(v.x, v.y, v.z, poi2_.a)
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1902] #endif
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1903] #endif
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1904] 
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1905] #if PS == 6
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1906] const int hp = P/2;
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1907] #else
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1908] const float hp = int(P/2) - 0.5*(1-(P%2)); // sample between pixels for even patch sizes
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1909] #endif
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1910] 
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1911] #if RS == 6
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1912] const int hr = R/2;
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1913] #else
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1914] const float hr = int(R/2) - 0.5*(1-(R%2)); // sample between pixels for even research sizes
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1915] #endif
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1916] 
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1917] // patch/research shapes
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1918] // each shape is depicted in a comment, where Z=5 (Z corresponds to P or R)
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1919] // dots (.) represent samples (pixels) and X represents the pixel-of-interest
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1920] 
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1921] // Z    .....
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1922] // Z    .....
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1923] // Z    ..X..
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1924] // Z    .....
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1925] // Z    .....
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1926] #define S_SQUARE(z,hz,incr) for (z.x = -hz; z.x <= hz; z.x++) for (z.y = -hz; z.y <= hz; incr)
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1927] 
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1928] // (in this instance Z=4)
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1929] // Z    ....
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1930] // Z    ....
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1931] // Z    ..X.
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1932] // Z    ....
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1933] #define S_SQUARE_EVEN(z,hz,incr) for (z.x = -hz; z.x < hz; z.x++) for (z.y = -hz; z.y < hz; incr)
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1934] 
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1935] // Z-4    .
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1936] // Z-2   ...
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1937] // Z    ..X..
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1938] #define S_TRIANGLE(z,hz,incr) for (z.y = -hz; z.y <= 0; z.y++) for (z.x = -abs(abs(z.y) - hz); z.x <= abs(abs(z.y) - hz); incr)
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1939] 
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1940] // Z-4    .
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1941] // Z-2   ...
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1942] // hz+1 ..X
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1943] #define S_TRUNC_TRIANGLE(z,hz,incr) for (z.y = -hz; z.y <= 0; z.y++) for (z.x = -abs(abs(z.y) - hz); z.x <= abs(abs(z.y) - hz)*int(z.y!=0); incr)
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1944] #define S_TRIANGLE_A(hz,Z) int(hz*hz+Z)
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1945] 
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1946] // Z-4    .
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1947] // Z-2   ...
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1948] // Z    ..X..
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1949] // Z-2   ...
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1950] // Z-4    .
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1951] #define S_DIAMOND(z,hz,incr) for (z.x = -hz; z.x <= hz; z.x++) for (z.y = -abs(abs(z.x) - hz); z.y <= abs(abs(z.x) - hz); incr)
[  99.992][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1952] #define S_DIAMOND_A(hz,Z) int(hz*hz*2+Z)
[  99.993][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1953] 
[  99.993][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1954] //
[  99.993][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1955] // Z    ..X..
[  99.993][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1956] //
[  99.993][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1957] #define S_HORIZONTAL(z,hz,incr) for (z.y = 0; z.y <= 0; z.y++) for (z.x = -hz; z.x <= hz; incr)
[  99.993][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1958] 
[  99.993][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1959] // 90 degree rotation of S_HORIZONTAL
[  99.993][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1960] #define S_VERTICAL(z,hz,incr) for (z.x = 0; z.x <= 0; z.x++) for (z.y = -hz; z.y <= hz; incr)
[  99.993][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1961] 
[  99.993][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1962] // 1      .
[  99.993][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1963] // 1      . 
[  99.993][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1964] // Z    ..X..
[  99.993][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1965] // 1      . 
[  99.993][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1966] // 1      .
[  99.993][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1967] #define S_PLUS(z,hz,incr) for (z.x = -hz; z.x <= hz; z.x++) for (z.y = -hz * int(z.x == 0); z.y <= hz * int(z.x == 0); incr)
[  99.993][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1968] #define S_PLUS_A(hz,Z) (Z*2 - 1)
[  99.993][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1969] 
[  99.993][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1970] // 3    . . .
[  99.993][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1971] // 3     ...
[  99.993][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1972] // Z    ..X..
[  99.993][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1973] // 3     ...
[  99.993][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1974] // 3    . . .
[  99.993][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1975] #define S_PLUS_X(z,hz,incr) for (z.x = -hz; z.x <= hz; z.x++) for (z.y = -abs(z.x) + -hz * int(z.x == 0); z.y <= abs(z.x) + hz * int(z.x == 0); incr)
[  99.993][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1976] #define S_PLUS_X_A(hz,Z) (Z*4 - 3)
[  99.993][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1977] 
[  99.993][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1978] // 1x1 square
[  99.993][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1979] #define S_1X1(z) for (z = vec3(0); z.x <= 0; z.x++)
[  99.993][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1980] 
[  99.993][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1981] #define T1 (T+1)
[  99.993][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1982] #define FOR_FRAME(r) for (r.z = 0; r.z < T1; r.z++)
[  99.993][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1983] 
[  99.993][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1984] // donut increment, increments without landing on (0,0,0)
[  99.993][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1985] // much faster than a continue statement
[  99.993][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1986] #define DINCR(z,c,a) ((z.c += a),(z.c += int(z == vec3(0))))
[  99.993][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1987] 
[  99.993][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1988] #define R_AREA(a) (a * T1 - 1)

[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2087] #else
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2088] #define sample(tex, pos, size, pt, off) tex((pos) + (pt) * vec2(off))
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2089] #endif
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2090] 
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2091] /* Guide images are bound through the G (luma) GC (chroma, or non-luma) 
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2092]  * textures. When bound, these are where the weights are computed. Otherwise 
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2093]  * the weights are computed on the hooked texture.
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2094]  */
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2095] 
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2096] #if GI && defined(LUMA_raw)
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2097] #define GET_(off) sample(G_tex, G_pos, G_size, G_pt, off)
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2098] #elif GI
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2099] #define GET_(off) sample(GC_tex, GC_pos, GC_size, GC_pt, off)
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2100] #else
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2101] #define GET_(off) sample(HOOKED_tex, HOOKED_pos, HOOKED_size, HOOKED_pt, off)
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2102] #endif
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2103] 
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2104] #if defined(G_raw) && (defined(LUMA_raw) || D1W)
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2105] #define GET_GUIDE_(off) sample(G_tex, G_pos, G_size, G_pt, off)
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2106] #define gather_offs(off, off_arr) (G_mul * vec4(textureGatherOffsets(G_raw, G_pos + vec2(off) * G_pt, off_arr)))
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2107] #define gather(off) G_gather(G_pos + (off) * G_pt, 0)
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2108] #elif defined(GC_raw)
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2109] #define GET_GUIDE_(off) sample(GC_tex, GC_pos, GC_size, GC_pt, off)
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2110] #else
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2111] #define GET_GUIDE_(off) GET_(off)
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2112] #define gather_offs(off, off_arr) (HOOKED_mul * vec4(textureGatherOffsets(HOOKED_raw, HOOKED_pos + vec2(off) * HOOKED_pt, off_arr)))
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2113] #define gather(off) HOOKED_gather(HOOKED_pos + (off)*HOOKED_pt, 0)
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2114] #endif
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2115] 
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2116] #if T
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2117] val GET(vec3 off)
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2118] {
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2119] 	switch (min(int(off.z), frame)) {
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2120] 	case 0: return val_swizz(GET_(off));
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2121] 
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2122] 	}
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2123] }
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2124] val GET_GUIDE(vec3 off)
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2125] {
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2126] 	return off.z == 0 ? val_guide_swizz(GET_GUIDE_(off)) : GET(off);
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2127] }
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2128] #else
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2129] #define GET(off) val_swizz(GET_(off))
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2130] #define GET_GUIDE(off) val_guide_swizz(GET_GUIDE_(off))
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2131] #endif
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2132] 
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2133] vec4 poi_ = GET_(vec3(0));
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2134] vec4 poi2_ = GET_GUIDE_(vec3(0));
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2135] val poi = val_swizz(poi_); // pixel-of-interest
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2136] val_guide poi2 = val_guide_swizz(poi2_); // guide pixel-of-interest
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2137] 
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2138] #if RI // rotation
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2139] vec2 rot(vec2 p, float d)
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2140] {
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2141] 	return vec2(
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2142] 		p.x * cos(radians(d)) - p.y * sin(radians(d)),
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2143] 		p.y * sin(radians(d)) + p.x * cos(radians(d))
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2144] 	);
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2145] }
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2146] #else
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2147] #define rot(p, d) (p)
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2148] #endif
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2149] 
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2150] #if RFI // reflection
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2151] vec2 ref(vec2 p, int d)
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2152] {
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2153] 	switch (d) {
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2154] 	case 0: return p;
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2155] 	case 1: return p * vec2(1, -1);
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2156] 	case 2: return p * vec2(-1, 1);
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2157] 	}
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2158] }
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2159] #else
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2160] #define ref(p, d) (p)
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2161] #endif
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2162] 
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2163] #if SST && R >= SST
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2164] float spatial_r(vec3 v)
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2165] {
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2166] 	v.xy += 0.5 - fract(HOOKED_pos*HOOKED_size);
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2167] 	v.z *= TD;
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2168] 	return SK(length(v)*SS);
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2169] }
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2170] #else
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2171] #define spatial_r(v) (1)
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2172] #endif
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2173] 
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2174] // 2D blur for sharpening
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2175] #if AS
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2176] float spatial_as(vec3 v)
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2177] {
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2178] 	v.xy += 0.5 - fract(HOOKED_pos*HOOKED_size);
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2179] 	return ASK(length(v)*ASS) * int(v.z == 0);
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2180] }
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2181] #endif
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2182] 
[  99.994][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2183] #if PST && P >= PST
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2184] #define spatial_p(v) PSK(length(v)*PSS)
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2185] #define normalize_p(x,expr) DIV((x), (expr))
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2186] #else
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2187] #define spatial_p(v) (1)
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2188] #define normalize_p(x,expr) ((x) * p_scale)
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2189] #endif
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2190] 
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2191] const float pdiff_scale = 1.0/max(EPSILON,POW2(S*0.013));
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2192] val_guide range(val_guide pdiff_sq)
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2193] {
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2194] 	pdiff_sq = sqrt(abs(pdiff_sq - max(EPSILON, RO)) * pdiff_scale);
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2195] 	return RK(pdiff_sq);
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2196] }
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2197] 
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2198] #define GATHER (PD == 0 && NG == 0 && SAMPLE == 0) // never textureGather if any of these conditions are false
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2199] #define REGULAR_ROTATIONS (RI == 0 || RI == 1 || RI == 3 || RI == 7)
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2200] 
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2201] #if (defined(LUMA_gather) || D1W) && ((PS == 0 || ((PS == 3 || PS == 7) && RI != 7) || PS == 8) && P == 3) && REGULAR_ROTATIONS && GATHER
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2202] // 3x3 diamond/plus or square patch_comparison_gather
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2203] const ivec2 offsets_adj[4] = { ivec2(0,-1), ivec2(1,0), ivec2(0,1), ivec2(-1,0) };
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2204] const ivec2 offsets_adj_sf[4] = { ivec2(0,-1) * SF, ivec2(1,0) * SF, ivec2(0,1) * SF, ivec2(-1,0) * SF };
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2205] vec4 poi_patch_adj = gather_offs(0, offsets_adj);
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2206] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2207] const ivec2 offsets_diag[4] = { ivec2(-1,-1), ivec2(1,-1), ivec2(1,1), ivec2(-1,1) };
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2208] const ivec2 offsets_diag_sf[4] = { ivec2(-1,-1) * SF, ivec2(1,-1) * SF, ivec2(1,1) * SF, ivec2(-1,1) * SF };
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2209] vec4 poi_patch_diag = gather_offs(0, offsets_diag);
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2210] #endif
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2211] float patch_comparison_gather(vec3 r)
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2212] {
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2213] 	float min_rot = p_area - 1;
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2214] 	vec4 transformer_adj = gather_offs(r, offsets_adj_sf);
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2215] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2216] 	vec4 transformer_diag = gather_offs(r, offsets_diag_sf);
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2217] #endif
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2218] 	FOR_ROTATION {
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2219] 		FOR_REFLECTION {
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2220] #if RFI
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2221] 			/* xxy
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2222] 			 * w y
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2223] 			 * wzz
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2224] 			 */
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2225] 			switch(rfi) {
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2226] 			case 1:
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2227] 				transformer_adj = transformer_adj.zyxw;
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2228] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2229] 				transformer_diag = transformer_diag.zyxw;
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2230] #endif
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2231] 				break;
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2232] 			case 2:
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2233] 				transformer_adj = transformer_adj.xwzy;
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2234] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2235] 				transformer_diag = transformer_diag.xwzy;
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2236] #endif
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2237] 				break;
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2238] 			}
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2239] #endif
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2240] 
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2241] 			vec4 pdiff_sq = POW2(poi_patch_adj - transformer_adj) * spatial_p(vec2(1,0));
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2242] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2243] 			pdiff_sq += POW2(poi_patch_diag - transformer_diag) * spatial_p(vec2(1,1));
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2244] #endif
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2245] 			min_rot = min(dot(pdiff_sq, vec4(1)), min_rot);
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2246] 
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2247] // un-reflect
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2248] #if RFI
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2249] 			switch(rfi) {
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2250] 			case 1:
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2251] 				transformer_adj = transformer_adj.zyxw;
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2252] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2253] 				transformer_diag = transformer_diag.zyxw;
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2254] #endif
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2255] 				break;
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2256] 			case 2:
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2257] 				transformer_adj = transformer_adj.xwzy;
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2258] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2259] 				transformer_diag = transformer_diag.xwzy;
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2260] #endif
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2261] 				break;
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2262] 			}
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2263] #endif
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2264] 		} // FOR_REFLECTION
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2265] #if RI == 7
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2266] 		transformer_adj = transformer_adj.wxyz;
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2267] 		// swap adjacents for diagonals
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2268] 		transformer_adj += transformer_diag;
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2269] 		transformer_diag = transformer_adj - transformer_diag;
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2270] 		transformer_adj -= transformer_diag;
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2271] #elif RI == 3
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2272] 		transformer_adj = transformer_adj.wxyz;
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2273] #elif RI == 1
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2274] 		transformer_adj = transformer_adj.zwxy;
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2275] #endif
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2276] #if RI == 3 && (PS == 0 || PS == 8)
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2277] 		transformer_diag = transformer_diag.wxyz;
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2278] #elif RI == 1 && (PS == 0 || PS == 8)
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2279] 		transformer_diag = transformer_diag.zwxy;
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2280] #endif
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2281] 	} // FOR_ROTATION
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2282] 	
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2283] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2284] 	float total_weight = spatial_p(vec2(0,0)) + 4 * spatial_p(vec2(0,1)) + 4 * spatial_p(vec2(1,1));
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2285] #else
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2286] 	float total_weight = spatial_p(vec2(0,0)) + 4 * spatial_p(vec2(0,1));
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2287] #endif
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2288] 
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2289] 	float center_diff = poi2.x - GET_GUIDE(r).x;
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2290] 	return normalize_p(POW2(center_diff) + min_rot, max(EPSILON,total_weight));
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2291] }
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2292] #elif (defined(LUMA_gather) || D1W) && PS == 4 && P == 3 && RI == 0 && RFI == 0 && GATHER
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2293] const ivec2 offsets[4] = { ivec2(0,-1), ivec2(-1,0), ivec2(0,0), ivec2(1,0) };
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2294] const ivec2 offsets_sf[4] = { ivec2(0,-1) * SF, ivec2(-1,0) * SF, ivec2(0,0) * SF, ivec2(1,0) * SF };
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2295] vec4 poi_patch = gather_offs(0, offsets);
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2296] vec4 spatial_p_weights = vec4(spatial_p(vec2(0,-1)), spatial_p(vec2(-1,0)), spatial_p(vec2(0,0)), spatial_p(vec2(1,0)));
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2297] float patch_comparison_gather(vec3 r)
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2298] {
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2299] 	vec4 pdiff = poi_patch - gather_offs(r, offsets_sf);
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2300] 	return normalize_p(
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2301] 		dot(POW2(pdiff) * spatial_p_weights, vec4(1)),
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2302] 		dot(spatial_p_weights, vec4(1))
[  99.995][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2303] 	);
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2304] }
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2305] #elif (defined(LUMA_gather) || D1W) && PS == 6 && RI == 0 && RFI == 0 && GATHER
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2306] // tiled even square patch_comparison_gather
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2307] // XXX extend to support odd square?
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2308] float patch_comparison_gather(vec3 r)
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2309] {
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2310] 	/* gather order:
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2311] 	 * w z
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2312] 	 * x y
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2313] 	 */
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2314] 	vec2 tile;
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2315] 	float pdiff_sq = 0;
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2316] 	float total_weight = 0;
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2317] 	for (tile.x = -hp; tile.x < hp; tile.x+=2) for (tile.y = -hp; tile.y < hp; tile.y+=2) {
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2318] 		vec4 diff = gather(tile + r.xy) - gather(tile);
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2319] 		vec4 weights = vec4(spatial_p(tile+vec2(0,1)), spatial_p(tile+vec2(1,1)), spatial_p(tile+vec2(1,0)), spatial_p(tile+vec2(0,0)));
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2320] 		pdiff_sq += dot(POW2(diff) * weights, vec4(1));
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2321] 		total_weight += dot(weights, vec4(1));
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2322] 	}
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2323] 
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2324] 	return normalize_p(pdiff_sq, max(EPSILON,total_weight));
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2325] }
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2326] #else
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2327] #define patch_comparison_gather patch_comparison
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2328] #define STORE_POI_PATCH 1
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2329] val_guide poi_patch[p_area];
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2330] #endif
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2331] 
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2332] val_guide patch_comparison(vec3 r)
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2333] {
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2334] 	vec3 p;
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2335] 	val_guide min_rot = val_guide(p_area);
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2336] 
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2337] 	FOR_ROTATION FOR_REFLECTION {
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2338] 		val_guide pdiff_sq = val_guide(0);
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2339] 		float total_weight = 0;
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2340] 
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2341] 		int p_index = 0;
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2342] 		FOR_PATCH(p) {
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2343] #ifdef STORE_POI_PATCH
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2344] 			val_guide poi_p = poi_patch[p_index++];
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2345] #else
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2346] 			val_guide poi_p = GET_GUIDE(p);
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2347] #endif
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2348] 			vec3 transformed_p = SF * vec3(ref(rot(p.xy, ri), rfi), p.z);
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2349] 			val_guide diff_sq = poi_p - GET_GUIDE(transformed_p + r);
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2350] 			diff_sq *= diff_sq;
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2351] 
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2352] 			float weight = spatial_p(p.xy);
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2353] 			pdiff_sq += diff_sq * weight;
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2354] 			total_weight += weight;
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2355] 		}
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2356] 
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2357] 		min_rot = min(min_rot, normalize_p(pdiff_sq, max(EPSILON,total_weight)));
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2358] 	}
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2359] 
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2360] 	return min_rot;
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2361] }
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2362] 
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2363] vec4 hook()
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2364] {
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2365] 	val_guide total_weight = val_guide(0);
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2366] 	val sum = val(0);
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2367] 	val result = val(0);
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2368] 
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2369] 	vec3 r = vec3(0);
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2370] 	vec3 me = vec3(0);
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2371] 
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2372] 	float sw = SW * spatial_r(vec3(0));
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2373] 
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2374] #if T && ME == 1 // temporal & motion estimation
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2375] 	vec3 me_tmp = vec3(0);
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2376] 	float maxweight = 0;
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2377] #elif T && ME == 2 // temporal & motion estimation
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2378] 	vec3 me_sum = vec3(0);
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2379] 	float me_weight = 0;
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2380] #endif
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2381] 
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2382] #if AS
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2383] 	float total_weight_as = 0;
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2384] 	val sum_as = val(0);
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2385] #endif
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2386] 
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2387] #if WD == 2 || V == 7 || C
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2388] #define STORE_WEIGHTS 1
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2389] #else
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2390] #define STORE_WEIGHTS 0
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2391] #endif
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2392] 
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2393] #if STORE_WEIGHTS
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2394] 	int r_index = 0;
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2395] 	val_guide_packed all_weights[r_area];
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2396] 	val_packed all_pixels[r_area];
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2397] #endif
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2398] 
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2399] #ifdef STORE_POI_PATCH
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2400] 	vec3 p;
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2401] 	int p_index = 0;
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2402] 	FOR_PATCH(p)
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2403] 		poi_patch[p_index++] = GET_GUIDE(p);
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2404] #endif
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2405] 	
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2406] #if WD == 1 // weight discard (moving cumulative average)
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2407] 	int r_iter = 1;
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2408] 	val_guide wd_total_weight = val_guide(0);
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2409] 	val wd_sum = val(0);
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2410] #endif
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2411] 
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2412] #if V == 7
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2413] 	vec2 v7cell = floor(HOOKED_size/R * HOOKED_pos) * R + hr;
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2414] 	vec2 v7cell_off = floor(HOOKED_pos * HOOKED_size) - floor(v7cell);
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2415] #endif
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2416] 
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2417] 	FOR_FRAME(r) {
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2418] 	// XXX ME is always a frame behind, should have the option to re-research after applying ME (could do it an arbitrary number of times per frame if desired)
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2419] #if T && ME == 1 // temporal & motion estimation max weight
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2420] 	if (r.z > 0) {
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2421] 		me += me_tmp * MEF;
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2422] 		me_tmp = vec3(0);
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2423] 		maxweight = 0;
[  99.996][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2424] 	}
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2425] #elif T && ME == 2 // temporal & motion estimation weighted average
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2426] 	if (r.z > 0) {
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2427] 		me += round(DIV(me_sum, me_weight) * MEF);
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2428] 		me_sum = vec3(0);
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2429] 		me_weight = 0;
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2430] 	}
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2431] #endif
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2432] 	FOR_RESEARCH(r) {
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2433] #if V == 7
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2434] 		r.xy += v7cell_off;
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2435] #endif
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2436] 
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2437] 		// r coords with appropriate transformations applied
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2438] 		vec3 tr = vec3(r.xy + floor(r.xy * RSF), r.z);
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2439] 		tr.xy += me.xy;
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2440] 
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2441] 		val px = GET(tr);
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2442] 
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2443] #if SKIP_PATCH
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2444] 		val weight = val(1);
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2445] #else
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2446] 		val_guide pdiff_sq = (r.z == 0) ? patch_comparison_gather(tr) : patch_comparison(tr);
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2447] 		val_guide weight = range(pdiff_sq);
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2448] #endif
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2449] 
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2450] #if T && ME == 1 // temporal & motion estimation max weight
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2451] 		me_tmp = vec3(tr.xy,0) * step(maxweight, weight.x) + me_tmp * (1 - step(maxweight, weight.x));
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2452] 		maxweight = max(maxweight, weight.x);
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2453] #elif T && ME == 2 // temporal & motion estimation weighted average
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2454] 		me_sum += vec3(tr.xy,0) * weight.x;
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2455] 		me_weight += weight.x;
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2456] #endif
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2457] 
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2458] 		weight *= spatial_r(r);
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2459] 
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2460] #if AS
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2461] 		float spatial_as_weight = spatial_as(tr);
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2462] 		sum_as += px * spatial_as_weight;
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2463] 		total_weight_as += spatial_as_weight;
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2464] #endif
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2465] 
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2466] #if WD == 1 // weight discard (moving cumulative average)
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2467] 		float wd_scale = RECIPROCAL(r_iter);
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2468] 
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2469] 		val_guide below_threshold = WDS * abs(min(val_guide(0.0), weight - (total_weight * wd_scale * WDT * WD1TK(sqrt(wd_scale*WDP)))));
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2470] 		val_guide wdkf = MAP_GUIDE(WDK, below_threshold);
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2471] 
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2472] 		wd_sum += px * weight * wdkf;
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2473] 		wd_total_weight += weight * wdkf;
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2474] 		r_iter++;
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2475] #if STORE_WEIGHTS
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2476] 		all_weights[r_index] = val_guide_pack(weight * wdkf);
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2477] 		all_pixels[r_index] = val_pack(px);
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2478] 		r_index++;
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2479] #endif
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2480] #elif STORE_WEIGHTS
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2481] 		all_weights[r_index] = val_guide_pack(weight);
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2482] 		all_pixels[r_index] = val_pack(px);
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2483] 		r_index++;
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2484] #endif
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2485] 
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2486] #if V == 7
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2487] 		r.xy -= v7cell_off;
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2488] #endif
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2489] 
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2490] 		sum += px * weight;
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2491] 		total_weight += weight;
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2492] 	} // FOR_RESEARCH
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2493] 	} // FOR_FRAME
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2494] 
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2495] 	val_guide avg_weight = total_weight * r_scale;
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2496] 
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2497] #if defined(LUMA_raw) && V == 4
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2498] 	return unval_guide(avg_weight);
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2499] #elif defined(CHROMA_raw) && V == 4
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2500] 	return vec4(0.5); // XXX visualize for chroma
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2501] #endif
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2502] 
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2503] #if C
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2504] 	total_weight = val_guide(0);
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2505] 	sum = val(0);
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2506] 
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2507] 	for (int c = 0; c <= C; c++) {
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2508] 		val_guide_packed all_weights_update[r_area];
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2509] 
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2510] 		r_index = 0;
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2511] 		FOR_FRAME(r) FOR_RESEARCH(r) {
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2512] 			val_guide c_sum = val_guide(0);
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2513] 			vec3 r2 = vec3(0);
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2514] 			int r2_index = 0;
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2515] 			FOR_FRAME(r2) FOR_RESEARCH(r2)
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2516] 				if (distance(r, r2) - sqrt(CD) <= FLT_EPSILON)
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2517] 					c_sum += val_guide_unpack(all_weights[r2_index++]);
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2518] 			if (length(r) - sqrt(CD) <= FLT_EPSILON)
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2519] 				c_sum += sw;
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2520] 			all_weights_update[r_index++] = val_guide_pack(c_sum);
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2521] 		}
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2522] 
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2523] 		r_index = 0;
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2524] 		FOR_FRAME(r) FOR_RESEARCH(r) {
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2525] 			val_guide old_weight = val_guide_unpack(all_weights[r_index]);
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2526] 			val_guide update = val_guide_unpack(all_weights_update[r_index]);
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2527] 			val_guide weight = old_weight * RECIPROCAL(max(EPSILON,CS))
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2528] 			                 + old_weight * update * r1_scale * CS;
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2529] 			all_weights[r_index] = val_guide_pack(weight);
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2530] 			if (c == C) { // only need to update this stuff on the final C iteration
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2531] 				val px = val_unpack(all_pixels[r_index]);
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2532] 				sum += px * weight;
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2533] 				total_weight += weight;
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2534] 				all_pixels[r_index] = val_pack(px);
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2535] 			}
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2536] 			r_index++;
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2537] 		}
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2538] 	} // for C
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2539] #endif
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2540] 
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2541] #if WD == 2 // weight discard (mean)
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2542] 	total_weight = val_guide(0);
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2543] 	sum = val(0);
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2544] 
[  99.997][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2545] 	r_index = 0;
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2546] 	FOR_FRAME(r) FOR_RESEARCH(r) {
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2547] 		val px = val_unpack(all_pixels[r_index]);
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2548] 		val_guide weight = val_guide_unpack(all_weights[r_index]);
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2549] 
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2550] 		val_guide below_threshold = WDS * abs(min(val_guide(0.0), weight - (avg_weight * WDT)));
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2551] 		weight *= MAP_GUIDE(WDK, below_threshold);
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2552] 
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2553] 		sum += px * weight;
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2554] 		total_weight += weight;
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2555] #if V == 7
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2556] 		all_pixels[r_index] = val_pack(px);
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2557] 		all_weights[r_index] = val_guide_pack(weight);
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2558] #endif
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2559] 		r_index++;
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2560] 	} // FOR_FRAME FOR_RESEARCH
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2561] #endif
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2562] 
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2563] #if WD == 1 // weight discard (moving cumulative average)
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2564] 	total_weight = wd_total_weight;
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2565] 	sum = wd_sum;
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2566] #endif
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2567] 
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2568] #if WD // weight discard
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2569] 	avg_weight = total_weight * r_scale;
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2570] #endif
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2571] 
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2572] 	total_weight += sw;
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2573] 	sum += poi * sw;
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2574] 	result = MED_DIV(sum, max(val(EPSILON),val(total_weight)));
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2575] 
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2576] 	// store frames for temporal
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2577] #if T > 1
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2578] 
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2579] #endif
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2580] #if T && TRF
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2581] 	imageStore(PREV1, ivec2(HOOKED_pos*HOOKED_size), unval(result));
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2582] #elif T
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2583] 	imageStore(PREV1, ivec2(HOOKED_pos*HOOKED_size), unval_guide(poi2));
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2584] #endif
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2585] 
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2586] #if AS == 1 // sharpen+denoise
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2587] #define AS_base result
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2588] #elif AS == 2 // sharpen only
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2589] #define AS_base poi
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2590] #endif
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2591] 
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2592] #if ASI == 0
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2593] #define AS_input result
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2594] #elif ASI == 1
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2595] #define AS_input poi
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2596] #endif
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2597] 
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2598] #if AS // sharpening
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2599] 	val usm = AS_input - MED_DIV(sum_as, max(EPSILON,total_weight_as));
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2600] 	usm = POW(usm, ASP);
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2601] 	const float as_scale_15 = 1.0/1.5;
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2602] 	usm *= ASAK(abs((AS_base + usm - 0.5) * as_scale_15) * ASA);
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2603] 	usm *= ASF;
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2604] 	result = AS_base + usm;
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2605] #endif
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2606] 
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2607] #if EP // extremes preserve
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2608] 	float luminance = EP_texOff(0).x;
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2609] 	float ep_weight = POW(max(EPSILON, min(1-luminance, luminance)*2), (luminance < 0.5 ? DP : BP));
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2610] 	result = mix(poi, result, ep_weight);
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2611] #else
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2612] 	float ep_weight = 0;
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2613] #endif
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2614] 
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2615] #if V == 1
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2616] 	result = clamp(pow(abs(poi - result), val(0.25)), 0.0, 1.0);
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2617] #elif V == 2
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2618] 	result = (poi - result) * 0.5 + 0.5;
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2619] #elif V == 3
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2620] 	result = val(avg_weight);
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2621] #elif V == 5
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2622] 	result = 0.5 + usm;
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2623] #elif V == 6
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2624] 	result = val(1 - ep_weight);
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2625] #elif V == 7
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2626] 	result = val(0);
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2627] 	r_index = 0;
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2628] 	FOR_FRAME(r) FOR_RESEARCH(r) {
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2629] 		if (v7cell_off == r.xy)
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2630] 			result = val_guide_unpack(all_weights[r_index]);
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2631] 		r_index++;
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2632] 	}
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2633] 
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2634] 	if (v7cell_off == vec2(0,0))
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2635] 		result = val(SW * spatial_r(vec3(0)));
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2636] #endif
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2637] 
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2638] // XXX visualize chroma for these
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2639] #if defined(CHROMA_raw) && (V == 3 || V == 4 || V == 6 || V == 7)
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2640] 	return vec4(0.5);
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2641] #endif
[  99.998][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [2642]

[ 100.030][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 72] 
[ 100.030][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 73] // Denoising factor (sigma, higher means more blur)
[ 100.030][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 74] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.030][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 75] #define S 2.171842300643018
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 76] #else
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 77] #define S 3.472706940155897
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 78] #endif
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 79] 
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 80] /* Noise resistant adaptive sharpening
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 81]  *
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 82]  * AS:
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 83]  * 	 - 0: disable
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 84]  * 	 - 1: sharpen+denoise
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 85]  * 	 - 2: sharpen only
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 86]  * ASF: Higher numbers make a sharper image
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 87]  * ASA: Anti-ringing, higher numbers increase strength
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 88]  * ASP: Power, lower numbers increase sharpening on lower frequency detail
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 89]  * ASS: Equivalent to SS but for ASK instead of SK
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 90]  * ASI:
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 91]  *  - 0: don't sharpen noise
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 92]  *  - 1: sharpen noise
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 93]  */
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 94] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 95] #define AS 0
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 96] #define ASF 0.0
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 97] #define ASA 0.0
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 98] #define ASP 0.0
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 99] #define ASS 0.0
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [100] #define ASI 0
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [101] #else
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [102] #define AS 0
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [103] #define ASF 0.0
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [104] #define ASA 0.0
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [105] #define ASP 0.0
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [106] #define ASS 0.0
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [107] #define ASI 0
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [108] #endif
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [109] 
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [110] /* Starting weight
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [111]  *
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [112]  * AKA the center weight, the weight of the pixel-of-interest.
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [113]  */
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [114] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [115] #define SW 0.874631892412684
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [116] #else
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [117] #define SW 0.3493678781214755
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [118] #endif
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [119] 
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [120] /* Spatial kernel
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [121]  *
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [122]  * Increasing the spatial sigma (SS) reduces the weight of further 
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [123]  * pixels.
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [124]  *
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [125]  * The intra-patch variants might help with larger patch sizes.
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [126]  *
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [127]  * SST: enables spatial kernel if R>=PST, 0 fully disables
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [128]  * SS: spatial sigma
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [129]  * PSS: intra-patch spatial sigma
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [130]  * PST: enables intra-patch spatial kernel if P>=PST, 0 fully disables
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [131]  */
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [132] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [133] #define SST 1
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [134] #define SS 0.1786363425615082
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [135] #define PST 0
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [136] #define PSS 0.0
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [137] #else
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [138] #define SST 1
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [139] #define SS 0.3241999209926485
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [140] #define PST 0
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [141] #define PSS 0.0
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [142] #endif
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [143] 
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [144] /* Extremes preserve
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [145]  *
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [146]  * This setting is dependent on code generation from shader_cfg, so this 
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [147]  * setting can only be enabled via shader_cfg.
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [148]  *
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [149]  * Reduce denoising in very bright/dark areas.
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [150]  *
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [151]  * The downscaling factor of the EP shader stage affects the size of the area 
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [152]  * checked for luminance.
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [153]  *
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [154]  * This is incompatible with RGB. If you have RGB hooks enabled then you will 
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [155]  * have to delete the EP shader stage or specify EP=0 through shader_cfg.
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [156]  *
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [157]  * EP: 1 to enable, 0 to disable
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [158]  * DP: EP strength on dark areas, 0 to fully denoise
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [159]  * BP: EP strength on bright areas, 0 to fully denoise
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [160]  */
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [161] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [162] #define EP 0
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [163] #define BP 0.0
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [164] #define DP 0.0
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [165] #else
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [166] #define EP 0
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [167] #define BP 0.0
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [168] #define DP 0.0
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [169] #endif
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [170] 
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [171] /* ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS */

[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [177] /* textureGather applicable configurations:
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [178]  *
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [179]  * - PS={0,3,7,8}:P=3:RI={0,1,3,7}:RFI={0,1,2}
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [180]  * - PS={0,8}:P=3:RI={0,1,3,7}:RFI={0,1,2}
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [181]  * - PS=4:P=3:PST=0:RI=0:RFI=0
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [182]  * - PS=6:RI=0:RFI=0
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [183]  *   - Currently the only scalable variant
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [184]  *
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [185]  * Options which always disable textureGather:
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [186]  * 	 - NG
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [187]  * 	 - SAMPLE
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [188]  * 	 - PD
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [189]  *
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [190]  * Running without textureGather may be much slower.
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [191]  */
[ 100.031][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [192] 
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [193] /* Patch & research sizes
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [194]  *
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [195]  * P should be an odd number. Higher values are slower and not always better.
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [196]  *
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [197]  * R should be an odd number greater than or equal to 3. Higher values are 
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [198]  * generally better, but slower.
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [199]  */
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [200] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [201] #define P 3
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [202] #define R 5
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [203] #else
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [204] #define P 3
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [205] #define R 5
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [206] #endif
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [207] 
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [208] /* Patch and research shapes
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [209]  *
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [210]  * Different shapes have different speed and quality characteristics. Every 
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [211]  * shape (besides square) is smaller than square.
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [212]  *
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [213]  * PS applies applies to patches, RS applies to research zones.
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [214]  *
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [215]  * 0: square (symmetrical)
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [216]  * 1: horizontal line (asymmetric)
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [217]  * 2: vertical line (asymmetric)
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [218]  * 3: diamond (symmetrical)
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [219]  * 4: triangle (asymmetric, pointing upward)
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [220]  * 5: truncated triangle (asymmetric on two axis, last row halved)
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [221]  * 6: even sized square (asymmetric on two axis)
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [222]  * 7: plus (symmetrical)
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [223]  * 8: plus X (symmetrical)
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [224]  */
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [225] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [226] #define RS 3
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [227] #define PS 0
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [228] #else
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [229] #define RS 3
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [230] #define PS 3
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [231] #endif
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [232] 
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [233] /* Weight discard
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [234]  *
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [235]  * Reduces weights that fall below a fraction of the average weight. This culls 
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [236]  * the most dissimilar samples from the blur, which can yield a better result, 
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [237]  * especially around edges.
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [238]  * 
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [239]  * WD:
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [240]  * 	 - 2: Mean. Better quality, but slower and requires GLSL 4.0 or later
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [241]  * 	 - 1: Moving cumulative average. Fast but inaccurate, blurs directionally.
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [242]  * 	 - 0: Disable
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [243]  *
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [244]  * WDT: Threshold coefficient, higher numbers discard more
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [245]  * WDP (only for WD=1): Increasing reduces the threshold for small sample sizes
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [246]  * WDS (not for WDK=is_zero): Higher numbers are more eager to reduce weights
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [247]  */
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [248] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [249] #define WD 1
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [250] #define WDT 0.2935708849017379
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [251] #define WDP 1.2788519721382683
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [252] #define WDS 1.0
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [253] #else
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [254] #define WD 0
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [255] #define WDT 0.0
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [256] #define WDP 0.0
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [257] #define WDS 1.0
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [258] #endif
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [259] 
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [260] /* Connectivity
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [261]  *
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [262]  * Increases weights that are near high weights, decreases weights that are 
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [263]  * near low weights.
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [264]  *
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [265]  * C: Number of passes to do, more increases the effect, 0 does nothing
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [266]  * CD: Distance between each pixel and its furthest neighbor
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [267]  * CS: Strength of effect, higher is more
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [268]  */
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [269] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [270] #define C 0
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [271] #define CD 1.0
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [272] #define CS 1.0
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [273] #else
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [274] #define C 0
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [275] #define CD 1.0
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [276] #define CS 1.0
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [277] #endif
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [278] 
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [279] /* Rotational/reflectional invariance
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [280]  *
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [281]  * Number of rotations/reflections to try for each patch comparison. Can be 
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [282]  * slow, but may improve feature preservation. More rotations/reflections gives 
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [283]  * diminishing returns. The most similar rotation/reflection is used.
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [284]  *
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [285]  * The angle in degrees of each rotation is 360/(RI+1), so RI=1 will do a 
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [286]  * single 180 degree rotation, RI=3 will do three 90 degree rotations, etc.
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [287]  *
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [288]  * Consider setting SAMPLE=1 if setting RI to a setting that would require 
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [289]  * sampling between pixels.
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [290]  *
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [291]  * RI: Rotational invariance
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [292]  * RFI (0 to 2): Reflectional invariance
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [293]  */
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [294] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [295] #define RI 0
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [296] #define RFI 2
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [297] #else
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [298] #define RI 0
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [299] #define RFI 0
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [300] #endif
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [301] 
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [302] /* Temporal denoising
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [303]  *
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [304]  * This setting is dependent on code generation from shader_cfg, so this 
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [305]  * setting can only be enabled via shader_cfg.
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [306]  *
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [307]  * Caveats:
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [308]  * 	 - Slower:
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [309]  * 	 	 - Gather optimizations only apply to the current frame
[ 100.032][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [310]  * 	 - Requires vo=gpu-next
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [311]  * 	 - Luma-only (this is a bug)
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [312]  * 	 - Buggy
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [313]  *
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [314]  * May cause motion blur and may struggle more with noise that persists across 
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [315]  * multiple frames (e.g., from compression or duplicate frames).
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [316]  *
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [317]  * Motion estimation (ME) should improve quality without impacting speed.
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [318]  *
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [319]  * Increasing temporal distortion (TD) can reduce motion blur.
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [320]  *
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [321]  * T: number of frames used
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [322]  * ME: motion estimation, 0 for none, 1 for max weight, 2 for weighted avg
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [323]  * MEF: estimate factor, compensates for ME being one frame behind
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [324]  * TRF: compare against the denoised frames
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [325]  * TD: temporal distortion, higher numbers give less weight to previous frames
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [326]  */
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [327] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [328] #define T 0
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [329] #define ME 1
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [330] #define MEF 2
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [331] #define TRF 0
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [332] #define TD 1.0
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [333] #else
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [334] #define T 0
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [335] #define ME 0
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [336] #define MEF 2
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [337] #define TRF 0
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [338] #define TD 1.0
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [339] #endif
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [340] 
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [341] /* Kernels
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [342]  *
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [343]  * SK: spatial kernel
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [344]  * RK: range kernel (takes patch differences)
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [345]  * ASK: adaptive sharpening kernel
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [346]  * PSK: intra-patch spatial kernel
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [347]  * WDK: weight discard kernel
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [348]  * WD1TK (WD=1 only): weight discard tolerance kernel
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [349]  *
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [350]  * List of available kernels:
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [351]  *
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [352]  * bicubic
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [353]  * cos
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [354]  * ffexp
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [355]  * gaussian
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [356]  * lanczos
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [357]  * quadratic
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [358]  * quadratic_ (unclamped)
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [359]  * sinc
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [360]  * sinc3
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [361]  * sinc_ (unclamped)
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [362]  * sphinx
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [363]  * sphinx_ (unclamped)
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [364]  * triangle
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [365]  * triangle_ (unclamped)
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [366]  */
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [367] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [368] #define SK gaussian
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [369] #define RK gaussian
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [370] #define ASK sinc
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [371] #define ASAK gaussian
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [372] #define PSK gaussian
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [373] #define WDK is_zero
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [374] #define WD1TK gaussian
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [375] #else
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [376] #define SK gaussian
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [377] #define RK gaussian
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [378] #define ASK sphinx_
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [379] #define ASAK gaussian
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [380] #define PSK gaussian
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [381] #define WDK is_zero
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [382] #define WD1TK gaussian
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [383] #endif
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [384] 
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [385] /* Kernel parameters
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [386]  *
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [387]  * The following kernels take parameters:
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [388]  *
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [389]  * ffexp: K0
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [390]  */
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [391] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [392] #define K0 1.0
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [393] #define K1 1.0
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [394] #else
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [395] #define K0 1.0
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [396] #define K1 1.0
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [397] #endif
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [398] 
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [399] /* Negative kernel parameter offsets
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [400]  *
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [401]  * Usually kernels go high -> low. These parameters allow for a kernel to go 
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [402]  * low -> high -> low.
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [403]  *
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [404]  * Values of 0.0 mean no effect, higher values increase the effect.
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [405]  *
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [406]  * RO: range kernel (takes patch differences)
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [407]  */
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [408] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [409] #define RO 6.373764517041128e-05
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [410] #else
[ 100.033][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [411] #define RO 0.0
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [412] #endif
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [413] 
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [414] /* Sampling method
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [415]  *
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [416]  * In most cases this shouldn't make any difference, only set to bilinear if 
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [417]  * it's necessary to sample between pixels (e.g., RI=2).
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [418]  *
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [419]  * 0: nearest neighbor
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [420]  * 1: bilinear
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [421]  */
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [422] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [423] #define SAMPLE 0
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [424] #else
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [425] #define SAMPLE 0
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [426] #endif
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [427] 
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [428] /* Research scaling factor
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [429]  *
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [430]  * Higher numbers sample more sparsely as the distance from the POI grows.
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [431]  */
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [432] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [433] #define RSF 0.0
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [434] #else
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [435] #define RSF 0.0
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [436] #endif
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [437] 
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [438] // Scaling factor (should match WIDTH/HEIGHT)
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [439] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [440] #define SF 1
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [441] #else
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [442] #define SF 1
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [443] #endif
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [444] 
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [445] // Use the guide image as the input image
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [446] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [447] #define GI 0
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [448] #else
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [449] #define GI 0
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [450] #endif
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [451] 
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [452] /* Visualization
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [453]  *
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [454]  * 0: off
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [455]  * 1: absolute difference between input/output to the power of 0.25
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [456]  * 2: difference between input/output centered on 0.5
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [457]  * 3: post-WD average weight map
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [458]  * 4: pre-WD average weight map
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [459]  * 5: unsharp mask
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [460]  * 6: EP
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [461]  * 7: celled weight map (incompatible with temporal)
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [462]  */
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [463] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [464] #define V 0
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [465] #else
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [466] #define V 0
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [467] #endif
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [468] 
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [469] // Fast approximate division
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [470] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [471] #define FAST_DIV 0
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [472] #else
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [473] #define FAST_DIV 0
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [474] #endif
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [475] 
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [476] // Force disable textureGather
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [477] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [478] #define NG 0
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [479] #else
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [480] #define NG 0
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [481] #endif
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [482] 
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [483] // Patch donut (probably useless)
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [484] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [485] #define PD 0
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [486] #else
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [487] #define PD 0
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [488] #endif
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [489] 
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [490] // Duplicate 1st weight (for luma-guided-chroma)
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [491] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [492] #define D1W 0
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [493] #else
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [494] #define D1W 0
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [495] #endif
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [496] 
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [497] // Skip patch comparison
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [498] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [499] #define SKIP_PATCH 0
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [500] #else
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [501] #define SKIP_PATCH 0
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [502] #endif
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [503] 
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [504] // Shader code
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [505] 
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [506] #define EPSILON 1.2e-38
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [507] #define FLT_EPSILON 1.19209290E-07
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [508] #define M_PI 3.14159265358979323846
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [509] #define POW2(x) ((x)*(x))
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [510] #define POW3(x) ((x)*(x)*(x))
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [511] 
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [512] // pow() implementation that gives -pow() when x<0
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [513] // avoids actually calling pow() since apparently it's buggy on nvidia
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [514] #define POW(x,y) (exp(log(abs(x)) * y) * sign(x))
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [515] 
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [516] // boolean logic w/ vectors
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [517] // from hdeband
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [518] #define NOT(x) (1 - (x))
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [519] #define AND *
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [520] #define TERNARY(cond, x, y) ((x)*(cond) + (y)*NOT(cond))
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [521] 
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [522] // from FSR
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [523] #if FAST_DIV
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [524] #define RECIPROCAL(x) uintBitsToFloat(uint(0x7ef07ebb) - floatBitsToUint(x))
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [525] #define DIV(x,y) ((x) * RECIPROCAL(y))
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [526] #define MED_RCP_B(x) uintBitsToFloat(uint(0x7ef19fff) - floatBitsToUint(x))
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [527] #define MED_RECIPROCAL(x) (MED_RCP_B(x) * (-MED_RCP_B(x) * x + 2))
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [528] #define MED_DIV(x,y) ((x) * MED_RECIPROCAL(y))
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [529] #else
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [530] #define RECIPROCAL(x) (1.0/(x))
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [531] #define MED_RECIPROCAL(x) (1.0/(x))
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [532] #define DIV(x,y) ((x)/(y))
[ 100.034][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [533] #define MED_DIV(x,y) ((x)/(y))
[ 100.035][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [534] #endif
[ 100.035][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [535] 
[ 100.035][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [536] // XXX make kernel params capable of being set per-kernel, e.g., RK0, SK0...
[ 100.035][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [537] 
[ 100.035][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [538] // kernels
[ 100.035][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [539] // XXX sinc & sphinx: 1e-3 was selected tentatively;  not sure what the correct value should be (1e-8 is too low)
[ 100.035][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [540] #define bicubic(x) bicubic_(clamp((x), 0.0, 2.0))
[ 100.035][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [541] #define bicubic_(x) ((1.0/6.0) * (POW3((x)+2) - 4 * POW3((x)+1) + 6 * POW3(x) - 4 * POW3(max((x)-1, 0))))
[ 100.035][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [542] #define ffexp(x) (POW(cos(max(EPSILON, clamp(x, 0.0, 1.0) * M_PI)), K0) * 0.5 + 0.5)
[ 100.035][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [543] #define gaussian(x) exp(-1 * POW2(x))
[ 100.035][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [544] #define is_zero(x) int(x == 0)
[ 100.035][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [545] #define lanczos(x) (sinc3(x) * sinc(x))
[ 100.035][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [546] #define quadratic(x) quadratic_(clamp((x), 0.0, 1.5))
[ 100.035][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [547] #define quadratic_(x) TERNARY(step(x, 0.5), 0.75 - POW2(x), 0.5 * POW2((x) - 1.5))
[ 100.035][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [548] #define sinc(x) sinc_(clamp((x), 0.0, 1.0))
[ 100.035][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [549] #define sinc3(x) sinc_(clamp((x), 0.0, 3.0))
[ 100.035][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [550] #define sinc_(x) TERNARY(step(x, 1e-3), 1.0, DIV(sin((x)*M_PI), ((x)*M_PI)))
[ 100.035][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [551] #define sphinx(x) sphinx_(clamp((x), 0.0, 1.4302966531242027))
[ 100.035][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [552] #define sphinx_(x) TERNARY(step(x, 1e-3), 1.0, DIV(3.0 * (sin((x)*M_PI) - (x)*M_PI * cos((x)*M_PI)), POW3((x)*M_PI)))
[ 100.035][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [553] #define triangle(x) triangle_(clamp((x), 0.0, 1.0))
[ 100.035][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [554] #define triangle_(x) (1 - (x))
[ 100.035][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [555] 
[ 100.035][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [556] #define MAP1(f,param) f(param)
[ 100.035][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [557] #define MAP2(f,param) vec2(f(param.x), f(param.y))
[ 100.035][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [558] #define MAP3(f,param) vec3(f(param.x), f(param.y), f(param.z))
[ 100.035][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [559] 
[ 100.035][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [560] #if defined(LUMA_raw)

[ 100.035][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [576] #else
[ 100.035][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [577] #define val vec3

[ 100.035][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [579] #define unval(v) vec4(v.x, v.y, v.z, poi_.a)
[ 100.035][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [580] #define val_packed val
[ 100.035][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [581] #define val_pack(v) (v)
[ 100.035][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [582] #define val_unpack(v) (v)
[ 100.035][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [583] #define MAP MAP3
[ 100.035][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [584] #endif
