[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [847] #else
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [848] #define GET_GUIDE_(off) GET_(off)
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [849] #define gather_offs(off, off_arr) (HOOKED_mul * vec4(textureGatherOffsets(HOOKED_raw, HOOKED_pos + vec2(off) * HOOKED_pt, off_arr)))
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [850] #define gather(off) HOOKED_gather(HOOKED_pos + (off)*HOOKED_pt, 0)
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [851] #endif
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [852] 
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [853] #if T
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [854] val GET(vec3 off)
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [855] {
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [856] 	switch (min(int(off.z), frame)) {
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [857] 	case 0: return val_swizz(GET_(off));
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [858] 
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [859] 	}
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [860] }
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [861] val GET_GUIDE(vec3 off)
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [862] {
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [863] 	return off.z == 0 ? val_guide_swizz(GET_GUIDE_(off)) : GET(off);
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [864] }
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [865] #else
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [866] #define GET(off) val_swizz(GET_(off))
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [867] #define GET_GUIDE(off) val_guide_swizz(GET_GUIDE_(off))
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [868] #endif
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [869] 
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [870] vec4 poi_ = GET_(vec3(0));
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [871] vec4 poi2_ = GET_GUIDE_(vec3(0));
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [872] val poi = val_swizz(poi_); // pixel-of-interest
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [873] val_guide poi2 = val_guide_swizz(poi2_); // guide pixel-of-interest
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [874] 
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [875] #if RI // rotation
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [876] vec2 rot(vec2 p, float d)
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [877] {
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [878] 	return vec2(
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [879] 		p.x * cos(radians(d)) - p.y * sin(radians(d)),
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [880] 		p.y * sin(radians(d)) + p.x * cos(radians(d))
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [881] 	);
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [882] }
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [883] #else
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [884] #define rot(p, d) (p)
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [885] #endif
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [886] 
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [887] #if RFI // reflection
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [888] vec2 ref(vec2 p, int d)
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [889] {
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [890] 	switch (d) {
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [891] 	case 0: return p;
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [892] 	case 1: return p * vec2(1, -1);
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [893] 	case 2: return p * vec2(-1, 1);
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [894] 	}
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [895] }
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [896] #else
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [897] #define ref(p, d) (p)
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [898] #endif
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [899] 
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [900] #if SST && R >= SST
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [901] float spatial_r(vec3 v)
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [902] {
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [903] 	v.xy += 0.5 - fract(HOOKED_pos*HOOKED_size);
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [904] 	v.z *= TD;
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [905] 	return SK(length(v)*SS);
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [906] }
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [907] #else
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [908] #define spatial_r(v) (1)
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [909] #endif
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [910] 
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [911] // 2D blur for sharpening
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [912] #if AS
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [913] float spatial_as(vec3 v)
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [914] {
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [915] 	v.xy += 0.5 - fract(HOOKED_pos*HOOKED_size);
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [916] 	return ASK(length(v)*ASS) * int(v.z == 0);
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [917] }
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [918] #endif
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [919] 
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [920] #if PST && P >= PST
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [921] #define spatial_p(v) PSK(length(v)*PSS)
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [922] #define normalize_p(x,expr) DIV((x), (expr))
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [923] #else
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [924] #define spatial_p(v) (1)
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [925] #define normalize_p(x,expr) ((x) * p_scale)
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [926] #endif
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [927] 
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [928] const float pdiff_scale = 1.0/max(EPSILON,POW2(S*0.013));
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [929] val_guide range(val_guide pdiff_sq)
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [930] {
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [931] 	pdiff_sq = sqrt(abs(pdiff_sq - max(EPSILON, RO)) * pdiff_scale);
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [932] 	return RK(pdiff_sq);
[ 100.052][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [933] }
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [934] 
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [935] #define GATHER (PD == 0 && NG == 0 && SAMPLE == 0) // never textureGather if any of these conditions are false
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [936] #define REGULAR_ROTATIONS (RI == 0 || RI == 1 || RI == 3 || RI == 7)
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [937] 
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [938] #if (defined(LUMA_gather) || D1W) && ((PS == 0 || ((PS == 3 || PS == 7) && RI != 7) || PS == 8) && P == 3) && REGULAR_ROTATIONS && GATHER
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [939] // 3x3 diamond/plus or square patch_comparison_gather
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [940] const ivec2 offsets_adj[4] = { ivec2(0,-1), ivec2(1,0), ivec2(0,1), ivec2(-1,0) };
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [941] const ivec2 offsets_adj_sf[4] = { ivec2(0,-1) * SF, ivec2(1,0) * SF, ivec2(0,1) * SF, ivec2(-1,0) * SF };
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [942] vec4 poi_patch_adj = gather_offs(0, offsets_adj);
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [943] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [944] const ivec2 offsets_diag[4] = { ivec2(-1,-1), ivec2(1,-1), ivec2(1,1), ivec2(-1,1) };
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [945] const ivec2 offsets_diag_sf[4] = { ivec2(-1,-1) * SF, ivec2(1,-1) * SF, ivec2(1,1) * SF, ivec2(-1,1) * SF };
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [946] vec4 poi_patch_diag = gather_offs(0, offsets_diag);
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [947] #endif
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [948] float patch_comparison_gather(vec3 r)
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [949] {
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [950] 	float min_rot = p_area - 1;
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [951] 	vec4 transformer_adj = gather_offs(r, offsets_adj_sf);
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [952] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [953] 	vec4 transformer_diag = gather_offs(r, offsets_diag_sf);
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [954] #endif
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [955] 	FOR_ROTATION {
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [956] 		FOR_REFLECTION {
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [957] #if RFI
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [958] 			/* xxy
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [959] 			 * w y
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [960] 			 * wzz
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [961] 			 */
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [962] 			switch(rfi) {
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [963] 			case 1:
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [964] 				transformer_adj = transformer_adj.zyxw;
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [965] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [966] 				transformer_diag = transformer_diag.zyxw;
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [967] #endif
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [968] 				break;
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [969] 			case 2:
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [970] 				transformer_adj = transformer_adj.xwzy;
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [971] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [972] 				transformer_diag = transformer_diag.xwzy;
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [973] #endif
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [974] 				break;
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [975] 			}
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [976] #endif
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [977] 
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [978] 			vec4 pdiff_sq = POW2(poi_patch_adj - transformer_adj) * spatial_p(vec2(1,0));
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [979] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [980] 			pdiff_sq += POW2(poi_patch_diag - transformer_diag) * spatial_p(vec2(1,1));
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [981] #endif
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [982] 			min_rot = min(dot(pdiff_sq, vec4(1)), min_rot);
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [983] 
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [984] // un-reflect
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [985] #if RFI
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [986] 			switch(rfi) {
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [987] 			case 1:
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [988] 				transformer_adj = transformer_adj.zyxw;
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [989] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [990] 				transformer_diag = transformer_diag.zyxw;
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [991] #endif
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [992] 				break;
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [993] 			case 2:
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [994] 				transformer_adj = transformer_adj.xwzy;
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [995] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [996] 				transformer_diag = transformer_diag.xwzy;
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [997] #endif
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [998] 				break;
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [999] 			}
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1000] #endif
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1001] 		} // FOR_REFLECTION
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1002] #if RI == 7
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1003] 		transformer_adj = transformer_adj.wxyz;
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1004] 		// swap adjacents for diagonals
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1005] 		transformer_adj += transformer_diag;
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1006] 		transformer_diag = transformer_adj - transformer_diag;
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1007] 		transformer_adj -= transformer_diag;
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1008] #elif RI == 3
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1009] 		transformer_adj = transformer_adj.wxyz;
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1010] #elif RI == 1
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1011] 		transformer_adj = transformer_adj.zwxy;
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1012] #endif
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1013] #if RI == 3 && (PS == 0 || PS == 8)
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1014] 		transformer_diag = transformer_diag.wxyz;
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1015] #elif RI == 1 && (PS == 0 || PS == 8)
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1016] 		transformer_diag = transformer_diag.zwxy;
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1017] #endif
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1018] 	} // FOR_ROTATION
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1019] 	
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1020] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1021] 	float total_weight = spatial_p(vec2(0,0)) + 4 * spatial_p(vec2(0,1)) + 4 * spatial_p(vec2(1,1));
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1022] #else
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1023] 	float total_weight = spatial_p(vec2(0,0)) + 4 * spatial_p(vec2(0,1));
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1024] #endif
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1025] 
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1026] 	float center_diff = poi2.x - GET_GUIDE(r).x;
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1027] 	return normalize_p(POW2(center_diff) + min_rot, max(EPSILON,total_weight));
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1028] }
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1029] #elif (defined(LUMA_gather) || D1W) && PS == 4 && P == 3 && RI == 0 && RFI == 0 && GATHER
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1030] const ivec2 offsets[4] = { ivec2(0,-1), ivec2(-1,0), ivec2(0,0), ivec2(1,0) };
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1031] const ivec2 offsets_sf[4] = { ivec2(0,-1) * SF, ivec2(-1,0) * SF, ivec2(0,0) * SF, ivec2(1,0) * SF };
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1032] vec4 poi_patch = gather_offs(0, offsets);
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1033] vec4 spatial_p_weights = vec4(spatial_p(vec2(0,-1)), spatial_p(vec2(-1,0)), spatial_p(vec2(0,0)), spatial_p(vec2(1,0)));
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1034] float patch_comparison_gather(vec3 r)
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1035] {
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1036] 	vec4 pdiff = poi_patch - gather_offs(r, offsets_sf);
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1037] 	return normalize_p(
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1038] 		dot(POW2(pdiff) * spatial_p_weights, vec4(1)),
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1039] 		dot(spatial_p_weights, vec4(1))
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1040] 	);
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1041] }
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1042] #elif (defined(LUMA_gather) || D1W) && PS == 6 && RI == 0 && RFI == 0 && GATHER
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1043] // tiled even square patch_comparison_gather
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1044] // XXX extend to support odd square?
[ 100.053][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1045] float patch_comparison_gather(vec3 r)
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1046] {
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1047] 	/* gather order:
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1048] 	 * w z
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1049] 	 * x y
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1050] 	 */
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1051] 	vec2 tile;
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1052] 	float pdiff_sq = 0;
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1053] 	float total_weight = 0;
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1054] 	for (tile.x = -hp; tile.x < hp; tile.x+=2) for (tile.y = -hp; tile.y < hp; tile.y+=2) {
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1055] 		vec4 diff = gather(tile + r.xy) - gather(tile);
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1056] 		vec4 weights = vec4(spatial_p(tile+vec2(0,1)), spatial_p(tile+vec2(1,1)), spatial_p(tile+vec2(1,0)), spatial_p(tile+vec2(0,0)));
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1057] 		pdiff_sq += dot(POW2(diff) * weights, vec4(1));
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1058] 		total_weight += dot(weights, vec4(1));
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1059] 	}
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1060] 
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1061] 	return normalize_p(pdiff_sq, max(EPSILON,total_weight));
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1062] }
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1063] #else
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1064] #define patch_comparison_gather patch_comparison
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1065] #define STORE_POI_PATCH 1
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1066] val_guide poi_patch[p_area];
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1067] #endif
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1068] 
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1069] val_guide patch_comparison(vec3 r)
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1070] {
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1071] 	vec3 p;
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1072] 	val_guide min_rot = val_guide(p_area);
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1073] 
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1074] 	FOR_ROTATION FOR_REFLECTION {
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1075] 		val_guide pdiff_sq = val_guide(0);
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1076] 		float total_weight = 0;
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1077] 
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1078] 		int p_index = 0;
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1079] 		FOR_PATCH(p) {
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1080] #ifdef STORE_POI_PATCH
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1081] 			val_guide poi_p = poi_patch[p_index++];
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1082] #else
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1083] 			val_guide poi_p = GET_GUIDE(p);
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1084] #endif
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1085] 			vec3 transformed_p = SF * vec3(ref(rot(p.xy, ri), rfi), p.z);
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1086] 			val_guide diff_sq = poi_p - GET_GUIDE(transformed_p + r);
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1087] 			diff_sq *= diff_sq;
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1088] 
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1089] 			float weight = spatial_p(p.xy);
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1090] 			pdiff_sq += diff_sq * weight;
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1091] 			total_weight += weight;
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1092] 		}
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1093] 
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1094] 		min_rot = min(min_rot, normalize_p(pdiff_sq, max(EPSILON,total_weight)));
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1095] 	}
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1096] 
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1097] 	return min_rot;
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1098] }
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1099] 
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1100] vec4 hook()
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1101] {
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1102] 	val_guide total_weight = val_guide(0);
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1103] 	val sum = val(0);
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1104] 	val result = val(0);
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1105] 
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1106] 	vec3 r = vec3(0);
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1107] 	vec3 me = vec3(0);
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1108] 
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1109] 	float sw = SW * spatial_r(vec3(0));
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1110] 
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1111] #if T && ME == 1 // temporal & motion estimation
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1112] 	vec3 me_tmp = vec3(0);
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1113] 	float maxweight = 0;
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1114] #elif T && ME == 2 // temporal & motion estimation
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1115] 	vec3 me_sum = vec3(0);
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1116] 	float me_weight = 0;
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1117] #endif
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1118] 
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1119] #if AS
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1120] 	float total_weight_as = 0;
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1121] 	val sum_as = val(0);
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1122] #endif
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1123] 
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1124] #if WD == 2 || V == 7 || C
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1125] #define STORE_WEIGHTS 1
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1126] #else
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1127] #define STORE_WEIGHTS 0
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1128] #endif
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1129] 
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1130] #if STORE_WEIGHTS
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1131] 	int r_index = 0;
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1132] 	val_guide_packed all_weights[r_area];
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1133] 	val_packed all_pixels[r_area];
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1134] #endif
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1135] 
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1136] #ifdef STORE_POI_PATCH
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1137] 	vec3 p;
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1138] 	int p_index = 0;
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1139] 	FOR_PATCH(p)
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1140] 		poi_patch[p_index++] = GET_GUIDE(p);
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1141] #endif
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1142] 	
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1143] #if WD == 1 // weight discard (moving cumulative average)
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1144] 	int r_iter = 1;
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1145] 	val_guide wd_total_weight = val_guide(0);
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1146] 	val wd_sum = val(0);
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1147] #endif
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1148] 
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1149] #if V == 7
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1150] 	vec2 v7cell = floor(HOOKED_size/R * HOOKED_pos) * R + hr;
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1151] 	vec2 v7cell_off = floor(HOOKED_pos * HOOKED_size) - floor(v7cell);
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1152] #endif
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1153] 
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1154] 	FOR_FRAME(r) {
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1155] 	// XXX ME is always a frame behind, should have the option to re-research after applying ME (could do it an arbitrary number of times per frame if desired)
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1156] #if T && ME == 1 // temporal & motion estimation max weight
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1157] 	if (r.z > 0) {
[ 100.054][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1158] 		me += me_tmp * MEF;
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1159] 		me_tmp = vec3(0);
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1160] 		maxweight = 0;
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1161] 	}
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1162] #elif T && ME == 2 // temporal & motion estimation weighted average
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1163] 	if (r.z > 0) {
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1164] 		me += round(DIV(me_sum, me_weight) * MEF);
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1165] 		me_sum = vec3(0);
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1166] 		me_weight = 0;
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1167] 	}
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1168] #endif
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1169] 	FOR_RESEARCH(r) {
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1170] #if V == 7
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1171] 		r.xy += v7cell_off;
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1172] #endif
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1173] 
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1174] 		// r coords with appropriate transformations applied
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1175] 		vec3 tr = vec3(r.xy + floor(r.xy * RSF), r.z);
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1176] 		tr.xy += me.xy;
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1177] 
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1178] 		val px = GET(tr);
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1179] 
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1180] #if SKIP_PATCH
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1181] 		val weight = val(1);
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1182] #else
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1183] 		val_guide pdiff_sq = (r.z == 0) ? patch_comparison_gather(tr) : patch_comparison(tr);
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1184] 		val_guide weight = range(pdiff_sq);
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1185] #endif
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1186] 
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1187] #if T && ME == 1 // temporal & motion estimation max weight
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1188] 		me_tmp = vec3(tr.xy,0) * step(maxweight, weight.x) + me_tmp * (1 - step(maxweight, weight.x));
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1189] 		maxweight = max(maxweight, weight.x);
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1190] #elif T && ME == 2 // temporal & motion estimation weighted average
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1191] 		me_sum += vec3(tr.xy,0) * weight.x;
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1192] 		me_weight += weight.x;
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1193] #endif
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1194] 
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1195] 		weight *= spatial_r(r);
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1196] 
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1197] #if AS
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1198] 		float spatial_as_weight = spatial_as(tr);
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1199] 		sum_as += px * spatial_as_weight;
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1200] 		total_weight_as += spatial_as_weight;
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1201] #endif
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1202] 
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1203] #if WD == 1 // weight discard (moving cumulative average)
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1204] 		float wd_scale = RECIPROCAL(r_iter);
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1205] 
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1206] 		val_guide below_threshold = WDS * abs(min(val_guide(0.0), weight - (total_weight * wd_scale * WDT * WD1TK(sqrt(wd_scale*WDP)))));
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1207] 		val_guide wdkf = MAP_GUIDE(WDK, below_threshold);
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1208] 
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1209] 		wd_sum += px * weight * wdkf;
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1210] 		wd_total_weight += weight * wdkf;
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1211] 		r_iter++;
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1212] #if STORE_WEIGHTS
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1213] 		all_weights[r_index] = val_guide_pack(weight * wdkf);
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1214] 		all_pixels[r_index] = val_pack(px);
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1215] 		r_index++;
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1216] #endif
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1217] #elif STORE_WEIGHTS
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1218] 		all_weights[r_index] = val_guide_pack(weight);
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1219] 		all_pixels[r_index] = val_pack(px);
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1220] 		r_index++;
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1221] #endif
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1222] 
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1223] #if V == 7
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1224] 		r.xy -= v7cell_off;
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1225] #endif
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1226] 
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1227] 		sum += px * weight;
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1228] 		total_weight += weight;
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1229] 	} // FOR_RESEARCH
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1230] 	} // FOR_FRAME
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1231] 
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1232] 	val_guide avg_weight = total_weight * r_scale;
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1233] 
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1234] #if defined(LUMA_raw) && V == 4
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1235] 	return unval_guide(avg_weight);

[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1237] 	return vec4(0.5); // XXX visualize for chroma
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1238] #endif
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1239] 
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1240] #if C
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1241] 	total_weight = val_guide(0);
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1242] 	sum = val(0);
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1243] 
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1244] 	for (int c = 0; c <= C; c++) {
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1245] 		val_guide_packed all_weights_update[r_area];
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1246] 
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1247] 		r_index = 0;
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1248] 		FOR_FRAME(r) FOR_RESEARCH(r) {
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1249] 			val_guide c_sum = val_guide(0);
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1250] 			vec3 r2 = vec3(0);
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1251] 			int r2_index = 0;
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1252] 			FOR_FRAME(r2) FOR_RESEARCH(r2)
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1253] 				if (distance(r, r2) - sqrt(CD) <= FLT_EPSILON)
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1254] 					c_sum += val_guide_unpack(all_weights[r2_index++]);

[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1258] 		}
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1259] 
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1260] 		r_index = 0;
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1261] 		FOR_FRAME(r) FOR_RESEARCH(r) {
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1262] 			val_guide old_weight = val_guide_unpack(all_weights[r_index]);

[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1264] 			val_guide weight = old_weight * RECIPROCAL(max(EPSILON,CS))
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1265] 			                 + old_weight * update * r1_scale * CS;
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1266] 			all_weights[r_index] = val_guide_pack(weight);
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1267] 			if (c == C) { // only need to update this stuff on the final C iteration
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1268] 				val px = val_unpack(all_pixels[r_index]);
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1269] 				sum += px * weight;
[ 100.055][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1270] 				total_weight += weight;
[ 100.056][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1271] 				all_pixels[r_index] = val_pack(px);
[ 100.056][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1272] 			}
[ 100.056][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1273] 			r_index++;
[ 100.056][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1274] 		}

[ 100.056][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1276] #endif

[ 100.056][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1281] 
[ 100.056][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1282] 	r_index = 0;
[ 100.056][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1283] 	FOR_FRAME(r) FOR_RESEARCH(r) {

[ 100.056][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1300] #if WD == 1 // weight discard (moving cumulative average)

[ 100.056][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1323] #if AS == 1 // sharpen+denoise

[ 100.056][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1334] 
[ 100.056][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1335] #if AS // sharpening
[ 100.056][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1336] 	val usm = AS_input - MED_DIV(sum_as, max(EPSILON,total_weight_as));
[ 100.056][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1337] 	usm = POW(usm, ASP);
[ 100.056][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1338] 	const float as_scale_15 = 1.0/1.5;
[ 100.056][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1339] 	usm *= ASAK(abs((AS_base + usm - 0.5) * as_scale_15) * ASA);
[ 100.056][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1340] 	usm *= ASF;
[ 100.056][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1341] 	result = AS_base + usm;
[ 100.056][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1342] #endif
[ 100.056][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1343] 
[ 100.056][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1344] #if EP // extremes preserve

[ 100.056][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1346] 	float ep_weight = POW(max(EPSILON, min(1-luminance, luminance)*2), (luminance < 0.5 ? DP : BP));
[ 100.056][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1347] 	result = mix(poi, result, ep_weight);

[ 100.056][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1350] #endif

[ 100.056][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1352] #if V == 1

[ 100.056][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1354] #elif V == 2
[ 100.056][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1355] 	result = (poi - result) * 0.5 + 0.5;
[ 100.056][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1356] #elif V == 3

[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 30] #define HOOKED_pos CHROMA_pos 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 31] #define HOOKED_size CHROMA_size 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 32] #define HOOKED_rot CHROMA_rot 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 33] #define HOOKED_off CHROMA_off 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 34] #define HOOKED_pt CHROMA_pt 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 35] #define HOOKED_map CHROMA_map 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 36] #define HOOKED_mul CHROMA_mul 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 37] #define HOOKED_tex CHROMA_tex 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 38] #define HOOKED_texOff CHROMA_texOff 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 39] #define HOOKED_gather CHROMA_gather 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 40] #define frame _7 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 41] #define random _8 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 42] #define input_size _9 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 43] #define target_size _a 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 44] #define tex_offset _b 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 45] const float _8002 = float(0.8703105449676514); 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 46] const float _8003 = float(0.0595848374068737); 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 47] vec4 _8001(vec4 color) {
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 48] // pl_shader_linearize           
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 49] color.rgb = max(color.rgb, 0.0); 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 50] color.rgb = _8002 * pow(color.rgb + vec3(_8003), vec3(2.4)); 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 51] return color;
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 52] }
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 53] 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 54] #define linearize _8001 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 55] const float _4002 = float(1.149015188217163); 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 56] const float _4003 = float(0.0595848374068737); 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 57] vec4 _4001(vec4 color) {
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 58] // pl_shader_delinearize 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 59] color.rgb = max(color.rgb, 0.0); 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 60] color.rgb = pow(_4002 * color.rgb, vec3(1.0/2.4)) - vec3(_4003); 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 61] return color;
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 62] }
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 63] 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 64] #define delinearize _4001 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 65] 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 66] 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 67] 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 68] // User variables
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 69] 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 70] // It is generally preferable to denoise luma and chroma differently, so the 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 71] // user variables for luma and chroma are split.
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 72] 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 73] // Denoising factor (sigma, higher means more blur)
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 74] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 75] #define S 2.171842300643018
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 76] #else
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 77] #define S 3.472706940155897
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 78] #endif
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 79] 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 80] /* Noise resistant adaptive sharpening
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 81]  *
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 82]  * AS:
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 83]  * 	 - 0: disable
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 84]  * 	 - 1: sharpen+denoise
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 85]  * 	 - 2: sharpen only
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 86]  * ASF: Higher numbers make a sharper image
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 87]  * ASA: Anti-ringing, higher numbers increase strength
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 88]  * ASP: Power, lower numbers increase sharpening on lower frequency detail
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 89]  * ASS: Equivalent to SS but for ASK instead of SK
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 90]  * ASI:
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 91]  *  - 0: don't sharpen noise
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 92]  *  - 1: sharpen noise
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 93]  */
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 94] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 95] #define AS 0
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 96] #define ASF 0.0
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 97] #define ASA 0.0
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 98] #define ASP 0.0
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 99] #define ASS 0.0
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [100] #define ASI 0
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [101] #else
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [102] #define AS 0
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [103] #define ASF 0.0
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [104] #define ASA 0.0
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [105] #define ASP 0.0
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [106] #define ASS 0.0
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [107] #define ASI 0
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [108] #endif
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [109] 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [110] /* Starting weight
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [111]  *
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [112]  * AKA the center weight, the weight of the pixel-of-interest.
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [113]  */
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [114] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [115] #define SW 0.874631892412684
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [116] #else
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [117] #define SW 0.3493678781214755
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [118] #endif
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [119] 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [120] /* Spatial kernel
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [121]  *
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [122]  * Increasing the spatial sigma (SS) reduces the weight of further 
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [123]  * pixels.
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [124]  *
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [125]  * The intra-patch variants might help with larger patch sizes.
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [126]  *
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [127]  * SST: enables spatial kernel if R>=PST, 0 fully disables
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [128]  * SS: spatial sigma
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [129]  * PSS: intra-patch spatial sigma
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [130]  * PST: enables intra-patch spatial kernel if P>=PST, 0 fully disables
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [131]  */
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [132] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [133] #define SST 1
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [134] #define SS 0.1786363425615082
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [135] #define PST 0
[ 100.059][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [136] #define PSS 0.0
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [137] #else
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [138] #define SST 1
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [139] #define SS 0.3241999209926485
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [140] #define PST 0
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [141] #define PSS 0.0
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [142] #endif
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [143] 
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [144] /* Extremes preserve
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [145]  *
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [146]  * This setting is dependent on code generation from shader_cfg, so this 
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [147]  * setting can only be enabled via shader_cfg.
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [148]  *
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [149]  * Reduce denoising in very bright/dark areas.
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [150]  *
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [151]  * The downscaling factor of the EP shader stage affects the size of the area 
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [152]  * checked for luminance.
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [153]  *
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [154]  * This is incompatible with RGB. If you have RGB hooks enabled then you will 
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [155]  * have to delete the EP shader stage or specify EP=0 through shader_cfg.
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [156]  *
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [157]  * EP: 1 to enable, 0 to disable
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [158]  * DP: EP strength on dark areas, 0 to fully denoise
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [159]  * BP: EP strength on bright areas, 0 to fully denoise
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [160]  */
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [161] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [162] #define EP 0
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [163] #define BP 0.0
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [164] #define DP 0.0
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [165] #else
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [166] #define EP 0
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [167] #define BP 0.0
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [168] #define DP 0.0
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [169] #endif
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [170] 
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [171] /* ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS */
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [172] /* ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS */
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [173] /* ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS */
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [174] /* ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS */
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [175] /* ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS */
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [176] 
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [177] /* textureGather applicable configurations:
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [178]  *
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [179]  * - PS={0,3,7,8}:P=3:RI={0,1,3,7}:RFI={0,1,2}
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [180]  * - PS={0,8}:P=3:RI={0,1,3,7}:RFI={0,1,2}
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [181]  * - PS=4:P=3:PST=0:RI=0:RFI=0
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [182]  * - PS=6:RI=0:RFI=0
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [183]  *   - Currently the only scalable variant
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [184]  *
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [185]  * Options which always disable textureGather:
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [186]  * 	 - NG
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [187]  * 	 - SAMPLE
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [188]  * 	 - PD
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [189]  *
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [190]  * Running without textureGather may be much slower.
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [191]  */
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [192] 
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [193] /* Patch & research sizes
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [194]  *
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [195]  * P should be an odd number. Higher values are slower and not always better.
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [196]  *
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [197]  * R should be an odd number greater than or equal to 3. Higher values are 
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [198]  * generally better, but slower.
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [199]  */
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [200] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [201] #define P 3
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [202] #define R 5
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [203] #else
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [204] #define P 3
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [205] #define R 5
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [206] #endif
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [207] 
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [208] /* Patch and research shapes
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [209]  *
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [210]  * Different shapes have different speed and quality characteristics. Every 
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [211]  * shape (besides square) is smaller than square.
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [212]  *
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [213]  * PS applies applies to patches, RS applies to research zones.
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [214]  *
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [215]  * 0: square (symmetrical)
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [216]  * 1: horizontal line (asymmetric)
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [217]  * 2: vertical line (asymmetric)
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [218]  * 3: diamond (symmetrical)
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [219]  * 4: triangle (asymmetric, pointing upward)
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [220]  * 5: truncated triangle (asymmetric on two axis, last row halved)
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [221]  * 6: even sized square (asymmetric on two axis)
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [222]  * 7: plus (symmetrical)
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [223]  * 8: plus X (symmetrical)
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [224]  */
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [225] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [226] #define RS 3
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [227] #define PS 0
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [228] #else
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [229] #define RS 3
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [230] #define PS 3
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [231] #endif
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [232] 
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [233] /* Weight discard
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [234]  *
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [235]  * Reduces weights that fall below a fraction of the average weight. This culls 
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [236]  * the most dissimilar samples from the blur, which can yield a better result, 
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [237]  * especially around edges.
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [238]  * 
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [239]  * WD:
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [240]  * 	 - 2: Mean. Better quality, but slower and requires GLSL 4.0 or later
[ 100.060][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [241]  * 	 - 1: Moving cumulative average. Fast but inaccurate, blurs directionally.
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [242]  * 	 - 0: Disable
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [243]  *
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [244]  * WDT: Threshold coefficient, higher numbers discard more
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [245]  * WDP (only for WD=1): Increasing reduces the threshold for small sample sizes
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [246]  * WDS (not for WDK=is_zero): Higher numbers are more eager to reduce weights
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [247]  */
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [248] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [249] #define WD 1
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [250] #define WDT 0.2935708849017379
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [251] #define WDP 1.2788519721382683
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [252] #define WDS 1.0
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [253] #else
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [254] #define WD 0
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [255] #define WDT 0.0
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [256] #define WDP 0.0
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [257] #define WDS 1.0
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [258] #endif
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [259] 
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [260] /* Connectivity
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [261]  *
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [262]  * Increases weights that are near high weights, decreases weights that are 
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [263]  * near low weights.
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [264]  *
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [265]  * C: Number of passes to do, more increases the effect, 0 does nothing
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [266]  * CD: Distance between each pixel and its furthest neighbor
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [267]  * CS: Strength of effect, higher is more
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [268]  */
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [269] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [270] #define C 0
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [271] #define CD 1.0
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [272] #define CS 1.0
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [273] #else
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [274] #define C 0
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [275] #define CD 1.0
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [276] #define CS 1.0
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [277] #endif
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [278] 
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [279] /* Rotational/reflectional invariance
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [280]  *
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [281]  * Number of rotations/reflections to try for each patch comparison. Can be 
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [282]  * slow, but may improve feature preservation. More rotations/reflections gives 
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [283]  * diminishing returns. The most similar rotation/reflection is used.
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [284]  *
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [285]  * The angle in degrees of each rotation is 360/(RI+1), so RI=1 will do a 
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [286]  * single 180 degree rotation, RI=3 will do three 90 degree rotations, etc.
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [287]  *
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [288]  * Consider setting SAMPLE=1 if setting RI to a setting that would require 
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [289]  * sampling between pixels.
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [290]  *
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [291]  * RI: Rotational invariance
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [292]  * RFI (0 to 2): Reflectional invariance
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [293]  */
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [294] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [295] #define RI 0
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [296] #define RFI 2
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [297] #else
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [298] #define RI 0
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [299] #define RFI 0
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [300] #endif
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [301] 
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [302] /* Temporal denoising
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [303]  *
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [304]  * This setting is dependent on code generation from shader_cfg, so this 
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [305]  * setting can only be enabled via shader_cfg.
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [306]  *
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [307]  * Caveats:
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [308]  * 	 - Slower:
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [309]  * 	 	 - Gather optimizations only apply to the current frame
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [310]  * 	 - Requires vo=gpu-next
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [311]  * 	 - Luma-only (this is a bug)
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [312]  * 	 - Buggy
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [313]  *
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [314]  * May cause motion blur and may struggle more with noise that persists across 
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [315]  * multiple frames (e.g., from compression or duplicate frames).
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [316]  *
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [317]  * Motion estimation (ME) should improve quality without impacting speed.
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [318]  *
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [319]  * Increasing temporal distortion (TD) can reduce motion blur.
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [320]  *
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [321]  * T: number of frames used
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [322]  * ME: motion estimation, 0 for none, 1 for max weight, 2 for weighted avg
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [323]  * MEF: estimate factor, compensates for ME being one frame behind
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [324]  * TRF: compare against the denoised frames
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [325]  * TD: temporal distortion, higher numbers give less weight to previous frames
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [326]  */
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [327] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [328] #define T 0
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [329] #define ME 1
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [330] #define MEF 2
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [331] #define TRF 0
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [332] #define TD 1.0
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [333] #else
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [334] #define T 0
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [335] #define ME 0
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [336] #define MEF 2
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [337] #define TRF 0
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [338] #define TD 1.0
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [339] #endif
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [340] 
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [341] /* Kernels
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [342]  *
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [343]  * SK: spatial kernel
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [344]  * RK: range kernel (takes patch differences)
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [345]  * ASK: adaptive sharpening kernel
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [346]  * PSK: intra-patch spatial kernel
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [347]  * WDK: weight discard kernel
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [348]  * WD1TK (WD=1 only): weight discard tolerance kernel
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [349]  *
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [350]  * List of available kernels:
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [351]  *
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [352]  * bicubic
[ 100.061][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [353]  * cos
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [354]  * ffexp
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [355]  * gaussian
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [356]  * lanczos
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [357]  * quadratic
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [358]  * quadratic_ (unclamped)
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [359]  * sinc
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [360]  * sinc3
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [361]  * sinc_ (unclamped)
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [362]  * sphinx
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [363]  * sphinx_ (unclamped)
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [364]  * triangle
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [365]  * triangle_ (unclamped)
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [366]  */
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [367] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [368] #define SK gaussian
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [369] #define RK gaussian
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [370] #define ASK sinc
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [371] #define ASAK gaussian
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [372] #define PSK gaussian
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [373] #define WDK is_zero
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [374] #define WD1TK gaussian
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [375] #else
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [376] #define SK gaussian
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [377] #define RK gaussian
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [378] #define ASK sphinx_
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [379] #define ASAK gaussian
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [380] #define PSK gaussian
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [381] #define WDK is_zero
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [382] #define WD1TK gaussian
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [383] #endif
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [384] 
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [385] /* Kernel parameters
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [386]  *
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [387]  * The following kernels take parameters:
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [388]  *
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [389]  * ffexp: K0
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [390]  */
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [391] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [392] #define K0 1.0
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [393] #define K1 1.0
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [394] #else
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [395] #define K0 1.0
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [396] #define K1 1.0
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [397] #endif
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [398] 
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [399] /* Negative kernel parameter offsets
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [400]  *
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [401]  * Usually kernels go high -> low. These parameters allow for a kernel to go 
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [402]  * low -> high -> low.
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [403]  *
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [404]  * Values of 0.0 mean no effect, higher values increase the effect.
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [405]  *
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [406]  * RO: range kernel (takes patch differences)
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [407]  */
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [408] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [409] #define RO 6.373764517041128e-05
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [410] #else
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [411] #define RO 0.0
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [412] #endif
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [413] 
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [414] /* Sampling method
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [415]  *
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [416]  * In most cases this shouldn't make any difference, only set to bilinear if 
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [417]  * it's necessary to sample between pixels (e.g., RI=2).
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [418]  *
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [419]  * 0: nearest neighbor
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [420]  * 1: bilinear
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [421]  */
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [422] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [423] #define SAMPLE 0
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [424] #else
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [425] #define SAMPLE 0
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [426] #endif
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [427] 
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [428] /* Research scaling factor
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [429]  *
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [430]  * Higher numbers sample more sparsely as the distance from the POI grows.
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [431]  */
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [432] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [433] #define RSF 0.0
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [434] #else
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [435] #define RSF 0.0
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [436] #endif
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [437] 
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [438] // Scaling factor (should match WIDTH/HEIGHT)
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [439] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [440] #define SF 1
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [441] #else
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [442] #define SF 1
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [443] #endif
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [444] 
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [445] // Use the guide image as the input image
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [446] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [447] #define GI 0
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [448] #else
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [449] #define GI 0
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [450] #endif
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [451] 
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [452] /* Visualization
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [453]  *
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [454]  * 0: off
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [455]  * 1: absolute difference between input/output to the power of 0.25
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [456]  * 2: difference between input/output centered on 0.5
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [457]  * 3: post-WD average weight map
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [458]  * 4: pre-WD average weight map
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [459]  * 5: unsharp mask
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [460]  * 6: EP
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [461]  * 7: celled weight map (incompatible with temporal)
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [462]  */
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [463] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [464] #define V 0
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [465] #else
[ 100.062][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [466] #define V 0
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [467] #endif
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [468] 
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [469] // Fast approximate division
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [470] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [471] #define FAST_DIV 0
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [472] #else
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [473] #define FAST_DIV 0
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [474] #endif
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [475] 
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [476] // Force disable textureGather
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [477] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [478] #define NG 0
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [479] #else
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [480] #define NG 0
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [481] #endif
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [482] 
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [483] // Patch donut (probably useless)
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [484] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [485] #define PD 0
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [486] #else
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [487] #define PD 0
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [488] #endif
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [489] 
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [490] // Duplicate 1st weight (for luma-guided-chroma)
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [491] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [492] #define D1W 0
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [493] #else
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [494] #define D1W 0
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [495] #endif
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [496] 
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [497] // Skip patch comparison
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [498] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [499] #define SKIP_PATCH 0
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [500] #else
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [501] #define SKIP_PATCH 0
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [502] #endif
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [503] 
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [504] // Shader code
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [505] 
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [506] #define EPSILON 1.2e-38
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [507] #define FLT_EPSILON 1.19209290E-07
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [508] #define M_PI 3.14159265358979323846
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [509] #define POW2(x) ((x)*(x))
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [510] #define POW3(x) ((x)*(x)*(x))
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [511] 
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [512] // pow() implementation that gives -pow() when x<0
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [513] // avoids actually calling pow() since apparently it's buggy on nvidia
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [514] #define POW(x,y) (exp(log(abs(x)) * y) * sign(x))
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [515] 
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [516] // boolean logic w/ vectors
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [517] // from hdeband
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [518] #define NOT(x) (1 - (x))
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [519] #define AND *
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [520] #define TERNARY(cond, x, y) ((x)*(cond) + (y)*NOT(cond))
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [521] 
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [522] // from FSR
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [523] #if FAST_DIV
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [524] #define RECIPROCAL(x) uintBitsToFloat(uint(0x7ef07ebb) - floatBitsToUint(x))
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [525] #define DIV(x,y) ((x) * RECIPROCAL(y))
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [526] #define MED_RCP_B(x) uintBitsToFloat(uint(0x7ef19fff) - floatBitsToUint(x))
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [527] #define MED_RECIPROCAL(x) (MED_RCP_B(x) * (-MED_RCP_B(x) * x + 2))
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [528] #define MED_DIV(x,y) ((x) * MED_RECIPROCAL(y))
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [529] #else
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [530] #define RECIPROCAL(x) (1.0/(x))
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [531] #define MED_RECIPROCAL(x) (1.0/(x))
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [532] #define DIV(x,y) ((x)/(y))
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [533] #define MED_DIV(x,y) ((x)/(y))
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [534] #endif
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [535] 
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [536] // XXX make kernel params capable of being set per-kernel, e.g., RK0, SK0...
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [537] 
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [538] // kernels
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [539] // XXX sinc & sphinx: 1e-3 was selected tentatively;  not sure what the correct value should be (1e-8 is too low)
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [540] #define bicubic(x) bicubic_(clamp((x), 0.0, 2.0))
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [541] #define bicubic_(x) ((1.0/6.0) * (POW3((x)+2) - 4 * POW3((x)+1) + 6 * POW3(x) - 4 * POW3(max((x)-1, 0))))
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [542] #define ffexp(x) (POW(cos(max(EPSILON, clamp(x, 0.0, 1.0) * M_PI)), K0) * 0.5 + 0.5)
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [543] #define gaussian(x) exp(-1 * POW2(x))
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [544] #define is_zero(x) int(x == 0)
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [545] #define lanczos(x) (sinc3(x) * sinc(x))
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [546] #define quadratic(x) quadratic_(clamp((x), 0.0, 1.5))
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [547] #define quadratic_(x) TERNARY(step(x, 0.5), 0.75 - POW2(x), 0.5 * POW2((x) - 1.5))
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [548] #define sinc(x) sinc_(clamp((x), 0.0, 1.0))
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [549] #define sinc3(x) sinc_(clamp((x), 0.0, 3.0))
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [550] #define sinc_(x) TERNARY(step(x, 1e-3), 1.0, DIV(sin((x)*M_PI), ((x)*M_PI)))
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [551] #define sphinx(x) sphinx_(clamp((x), 0.0, 1.4302966531242027))
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [552] #define sphinx_(x) TERNARY(step(x, 1e-3), 1.0, DIV(3.0 * (sin((x)*M_PI) - (x)*M_PI * cos((x)*M_PI)), POW3((x)*M_PI)))
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [553] #define triangle(x) triangle_(clamp((x), 0.0, 1.0))
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [554] #define triangle_(x) (1 - (x))
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [555] 
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [556] #define MAP1(f,param) f(param)
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [557] #define MAP2(f,param) vec2(f(param.x), f(param.y))
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [558] #define MAP3(f,param) vec3(f(param.x), f(param.y), f(param.z))
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [559] 
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [560] #if defined(LUMA_raw)
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [561] #define val float
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [562] #define val_swizz(v) (v.x)
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [563] #define unval(v) vec4(v, 0, 0, poi_.a)
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [564] #define val_packed val
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [565] #define val_pack(v) (v)
[ 100.063][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [566] #define val_unpack(v) (v)

[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [621] 
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [622] // patch/research shapes
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [623] // each shape is depicted in a comment, where Z=5 (Z corresponds to P or R)
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [624] // dots (.) represent samples (pixels) and X represents the pixel-of-interest
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [625] 
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [626] // Z    .....
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [627] // Z    .....
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [628] // Z    ..X..
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [629] // Z    .....
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [630] // Z    .....
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [631] #define S_SQUARE(z,hz,incr) for (z.x = -hz;  z.x <= hz;  z.x++) for (z.y = -hz;  z.y <= hz;  incr)
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [632] 
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [633] // (in this instance Z=4)
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [634] // Z    ....
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [635] // Z    ....
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [636] // Z    ..X.
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [637] // Z    ....
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [638] #define S_SQUARE_EVEN(z,hz,incr) for (z.x = -hz;  z.x < hz;  z.x++) for (z.y = -hz;  z.y < hz;  incr)
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [639] 
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [640] // Z-4    .
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [641] // Z-2   ...
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [642] // Z    ..X..
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [643] #define S_TRIANGLE(z,hz,incr) for (z.y = -hz;  z.y <= 0;  z.y++) for (z.x = -abs(abs(z.y) - hz);  z.x <= abs(abs(z.y) - hz);  incr)
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [644] 
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [645] // Z-4    .
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [646] // Z-2   ...
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [647] // hz+1 ..X
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [648] #define S_TRUNC_TRIANGLE(z,hz,incr) for (z.y = -hz;  z.y <= 0;  z.y++) for (z.x = -abs(abs(z.y) - hz);  z.x <= abs(abs(z.y) - hz)*int(z.y!=0);  incr)
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [649] #define S_TRIANGLE_A(hz,Z) int(hz*hz+Z)
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [650] 
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [651] // Z-4    .
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [652] // Z-2   ...
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [653] // Z    ..X..
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [654] // Z-2   ...
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [655] // Z-4    .
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [656] #define S_DIAMOND(z,hz,incr) for (z.x = -hz;  z.x <= hz;  z.x++) for (z.y = -abs(abs(z.x) - hz);  z.y <= abs(abs(z.x) - hz);  incr)
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [657] #define S_DIAMOND_A(hz,Z) int(hz*hz*2+Z)
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [658] 
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [659] //
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [660] // Z    ..X..
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [661] //
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [662] #define S_HORIZONTAL(z,hz,incr) for (z.y = 0;  z.y <= 0;  z.y++) for (z.x = -hz;  z.x <= hz;  incr)
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [663] 
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [664] // 90 degree rotation of S_HORIZONTAL
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [665] #define S_VERTICAL(z,hz,incr) for (z.x = 0;  z.x <= 0;  z.x++) for (z.y = -hz;  z.y <= hz;  incr)
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [666] 
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [667] // 1      .
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [668] // 1      . 
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [669] // Z    ..X..
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [670] // 1      . 
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [671] // 1      .
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [672] #define S_PLUS(z,hz,incr) for (z.x = -hz;  z.x <= hz;  z.x++) for (z.y = -hz * int(z.x == 0);  z.y <= hz * int(z.x == 0);  incr)
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [673] #define S_PLUS_A(hz,Z) (Z*2 - 1)
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [674] 
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [675] // 3    . . .
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [676] // 3     ...
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [677] // Z    ..X..
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [678] // 3     ...
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [679] // 3    . . .
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [680] #define S_PLUS_X(z,hz,incr) for (z.x = -hz;  z.x <= hz;  z.x++) for (z.y = -abs(z.x) + -hz * int(z.x == 0);  z.y <= abs(z.x) + hz * int(z.x == 0);  incr)
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [681] #define S_PLUS_X_A(hz,Z) (Z*4 - 3)
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [682] 
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [683] // 1x1 square
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [684] #define S_1X1(z) for (z = vec3(0);  z.x <= 0;  z.x++)
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [685] 
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [686] #define T1 (T+1)
[ 100.064][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [687] #define FOR_FRAME(r) for (r.z = 0;  r.z < T1;  r.z++)
[ 100.065][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [688] 
[ 100.065][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [689] // donut increment, increments without landing on (0,0,0)
[ 100.065][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [690] // much faster than a continue statement
[ 100.065][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [691] #define DINCR(z,c,a) ((z.c += a),(z.c += int(z == vec3(0))))
[ 100.065][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [692] 
[ 100.065][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [693] #define R_AREA(a) (a * T1 - 1)

[ 100.065][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [695] // research shapes
