[ 100.065][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [789] 
[ 100.065][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [790] #if SAMPLE == 0
[ 100.065][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [791] #define sample(tex, pos, size, pt, off) tex((pos) + (pt) * (vec2(off) + 0.5 - fract((pos) * (size))))
[ 100.065][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [792] #else
[ 100.065][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [793] #define sample(tex, pos, size, pt, off) tex((pos) + (pt) * vec2(off))
[ 100.065][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [794] #endif
[ 100.065][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [795] 
[ 100.065][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [796] /* Guide images are bound through the G (luma) GC (chroma, or non-luma) 
[ 100.065][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [797]  * textures. When bound, these are where the weights are computed. Otherwise 
[ 100.065][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [798]  * the weights are computed on the hooked texture.
[ 100.065][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [799]  */
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [800] 
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [801] #if GI && defined(LUMA_raw)
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [802] #define GET_(off) sample(G_tex, G_pos, G_size, G_pt, off)
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [803] #elif GI
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [804] #define GET_(off) sample(GC_tex, GC_pos, GC_size, GC_pt, off)
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [805] #else
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [806] #define GET_(off) sample(HOOKED_tex, HOOKED_pos, HOOKED_size, HOOKED_pt, off)
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [807] #endif
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [808] 
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [809] #if defined(G_raw) && (defined(LUMA_raw) || D1W)
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [810] #define GET_GUIDE_(off) sample(G_tex, G_pos, G_size, G_pt, off)
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [811] #define gather_offs(off, off_arr) (G_mul * vec4(textureGatherOffsets(G_raw, G_pos + vec2(off) * G_pt, off_arr)))
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [812] #define gather(off) G_gather(G_pos + (off) * G_pt, 0)
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [813] #elif defined(GC_raw)
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [814] #define GET_GUIDE_(off) sample(GC_tex, GC_pos, GC_size, GC_pt, off)
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [815] #else
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [816] #define GET_GUIDE_(off) GET_(off)
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [817] #define gather_offs(off, off_arr) (HOOKED_mul * vec4(textureGatherOffsets(HOOKED_raw, HOOKED_pos + vec2(off) * HOOKED_pt, off_arr)))
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [818] #define gather(off) HOOKED_gather(HOOKED_pos + (off)*HOOKED_pt, 0)
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [819] #endif
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [820] 
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [821] #if T
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [822] val GET(vec3 off)
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [823] {
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [824] 	 switch (min(int(off.z), frame)) {
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [825] 	 case 0: return val_swizz(GET_(off)); 
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [826] 
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [827] 	 }
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [828] }
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [829] val GET_GUIDE(vec3 off)
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [830] {
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [831] 	 return off.z == 0 ? val_guide_swizz(GET_GUIDE_(off)) : GET(off); 
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [832] }
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [833] #else
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [834] #define GET(off) val_swizz(GET_(off))
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [835] #define GET_GUIDE(off) val_guide_swizz(GET_GUIDE_(off))
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [836] #endif
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [837] 
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [838] vec4 poi_ = GET_(vec3(0)); 
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [839] vec4 poi2_ = GET_GUIDE_(vec3(0)); 
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [840] val poi = val_swizz(poi_);  // pixel-of-interest
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [841] val_guide poi2 = val_guide_swizz(poi2_);  // guide pixel-of-interest
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [842] 
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [843] #if RI // rotation
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [844] vec2 rot(vec2 p, float d)
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [845] {
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [846] 	 return vec2(
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [847] 	 	 p.x * cos(radians(d)) - p.y * sin(radians(d)),
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [848] 	 	 p.y * sin(radians(d)) + p.x * cos(radians(d))
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [849] 	 ); 
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [850] }
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [851] #else
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [852] #define rot(p, d) (p)
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [853] #endif
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [854] 
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [855] #if RFI // reflection
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [856] vec2 ref(vec2 p, int d)
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [857] {
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [858] 	 switch (d) {
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [859] 	 case 0: return p; 
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [860] 	 case 1: return p * vec2(1, -1); 
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [861] 	 case 2: return p * vec2(-1, 1); 
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [862] 	 }
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [863] }
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [864] #else
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [865] #define ref(p, d) (p)
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [866] #endif
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [867] 
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [868] #if SST && R >= SST
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [869] float spatial_r(vec3 v)
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [870] {
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [871] 	 v.xy += 0.5 - fract(HOOKED_pos*HOOKED_size); 
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [872] 	 v.z *= TD; 
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [873] 	 return SK(length(v)*SS); 
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [874] }
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [875] #else
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [876] #define spatial_r(v) (1)
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [877] #endif
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [878] 
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [879] // 2D blur for sharpening
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [880] #if AS
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [881] float spatial_as(vec3 v)
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [882] {
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [883] 	 v.xy += 0.5 - fract(HOOKED_pos*HOOKED_size); 
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [884] 	 return ASK(length(v)*ASS) * int(v.z == 0); 
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [885] }
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [886] #endif
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [887] 
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [888] #if PST && P >= PST
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [889] #define spatial_p(v) PSK(length(v)*PSS)
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [890] #define normalize_p(x,expr) DIV((x), (expr))
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [891] #else
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [892] #define spatial_p(v) (1)
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [893] #define normalize_p(x,expr) ((x) * p_scale)
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [894] #endif
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [895] 
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [896] const float pdiff_scale = 1.0/max(EPSILON,POW2(S*0.013)); 
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [897] val_guide range(val_guide pdiff_sq)
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [898] {
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [899] 	 pdiff_sq = sqrt(abs(pdiff_sq - max(EPSILON, RO)) * pdiff_scale); 
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [900] 	 return RK(pdiff_sq); 
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [901] }
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [902] 
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [903] #define GATHER (PD == 0 && NG == 0 && SAMPLE == 0) // never textureGather if any of these conditions are false
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [904] #define REGULAR_ROTATIONS (RI == 0 || RI == 1 || RI == 3 || RI == 7)
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [905] 
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [906] #if (defined(LUMA_gather) || D1W) && ((PS == 0 || ((PS == 3 || PS == 7) && RI != 7) || PS == 8) && P == 3) && REGULAR_ROTATIONS && GATHER
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [907] // 3x3 diamond/plus or square patch_comparison_gather
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [908] const ivec2 offsets_adj[4] = { ivec2(0,-1), ivec2(1,0), ivec2(0,1), ivec2(-1,0) }; 
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [909] const ivec2 offsets_adj_sf[4] = { ivec2(0,-1) * SF, ivec2(1,0) * SF, ivec2(0,1) * SF, ivec2(-1,0) * SF }; 
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [910] vec4 poi_patch_adj = gather_offs(0, offsets_adj); 
[ 100.066][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [911] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [912] const ivec2 offsets_diag[4] = { ivec2(-1,-1), ivec2(1,-1), ivec2(1,1), ivec2(-1,1) }; 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [913] const ivec2 offsets_diag_sf[4] = { ivec2(-1,-1) * SF, ivec2(1,-1) * SF, ivec2(1,1) * SF, ivec2(-1,1) * SF }; 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [914] vec4 poi_patch_diag = gather_offs(0, offsets_diag); 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [915] #endif
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [916] float patch_comparison_gather(vec3 r)
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [917] {
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [918] 	 float min_rot = p_area - 1; 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [919] 	 vec4 transformer_adj = gather_offs(r, offsets_adj_sf); 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [920] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [921] 	 vec4 transformer_diag = gather_offs(r, offsets_diag_sf); 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [922] #endif
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [923] 	 FOR_ROTATION {
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [924] 	 	 FOR_REFLECTION {
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [925] #if RFI
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [926] 	 	 	 /* xxy
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [927] 	 	 	  * w y
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [928] 	 	 	  * wzz
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [929] 	 	 	  */
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [930] 	 	 	 switch(rfi) {
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [931] 	 	 	 case 1:
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [932] 	 	 	 	 transformer_adj = transformer_adj.zyxw; 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [933] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [934] 	 	 	 	 transformer_diag = transformer_diag.zyxw; 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [935] #endif
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [936] 	 	 	 	 break; 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [937] 	 	 	 case 2:
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [938] 	 	 	 	 transformer_adj = transformer_adj.xwzy; 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [939] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [940] 	 	 	 	 transformer_diag = transformer_diag.xwzy; 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [941] #endif
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [942] 	 	 	 	 break; 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [943] 	 	 	 }
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [944] #endif
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [945] 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [946] 	 	 	 vec4 pdiff_sq = POW2(poi_patch_adj - transformer_adj) * spatial_p(vec2(1,0)); 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [947] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [948] 	 	 	 pdiff_sq += POW2(poi_patch_diag - transformer_diag) * spatial_p(vec2(1,1)); 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [949] #endif
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [950] 	 	 	 min_rot = min(dot(pdiff_sq, vec4(1)), min_rot); 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [951] 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [952] // un-reflect
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [953] #if RFI
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [954] 	 	 	 switch(rfi) {
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [955] 	 	 	 case 1:
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [956] 	 	 	 	 transformer_adj = transformer_adj.zyxw; 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [957] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [958] 	 	 	 	 transformer_diag = transformer_diag.zyxw; 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [959] #endif
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [960] 	 	 	 	 break; 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [961] 	 	 	 case 2:
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [962] 	 	 	 	 transformer_adj = transformer_adj.xwzy; 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [963] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [964] 	 	 	 	 transformer_diag = transformer_diag.xwzy; 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [965] #endif
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [966] 	 	 	 	 break; 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [967] 	 	 	 }
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [968] #endif
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [969] 	 	 } // FOR_REFLECTION
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [970] #if RI == 7
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [971] 	 	 transformer_adj = transformer_adj.wxyz; 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [972] 	 	 // swap adjacents for diagonals
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [973] 	 	 transformer_adj += transformer_diag; 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [974] 	 	 transformer_diag = transformer_adj - transformer_diag; 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [975] 	 	 transformer_adj -= transformer_diag; 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [976] #elif RI == 3
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [977] 	 	 transformer_adj = transformer_adj.wxyz; 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [978] #elif RI == 1
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [979] 	 	 transformer_adj = transformer_adj.zwxy; 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [980] #endif
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [981] #if RI == 3 && (PS == 0 || PS == 8)
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [982] 	 	 transformer_diag = transformer_diag.wxyz; 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [983] #elif RI == 1 && (PS == 0 || PS == 8)
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [984] 	 	 transformer_diag = transformer_diag.zwxy; 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [985] #endif
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [986] 	 } // FOR_ROTATION
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [987] 	 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [988] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [989] 	 float total_weight = spatial_p(vec2(0,0)) + 4 * spatial_p(vec2(0,1)) + 4 * spatial_p(vec2(1,1)); 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [990] #else
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [991] 	 float total_weight = spatial_p(vec2(0,0)) + 4 * spatial_p(vec2(0,1)); 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [992] #endif
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [993] 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [994] 	 float center_diff = poi2.x - GET_GUIDE(r).x; 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [995] 	 return normalize_p(POW2(center_diff) + min_rot, max(EPSILON,total_weight)); 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [996] }
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [997] #elif (defined(LUMA_gather) || D1W) && PS == 4 && P == 3 && RI == 0 && RFI == 0 && GATHER
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [998] const ivec2 offsets[4] = { ivec2(0,-1), ivec2(-1,0), ivec2(0,0), ivec2(1,0) }; 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [999] const ivec2 offsets_sf[4] = { ivec2(0,-1) * SF, ivec2(-1,0) * SF, ivec2(0,0) * SF, ivec2(1,0) * SF }; 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1000] vec4 poi_patch = gather_offs(0, offsets); 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1001] vec4 spatial_p_weights = vec4(spatial_p(vec2(0,-1)), spatial_p(vec2(-1,0)), spatial_p(vec2(0,0)), spatial_p(vec2(1,0))); 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1002] float patch_comparison_gather(vec3 r)
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1003] {
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1004] 	 vec4 pdiff = poi_patch - gather_offs(r, offsets_sf); 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1005] 	 return normalize_p(
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1006] 	 	 dot(POW2(pdiff) * spatial_p_weights, vec4(1)),
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1007] 	 	 dot(spatial_p_weights, vec4(1))
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1008] 	 ); 
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1009] }
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1010] #elif (defined(LUMA_gather) || D1W) && PS == 6 && RI == 0 && RFI == 0 && GATHER
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1011] // tiled even square patch_comparison_gather
[ 100.067][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1012] // XXX extend to support odd square?
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1013] float patch_comparison_gather(vec3 r)
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1014] {
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1015] 	 /* gather order:
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1016] 	  * w z
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1017] 	  * x y
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1018] 	  */
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1019] 	 vec2 tile; 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1020] 	 float pdiff_sq = 0; 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1021] 	 float total_weight = 0; 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1022] 	 for (tile.x = -hp;  tile.x < hp;  tile.x+=2) for (tile.y = -hp;  tile.y < hp;  tile.y+=2) {
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1023] 	 	 vec4 diff = gather(tile + r.xy) - gather(tile); 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1024] 	 	 vec4 weights = vec4(spatial_p(tile+vec2(0,1)), spatial_p(tile+vec2(1,1)), spatial_p(tile+vec2(1,0)), spatial_p(tile+vec2(0,0))); 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1025] 	 	 pdiff_sq += dot(POW2(diff) * weights, vec4(1)); 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1026] 	 	 total_weight += dot(weights, vec4(1)); 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1027] 	 }
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1028] 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1029] 	 return normalize_p(pdiff_sq, max(EPSILON,total_weight)); 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1030] }
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1031] #else
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1032] #define patch_comparison_gather patch_comparison
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1033] #define STORE_POI_PATCH 1
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1034] val_guide poi_patch[p_area]; 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1035] #endif
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1036] 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1037] val_guide patch_comparison(vec3 r)
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1038] {
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1039] 	 vec3 p; 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1040] 	 val_guide min_rot = val_guide(p_area); 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1041] 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1042] 	 FOR_ROTATION FOR_REFLECTION {
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1043] 	 	 val_guide pdiff_sq = val_guide(0); 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1044] 	 	 float total_weight = 0; 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1045] 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1046] 	 	 int p_index = 0; 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1047] 	 	 FOR_PATCH(p) {
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1048] #ifdef STORE_POI_PATCH
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1049] 	 	 	 val_guide poi_p = poi_patch[p_index++]; 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1050] #else
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1051] 	 	 	 val_guide poi_p = GET_GUIDE(p); 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1052] #endif
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1053] 	 	 	 vec3 transformed_p = SF * vec3(ref(rot(p.xy, ri), rfi), p.z); 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1054] 	 	 	 val_guide diff_sq = poi_p - GET_GUIDE(transformed_p + r); 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1055] 	 	 	 diff_sq *= diff_sq; 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1056] 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1057] 	 	 	 float weight = spatial_p(p.xy); 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1058] 	 	 	 pdiff_sq += diff_sq * weight; 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1059] 	 	 	 total_weight += weight; 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1060] 	 	 }
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1061] 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1062] 	 	 min_rot = min(min_rot, normalize_p(pdiff_sq, max(EPSILON,total_weight))); 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1063] 	 }
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1064] 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1065] 	 return min_rot; 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1066] }
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1067] 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1068] vec4 hook()
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1069] {
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1070] 	 val_guide total_weight = val_guide(0); 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1071] 	 val sum = val(0); 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1072] 	 val result = val(0); 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1073] 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1074] 	 vec3 r = vec3(0); 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1075] 	 vec3 me = vec3(0); 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1076] 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1077] 	 float sw = SW * spatial_r(vec3(0)); 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1078] 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1079] #if T && ME == 1 // temporal & motion estimation
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1080] 	 vec3 me_tmp = vec3(0); 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1081] 	 float maxweight = 0; 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1082] #elif T && ME == 2 // temporal & motion estimation
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1083] 	 vec3 me_sum = vec3(0); 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1084] 	 float me_weight = 0; 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1085] #endif
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1086] 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1087] #if AS
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1088] 	 float total_weight_as = 0; 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1089] 	 val sum_as = val(0); 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1090] #endif
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1091] 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1092] #if WD == 2 || V == 7 || C
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1093] #define STORE_WEIGHTS 1
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1094] #else
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1095] #define STORE_WEIGHTS 0
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1096] #endif
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1097] 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1098] #if STORE_WEIGHTS
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1099] 	 int r_index = 0; 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1100] 	 val_guide_packed all_weights[r_area]; 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1101] 	 val_packed all_pixels[r_area]; 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1102] #endif
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1103] 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1104] #ifdef STORE_POI_PATCH
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1105] 	 vec3 p; 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1106] 	 int p_index = 0; 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1107] 	 FOR_PATCH(p)
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1108] 	 	 poi_patch[p_index++] = GET_GUIDE(p); 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1109] #endif
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1110] 	 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1111] #if WD == 1 // weight discard (moving cumulative average)
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1112] 	 int r_iter = 1; 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1113] 	 val_guide wd_total_weight = val_guide(0); 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1114] 	 val wd_sum = val(0); 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1115] #endif
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1116] 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1117] #if V == 7
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1118] 	 vec2 v7cell = floor(HOOKED_size/R * HOOKED_pos) * R + hr; 
[ 100.068][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1119] 	 vec2 v7cell_off = floor(HOOKED_pos * HOOKED_size) - floor(v7cell); 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1120] #endif
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1121] 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1122] 	 FOR_FRAME(r) {
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1123] 	 // XXX ME is always a frame behind, should have the option to re-research after applying ME (could do it an arbitrary number of times per frame if desired)
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1124] #if T && ME == 1 // temporal & motion estimation max weight
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1125] 	 if (r.z > 0) {
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1126] 	 	 me += me_tmp * MEF; 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1127] 	 	 me_tmp = vec3(0); 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1128] 	 	 maxweight = 0; 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1129] 	 }
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1130] #elif T && ME == 2 // temporal & motion estimation weighted average
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1131] 	 if (r.z > 0) {
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1132] 	 	 me += round(DIV(me_sum, me_weight) * MEF); 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1133] 	 	 me_sum = vec3(0); 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1134] 	 	 me_weight = 0; 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1135] 	 }
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1136] #endif
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1137] 	 FOR_RESEARCH(r) {
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1138] #if V == 7
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1139] 	 	 r.xy += v7cell_off; 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1140] #endif
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1141] 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1142] 	 	 // r coords with appropriate transformations applied
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1143] 	 	 vec3 tr = vec3(r.xy + floor(r.xy * RSF), r.z); 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1144] 	 	 tr.xy += me.xy; 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1145] 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1146] 	 	 val px = GET(tr); 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1147] 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1148] #if SKIP_PATCH
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1149] 	 	 val weight = val(1); 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1150] #else
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1151] 	 	 val_guide pdiff_sq = (r.z == 0) ? patch_comparison_gather(tr) : patch_comparison(tr); 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1152] 	 	 val_guide weight = range(pdiff_sq); 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1153] #endif
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1154] 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1155] #if T && ME == 1 // temporal & motion estimation max weight
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1156] 	 	 me_tmp = vec3(tr.xy,0) * step(maxweight, weight.x) + me_tmp * (1 - step(maxweight, weight.x)); 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1157] 	 	 maxweight = max(maxweight, weight.x); 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1158] #elif T && ME == 2 // temporal & motion estimation weighted average
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1159] 	 	 me_sum += vec3(tr.xy,0) * weight.x; 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1160] 	 	 me_weight += weight.x; 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1161] #endif
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1162] 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1163] 	 	 weight *= spatial_r(r); 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1164] 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1165] #if AS
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1166] 	 	 float spatial_as_weight = spatial_as(tr); 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1167] 	 	 sum_as += px * spatial_as_weight; 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1168] 	 	 total_weight_as += spatial_as_weight; 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1169] #endif
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1170] 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1171] #if WD == 1 // weight discard (moving cumulative average)
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1172] 	 	 float wd_scale = RECIPROCAL(r_iter); 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1173] 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1174] 	 	 val_guide below_threshold = WDS * abs(min(val_guide(0.0), weight - (total_weight * wd_scale * WDT * WD1TK(sqrt(wd_scale*WDP))))); 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1175] 	 	 val_guide wdkf = MAP_GUIDE(WDK, below_threshold); 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1176] 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1177] 	 	 wd_sum += px * weight * wdkf; 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1178] 	 	 wd_total_weight += weight * wdkf; 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1179] 	 	 r_iter++; 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1180] #if STORE_WEIGHTS
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1181] 	 	 all_weights[r_index] = val_guide_pack(weight * wdkf); 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1182] 	 	 all_pixels[r_index] = val_pack(px); 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1183] 	 	 r_index++; 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1184] #endif
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1185] #elif STORE_WEIGHTS
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1186] 	 	 all_weights[r_index] = val_guide_pack(weight); 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1187] 	 	 all_pixels[r_index] = val_pack(px); 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1188] 	 	 r_index++; 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1189] #endif
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1190] 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1191] #if V == 7
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1192] 	 	 r.xy -= v7cell_off; 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1193] #endif
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1194] 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1195] 	 	 sum += px * weight; 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1196] 	 	 total_weight += weight; 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1197] 	 } // FOR_RESEARCH
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1198] 	 } // FOR_FRAME
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1199] 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1200] 	 val_guide avg_weight = total_weight * r_scale; 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1201] 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1202] #if defined(LUMA_raw) && V == 4
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1203] 	 return unval_guide(avg_weight); 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1204] #elif defined(CHROMA_raw) && V == 4
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1205] 	 return vec4(0.5);  // XXX visualize for chroma
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1206] #endif
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1207] 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1208] #if C
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1209] 	 total_weight = val_guide(0); 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1210] 	 sum = val(0); 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1211] 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1212] 	 for (int c = 0;  c <= C;  c++) {
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1213] 	 	 val_guide_packed all_weights_update[r_area]; 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1214] 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1215] 	 	 r_index = 0; 
[ 100.069][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1216] 	 	 FOR_FRAME(r) FOR_RESEARCH(r) {
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1217] 	 	 	 val_guide c_sum = val_guide(0); 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1218] 	 	 	 vec3 r2 = vec3(0); 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1219] 	 	 	 int r2_index = 0; 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1220] 	 	 	 FOR_FRAME(r2) FOR_RESEARCH(r2)
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1221] 	 	 	 	 if (distance(r, r2) - sqrt(CD) <= FLT_EPSILON)
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1222] 	 	 	 	 	 c_sum += val_guide_unpack(all_weights[r2_index++]); 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1223] 	 	 	 if (length(r) - sqrt(CD) <= FLT_EPSILON)
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1224] 	 	 	 	 c_sum += sw; 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1225] 	 	 	 all_weights_update[r_index++] = val_guide_pack(c_sum); 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1226] 	 	 }
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1227] 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1228] 	 	 r_index = 0; 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1229] 	 	 FOR_FRAME(r) FOR_RESEARCH(r) {
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1230] 	 	 	 val_guide old_weight = val_guide_unpack(all_weights[r_index]); 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1231] 	 	 	 val_guide update = val_guide_unpack(all_weights_update[r_index]); 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1232] 	 	 	 val_guide weight = old_weight * RECIPROCAL(max(EPSILON,CS))
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1233] 	 	 	                  + old_weight * update * r1_scale * CS; 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1234] 	 	 	 all_weights[r_index] = val_guide_pack(weight); 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1235] 	 	 	 if (c == C) { // only need to update this stuff on the final C iteration
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1236] 	 	 	 	 val px = val_unpack(all_pixels[r_index]); 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1237] 	 	 	 	 sum += px * weight; 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1238] 	 	 	 	 total_weight += weight; 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1239] 	 	 	 	 all_pixels[r_index] = val_pack(px); 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1240] 	 	 	 }
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1241] 	 	 	 r_index++; 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1242] 	 	 }
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1243] 	 } // for C
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1244] #endif
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1245] 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1246] #if WD == 2 // weight discard (mean)
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1247] 	 total_weight = val_guide(0); 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1248] 	 sum = val(0); 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1249] 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1250] 	 r_index = 0; 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1251] 	 FOR_FRAME(r) FOR_RESEARCH(r) {
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1252] 	 	 val px = val_unpack(all_pixels[r_index]); 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1253] 	 	 val_guide weight = val_guide_unpack(all_weights[r_index]); 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1254] 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1255] 	 	 val_guide below_threshold = WDS * abs(min(val_guide(0.0), weight - (avg_weight * WDT))); 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1256] 	 	 weight *= MAP_GUIDE(WDK, below_threshold); 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1257] 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1258] 	 	 sum += px * weight; 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1259] 	 	 total_weight += weight; 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1260] #if V == 7
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1261] 	 	 all_pixels[r_index] = val_pack(px); 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1262] 	 	 all_weights[r_index] = val_guide_pack(weight); 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1263] #endif
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1264] 	 	 r_index++; 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1265] 	 } // FOR_FRAME FOR_RESEARCH
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1266] #endif
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1267] 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1268] #if WD == 1 // weight discard (moving cumulative average)
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1269] 	 total_weight = wd_total_weight; 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1270] 	 sum = wd_sum; 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1271] #endif
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1272] 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1273] #if WD // weight discard
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1274] 	 avg_weight = total_weight * r_scale; 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1275] #endif
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1276] 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1277] 	 total_weight += sw; 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1278] 	 sum += poi * sw; 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1279] 	 result = MED_DIV(sum, max(val(EPSILON),val(total_weight))); 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1280] 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1281] 	 // store frames for temporal
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1282] #if T > 1
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1283] 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1284] #endif
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1285] #if T && TRF
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1286] 	 imageStore(PREV1, ivec2(HOOKED_pos*HOOKED_size), unval(result)); 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1287] #elif T
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1288] 	 imageStore(PREV1, ivec2(HOOKED_pos*HOOKED_size), unval_guide(poi2)); 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1289] #endif
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1290] 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1291] #if AS == 1 // sharpen+denoise
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1292] #define AS_base result
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1293] #elif AS == 2 // sharpen only
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1294] #define AS_base poi
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1295] #endif
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1296] 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1297] #if ASI == 0
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1298] #define AS_input result
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1299] #elif ASI == 1
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1300] #define AS_input poi
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1301] #endif
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1302] 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1303] #if AS // sharpening
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1304] 	 val usm = AS_input - MED_DIV(sum_as, max(EPSILON,total_weight_as)); 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1305] 	 usm = POW(usm, ASP); 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1306] 	 const float as_scale_15 = 1.0/1.5; 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1307] 	 usm *= ASAK(abs((AS_base + usm - 0.5) * as_scale_15) * ASA); 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1308] 	 usm *= ASF; 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1309] 	 result = AS_base + usm; 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1310] #endif
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1311] 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1312] #if EP // extremes preserve
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1313] 	 float luminance = EP_texOff(0).x; 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1314] 	 float ep_weight = POW(max(EPSILON, min(1-luminance, luminance)*2), (luminance < 0.5 ? DP : BP)); 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1315] 	 result = mix(poi, result, ep_weight); 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1316] #else
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1317] 	 float ep_weight = 0; 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1318] #endif
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1319] 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1320] #if V == 1
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1321] 	 result = clamp(pow(abs(poi - result), val(0.25)), 0.0, 1.0); 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1322] #elif V == 2
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1323] 	 result = (poi - result) * 0.5 + 0.5; 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1324] #elif V == 3
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1325] 	 result = val(avg_weight); 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1326] #elif V == 5
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1327] 	 result = 0.5 + usm; 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1328] #elif V == 6
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1329] 	 result = val(1 - ep_weight); 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1330] #elif V == 7
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1331] 	 result = val(0); 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1332] 	 r_index = 0; 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1333] 	 FOR_FRAME(r) FOR_RESEARCH(r) {
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1334] 	 	 if (v7cell_off == r.xy)
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1335] 	 	 	 result = val_guide_unpack(all_weights[r_index]); 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1336] 	 	 r_index++; 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1337] 	 }
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1338] 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1339] 	 if (v7cell_off == vec2(0,0))
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1340] 	 	 result = val(SW * spatial_r(vec3(0))); 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1341] #endif
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1342] 
[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1343] // XXX visualize chroma for these

[ 100.070][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1346] #endif
[ 100.071][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1347]

[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 89] vec4 _4001(vec4 color) {

[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [100] // User variables
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [101] 
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [102] // It is generally preferable to denoise luma and chroma differently, so the 
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [103] // user variables for luma and chroma are split.
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [104] 
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [105] // Denoising factor (sigma, higher means more blur)
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [106] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [107] #define S 3.559719405746641
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [108] #else
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [109] #define S 0.644044031464058
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [110] #endif
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [111] 
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [112] /* Noise resistant adaptive sharpening
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [113]  *
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [114]  * AS:
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [115]  * 	- 0: disable
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [116]  * 	- 1: sharpen+denoise
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [117]  * 	- 2: sharpen only
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [118]  * ASF: Higher numbers make a sharper image
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [119]  * ASA: Anti-ringing, higher numbers increase strength
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [120]  * ASP: Power, lower numbers increase sharpening on lower frequency detail
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [121]  * ASS: Equivalent to SS but for ASK instead of SK
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [122]  * ASI:
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [123]  *  - 0: don't sharpen noise
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [124]  *  - 1: sharpen noise
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [125]  */
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [126] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [127] #define AS 0
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [128] #define ASF 0.0
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [129] #define ASA 0.0
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [130] #define ASP 0.0
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [131] #define ASS 0.0
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [132] #define ASI 0
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [133] #else
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [134] #define AS 0
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [135] #define ASF 0.0
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [136] #define ASA 0.0
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [137] #define ASP 0.0
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [138] #define ASS 0.0
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [139] #define ASI 0
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [140] #endif
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [141] 
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [142] /* Starting weight
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [143]  *
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [144]  * AKA the center weight, the weight of the pixel-of-interest.
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [145]  */
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [146] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [147] #define SW 0.5211292610050897
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [148] #else
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [149] #define SW 0.32722815587389364
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [150] #endif
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [151] 
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [152] /* Spatial kernel
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [153]  *
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [154]  * Increasing the spatial sigma (SS) reduces the weight of further 
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [155]  * pixels.
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [156]  *
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [157]  * The intra-patch variants might help with larger patch sizes.
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [158]  *
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [159]  * SST: enables spatial kernel if R>=PST, 0 fully disables
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [160]  * SS: spatial sigma
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [161]  * PSS: intra-patch spatial sigma
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [162]  * PST: enables intra-patch spatial kernel if P>=PST, 0 fully disables
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [163]  */
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [164] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [165] #define SST 1
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [166] #define SS 1.3662208603933492
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [167] #define PST 0
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [168] #define PSS 0.0
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [169] #else
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [170] #define SST 1
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [171] #define SS 0.07604576880459668
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [172] #define PST 0
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [173] #define PSS 0.0
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [174] #endif
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [175] 
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [176] /* Extremes preserve
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [177]  *
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [178]  * This setting is dependent on code generation from shader_cfg, so this 
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [179]  * setting can only be enabled via shader_cfg.
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [180]  *
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [181]  * Reduce denoising in very bright/dark areas.
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [182]  *
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [183]  * The downscaling factor of the EP shader stage affects the size of the area 
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [184]  * checked for luminance.
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [185]  *
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [186]  * This is incompatible with RGB. If you have RGB hooks enabled then you will 
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [187]  * have to delete the EP shader stage or specify EP=0 through shader_cfg.
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [188]  *
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [189]  * EP: 1 to enable, 0 to disable
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [190]  * DP: EP strength on dark areas, 0 to fully denoise
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [191]  * BP: EP strength on bright areas, 0 to fully denoise
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [192]  */
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [193] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [194] #define EP 0
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [195] #define BP 0.0
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [196] #define DP 0.0
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [197] #else
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [198] #define EP 0
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [199] #define BP 0.0
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [200] #define DP 0.0
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [201] #endif
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [202] 
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [203] /* ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS */
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [204] /* ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS */
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [205] /* ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS */
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [206] /* ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS */
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [207] /* ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS * ADVANCED OPTIONS */
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [208] 
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [209] /* textureGather applicable configurations:
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [210]  *
[ 100.074][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [211]  * - PS={0,3,7,8}:P=3:RI={0,1,3,7}:RFI={0,1,2}
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [212]  * - PS={0,8}:P=3:RI={0,1,3,7}:RFI={0,1,2}
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [213]  * - PS=4:P=3:PST=0:RI=0:RFI=0
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [214]  * - PS=6:RI=0:RFI=0
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [215]  *   - Currently the only scalable variant
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [216]  *
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [217]  * Options which always disable textureGather:
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [218]  * 	- NG
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [219]  * 	- SAMPLE
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [220]  * 	- PD
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [221]  *
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [222]  * Running without textureGather may be much slower.
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [223]  */
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [224] 
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [225] /* Patch & research sizes
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [226]  *
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [227]  * P should be an odd number. Higher values are slower and not always better.
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [228]  *
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [229]  * R should be an odd number greater than or equal to 3. Higher values are 
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [230]  * generally better, but slower.
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [231]  */
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [232] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [233] #define P 3
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [234] #define R 3
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [235] #else
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [236] #define P 3
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [237] #define R 5
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [238] #endif
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [239] 
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [240] /* Patch and research shapes
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [241]  *
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [242]  * Different shapes have different speed and quality characteristics. Every 
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [243]  * shape (besides square) is smaller than square.
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [244]  *
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [245]  * PS applies applies to patches, RS applies to research zones.
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [246]  *
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [247]  * 0: square (symmetrical)
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [248]  * 1: horizontal line (asymmetric)
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [249]  * 2: vertical line (asymmetric)
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [250]  * 3: diamond (symmetrical)
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [251]  * 4: triangle (asymmetric, pointing upward)
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [252]  * 5: truncated triangle (asymmetric on two axis, last row halved)
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [253]  * 6: even sized square (asymmetric on two axis)
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [254]  * 7: plus (symmetrical)
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [255]  * 8: plus X (symmetrical)
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [256]  */
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [257] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [258] #define RS 3
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [259] #define PS 3
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [260] #else
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [261] #define RS 3
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [262] #define PS 3
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [263] #endif
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [264] 
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [265] /* Weight discard
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [266]  *
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [267]  * Reduces weights that fall below a fraction of the average weight. This culls 
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [268]  * the most dissimilar samples from the blur, which can yield a better result, 
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [269]  * especially around edges.
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [270]  * 
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [271]  * WD:
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [272]  * 	- 2: Mean. Better quality, but slower and requires GLSL 4.0 or later
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [273]  * 	- 1: Moving cumulative average. Fast but inaccurate, blurs directionally.
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [274]  * 	- 0: Disable
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [275]  *
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [276]  * WDT: Threshold coefficient, higher numbers discard more
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [277]  * WDP (only for WD=1): Increasing reduces the threshold for small sample sizes
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [278]  * WDS (not for WDK=is_zero): Higher numbers are more eager to reduce weights
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [279]  */
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [280] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [281] #define WD 2
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [282] #define WDT 0.6302678350888067
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [283] #define WDP 0.0
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [284] #define WDS 1.0
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [285] #else
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [286] #define WD 0
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [287] #define WDT 0.0
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [288] #define WDP 0.0
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [289] #define WDS 1.0
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [290] #endif
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [291] 
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [292] /* Connectivity
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [293]  *
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [294]  * Increases weights that are near high weights, decreases weights that are 
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [295]  * near low weights.
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [296]  *
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [297]  * C: Number of passes to do, more increases the effect, 0 does nothing
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [298]  * CD: Distance between each pixel and its furthest neighbor
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [299]  * CS: Strength of effect, higher is more
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [300]  */
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [301] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [302] #define C 0
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [303] #define CD 1.0
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [304] #define CS 1.0
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [305] #else
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [306] #define C 0
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [307] #define CD 1.0
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [308] #define CS 1.0
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [309] #endif
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [310] 
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [311] /* Rotational/reflectional invariance
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [312]  *
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [313]  * Number of rotations/reflections to try for each patch comparison. Can be 
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [314]  * slow, but may improve feature preservation. More rotations/reflections gives 
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [315]  * diminishing returns. The most similar rotation/reflection is used.
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [316]  *
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [317]  * The angle in degrees of each rotation is 360/(RI+1), so RI=1 will do a 
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [318]  * single 180 degree rotation, RI=3 will do three 90 degree rotations, etc.
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [319]  *
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [320]  * Consider setting SAMPLE=1 if setting RI to a setting that would require 
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [321]  * sampling between pixels.
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [322]  *
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [323]  * RI: Rotational invariance
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [324]  * RFI (0 to 2): Reflectional invariance
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [325]  */
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [326] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [327] #define RI 0
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [328] #define RFI 2
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [329] #else
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [330] #define RI 0
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [331] #define RFI 0
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [332] #endif
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [333] 
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [334] /* Temporal denoising
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [335]  *
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [336]  * This setting is dependent on code generation from shader_cfg, so this 
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [337]  * setting can only be enabled via shader_cfg.
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [338]  *
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [339]  * Caveats:
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [340]  * 	- Slower:
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [341]  * 		- Gather optimizations only apply to the current frame
[ 100.075][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [342]  * 	- Requires vo=gpu-next
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [343]  * 	- Luma-only (this is a bug)
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [344]  * 	- Buggy
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [345]  *
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [346]  * May cause motion blur and may struggle more with noise that persists across 
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [347]  * multiple frames (e.g., from compression or duplicate frames).
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [348]  *
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [349]  * Motion estimation (ME) should improve quality without impacting speed.
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [350]  *
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [351]  * Increasing temporal distortion (TD) can reduce motion blur.
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [352]  *
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [353]  * T: number of frames used
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [354]  * ME: motion estimation, 0 for none, 1 for max weight, 2 for weighted avg
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [355]  * MEF: estimate factor, compensates for ME being one frame behind
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [356]  * TRF: compare against the denoised frames
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [357]  * TD: temporal distortion, higher numbers give less weight to previous frames
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [358]  */
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [359] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [360] #define T 0
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [361] #define ME 1
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [362] #define MEF 2
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [363] #define TRF 0
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [364] #define TD 1.0
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [365] #else
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [366] #define T 0
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [367] #define ME 0
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [368] #define MEF 2
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [369] #define TRF 0
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [370] #define TD 1.0
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [371] #endif
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [372] 
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [373] /* Kernels
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [374]  *
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [375]  * SK: spatial kernel
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [376]  * RK: range kernel (takes patch differences)
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [377]  * ASK: adaptive sharpening kernel
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [378]  * PSK: intra-patch spatial kernel
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [379]  * WDK: weight discard kernel
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [380]  * WD1TK (WD=1 only): weight discard tolerance kernel
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [381]  *
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [382]  * List of available kernels:
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [383]  *
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [384]  * bicubic
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [385]  * cos
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [386]  * ffexp
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [387]  * gaussian
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [388]  * lanczos
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [389]  * quadratic
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [390]  * quadratic_ (unclamped)
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [391]  * sinc
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [392]  * sinc3
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [393]  * sinc_ (unclamped)
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [394]  * sphinx
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [395]  * sphinx_ (unclamped)
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [396]  * triangle
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [397]  * triangle_ (unclamped)
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [398]  */
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [399] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [400] #define SK gaussian
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [401] #define RK gaussian

[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [416] 
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [417] /* Kernel parameters
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [418]  *
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [419]  * The following kernels take parameters:
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [420]  *
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [421]  * ffexp: K0
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [422]  */
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [423] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [424] #define K0 1.0
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [425] #define K1 1.0
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [426] #else
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [427] #define K0 1.0
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [428] #define K1 1.0
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [429] #endif
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [430] 
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [431] /* Negative kernel parameter offsets
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [432]  *
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [433]  * Usually kernels go high -> low. These parameters allow for a kernel to go 
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [434]  * low -> high -> low.
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [435]  *
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [436]  * Values of 0.0 mean no effect, higher values increase the effect.
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [437]  *
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [438]  * RO: range kernel (takes patch differences)
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [439]  */
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [440] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [441] #define RO 9.4514748889311e-05
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [442] #else
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [443] #define RO 8.568093800527619e-05
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [444] #endif
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [445] 
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [446] /* Sampling method
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [447]  *
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [448]  * In most cases this shouldn't make any difference, only set to bilinear if 
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [449]  * it's necessary to sample between pixels (e.g., RI=2).
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [450]  *
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [451]  * 0: nearest neighbor
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [452]  * 1: bilinear
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [453]  */
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [454] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [455] #define SAMPLE 0
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [456] #else
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [457] #define SAMPLE 0
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [458] #endif
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [459] 
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [460] /* Research scaling factor
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [461]  *
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [462]  * Higher numbers sample more sparsely as the distance from the POI grows.
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [463]  */
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [464] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [465] #define RSF 0.0
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [466] #else
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [467] #define RSF 0.0
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [468] #endif
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [469] 
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [470] // Scaling factor (should match WIDTH/HEIGHT)
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [471] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [472] #define SF 1
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [473] #else
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [474] #define SF 1
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [475] #endif
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [476] 
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [477] // Use the guide image as the input image
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [478] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [479] #define GI 1
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [480] #else
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [481] #define GI 1
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [482] #endif
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [483] 
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [484] /* Visualization
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [485]  *
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [486]  * 0: off
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [487]  * 1: absolute difference between input/output to the power of 0.25
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [488]  * 2: difference between input/output centered on 0.5
[ 100.076][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [489]  * 3: post-WD average weight map
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [490]  * 4: pre-WD average weight map
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [491]  * 5: unsharp mask
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [492]  * 6: EP
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [493]  * 7: celled weight map (incompatible with temporal)
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [494]  */
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [495] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [496] #define V 0
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [497] #else
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [498] #define V 0
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [499] #endif
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [500]

[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [504] #else

[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [535] 
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [536] // Shader code
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [537] 
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [538] #define EPSILON 1.2e-38
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [539] #define FLT_EPSILON 1.19209290E-07
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [540] #define M_PI 3.14159265358979323846
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [541] #define POW2(x) ((x)*(x))
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [542] #define POW3(x) ((x)*(x)*(x))
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [543] 
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [544] // pow() implementation that gives -pow() when x<0
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [545] // avoids actually calling pow() since apparently it's buggy on nvidia
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [546] #define POW(x,y) (exp(log(abs(x)) * y) * sign(x))
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [547] 
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [548] // boolean logic w/ vectors
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [549] // from hdeband
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [550] #define NOT(x) (1 - (x))
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [551] #define AND *
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [552] #define TERNARY(cond, x, y) ((x)*(cond) + (y)*NOT(cond))
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [553] 
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [554] // from FSR
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [555] #if FAST_DIV
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [556] #define RECIPROCAL(x) uintBitsToFloat(uint(0x7ef07ebb) - floatBitsToUint(x))
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [557] #define DIV(x,y) ((x) * RECIPROCAL(y))
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [558] #define MED_RCP_B(x) uintBitsToFloat(uint(0x7ef19fff) - floatBitsToUint(x))
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [559] #define MED_RECIPROCAL(x) (MED_RCP_B(x) * (-MED_RCP_B(x) * x + 2))
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [560] #define MED_DIV(x,y) ((x) * MED_RECIPROCAL(y))
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [561] #else
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [562] #define RECIPROCAL(x) (1.0/(x))
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [563] #define MED_RECIPROCAL(x) (1.0/(x))
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [564] #define DIV(x,y) ((x)/(y))
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [565] #define MED_DIV(x,y) ((x)/(y))
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [566] #endif
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [567] 
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [568] // XXX make kernel params capable of being set per-kernel, e.g., RK0, SK0...
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [569] 
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [570] // kernels
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [571] // XXX sinc & sphinx: 1e-3 was selected tentatively; not sure what the correct value should be (1e-8 is too low)
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [572] #define bicubic(x) bicubic_(clamp((x), 0.0, 2.0))
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [573] #define bicubic_(x) ((1.0/6.0) * (POW3((x)+2) - 4 * POW3((x)+1) + 6 * POW3(x) - 4 * POW3(max((x)-1, 0))))
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [574] #define ffexp(x) (POW(cos(max(EPSILON, clamp(x, 0.0, 1.0) * M_PI)), K0) * 0.5 + 0.5)
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [575] #define gaussian(x) exp(-1 * POW2(x))
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [576] #define is_zero(x) int(x == 0)
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [577] #define lanczos(x) (sinc3(x) * sinc(x))
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [578] #define quadratic(x) quadratic_(clamp((x), 0.0, 1.5))
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [579] #define quadratic_(x) TERNARY(step(x, 0.5), 0.75 - POW2(x), 0.5 * POW2((x) - 1.5))
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [580] #define sinc(x) sinc_(clamp((x), 0.0, 1.0))
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [581] #define sinc3(x) sinc_(clamp((x), 0.0, 3.0))
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [582] #define sinc_(x) TERNARY(step(x, 1e-3), 1.0, DIV(sin((x)*M_PI), ((x)*M_PI)))
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [583] #define sphinx(x) sphinx_(clamp((x), 0.0, 1.4302966531242027))
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [584] #define sphinx_(x) TERNARY(step(x, 1e-3), 1.0, DIV(3.0 * (sin((x)*M_PI) - (x)*M_PI * cos((x)*M_PI)), POW3((x)*M_PI)))
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [585] #define triangle(x) triangle_(clamp((x), 0.0, 1.0))
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [586] #define triangle_(x) (1 - (x))
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [587] 
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [588] #define MAP1(f,param) f(param)
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [589] #define MAP2(f,param) vec2(f(param.x), f(param.y))
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [590] #define MAP3(f,param) vec3(f(param.x), f(param.y), f(param.z))
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [591] 
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [592] #if defined(LUMA_raw)
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [593] #define val float
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [594] #define val_swizz(v) (v.x)
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [595] #define unval(v) vec4(v, 0, 0, poi_.a)
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [596] #define val_packed val
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [597] #define val_pack(v) (v)
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [598] #define val_unpack(v) (v)
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [599] #define MAP MAP1
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [600] #elif defined(CHROMA_raw)
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [601] #define val vec2
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [602] #define val_swizz(v) (v.xy)
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [603] #define unval(v) vec4(v.x, v.y, 0, poi_.a)
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [604] #define val_packed uint
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [605] #define val_pack(v) packUnorm2x16(v)
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [606] #define val_unpack(v) unpackUnorm2x16(v)
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [607] #define MAP MAP2
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [608] #else
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [609] #define val vec3
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [610] #define val_swizz(v) (v.xyz)
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [611] #define unval(v) vec4(v.x, v.y, v.z, poi_.a)
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [612] #define val_packed val
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [613] #define val_pack(v) (v)
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [614] #define val_unpack(v) (v)
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [615] #define MAP MAP3
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [616] #endif
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [617] 
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [618] #if D1W // float guide
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [619] #define val_guide float
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [620] #define val_guide_swizz(v) (v.x)
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [621] #define val_guide_packed float

[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [623] #define val_guide_unpack(v) (v)

[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [637] #else

[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [640] #endif
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [641] 
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [642] #if PS == 6
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [643] const int hp = P/2;
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [644] #else
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [645] const float hp = int(P/2) - 0.5*(1-(P%2)); // sample between pixels for even patch sizes
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [646] #endif
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [647] 
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [648] #if RS == 6
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [649] const int hr = R/2;
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [650] #else
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [651] const float hr = int(R/2) - 0.5*(1-(R%2)); // sample between pixels for even research sizes
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [652] #endif
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [653] 
[ 100.077][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [654] // patch/research shapes
[ 100.078][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [655] // each shape is depicted in a comment, where Z=5 (Z corresponds to P or R)
[ 100.078][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [656] // dots (.) represent samples (pixels) and X represents the pixel-of-interest
[ 100.078][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [657] 
[ 100.078][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [658] // Z    .....
[ 100.078][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [659] // Z    .....
[ 100.078][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [660] // Z    ..X..

[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [821] 
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [822] #if SAMPLE == 0
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [823] #define sample(tex, pos, size, pt, off) tex((pos) + (pt) * (vec2(off) + 0.5 - fract((pos) * (size))))
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [824] #else
