[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [826] #endif
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [827] 
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [828] /* Guide images are bound through the G (luma) GC (chroma, or non-luma) 
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [829]  * textures. When bound, these are where the weights are computed. Otherwise 
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [830]  * the weights are computed on the hooked texture.
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [831]  */
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [832] 
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [833] #if GI && defined(LUMA_raw)
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [834] #define GET_(off) sample(G_tex, G_pos, G_size, G_pt, off)
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [835] #elif GI
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [836] #define GET_(off) sample(GC_tex, GC_pos, GC_size, GC_pt, off)
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [837] #else
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [838] #define GET_(off) sample(HOOKED_tex, HOOKED_pos, HOOKED_size, HOOKED_pt, off)
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [839] #endif
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [840] 
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [841] #if defined(G_raw) && (defined(LUMA_raw) || D1W)
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [842] #define GET_GUIDE_(off) sample(G_tex, G_pos, G_size, G_pt, off)
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [843] #define gather_offs(off, off_arr) (G_mul * vec4(textureGatherOffsets(G_raw, G_pos + vec2(off) * G_pt, off_arr)))
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [844] #define gather(off) G_gather(G_pos + (off) * G_pt, 0)
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [845] #elif defined(GC_raw)
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [846] #define GET_GUIDE_(off) sample(GC_tex, GC_pos, GC_size, GC_pt, off)
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [847] #else
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [848] #define GET_GUIDE_(off) GET_(off)
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [849] #define gather_offs(off, off_arr) (HOOKED_mul * vec4(textureGatherOffsets(HOOKED_raw, HOOKED_pos + vec2(off) * HOOKED_pt, off_arr)))
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [850] #define gather(off) HOOKED_gather(HOOKED_pos + (off)*HOOKED_pt, 0)
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [851] #endif
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [852] 
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [853] #if T
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [854] val GET(vec3 off)
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [855] {
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [856] 	switch (min(int(off.z), frame)) {
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [857] 	case 0: return val_swizz(GET_(off));
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [858] 
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [859] 	}
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [860] }
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [861] val GET_GUIDE(vec3 off)
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [862] {
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [863] 	return off.z == 0 ? val_guide_swizz(GET_GUIDE_(off)) : GET(off);
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [864] }
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [865] #else
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [866] #define GET(off) val_swizz(GET_(off))
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [867] #define GET_GUIDE(off) val_guide_swizz(GET_GUIDE_(off))
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [868] #endif
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [869] 
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [870] vec4 poi_ = GET_(vec3(0));
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [871] vec4 poi2_ = GET_GUIDE_(vec3(0));
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [872] val poi = val_swizz(poi_); // pixel-of-interest
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [873] val_guide poi2 = val_guide_swizz(poi2_); // guide pixel-of-interest
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [874] 
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [875] #if RI // rotation
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [876] vec2 rot(vec2 p, float d)
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [877] {
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [878] 	return vec2(
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [879] 		p.x * cos(radians(d)) - p.y * sin(radians(d)),
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [880] 		p.y * sin(radians(d)) + p.x * cos(radians(d))
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [881] 	);
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [882] }
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [883] #else
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [884] #define rot(p, d) (p)
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [885] #endif
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [886] 
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [887] #if RFI // reflection
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [888] vec2 ref(vec2 p, int d)
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [889] {
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [890] 	switch (d) {
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [891] 	case 0: return p;
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [892] 	case 1: return p * vec2(1, -1);
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [893] 	case 2: return p * vec2(-1, 1);
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [894] 	}
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [895] }
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [896] #else
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [897] #define ref(p, d) (p)
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [898] #endif
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [899] 
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [900] #if SST && R >= SST
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [901] float spatial_r(vec3 v)
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [902] {
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [903] 	v.xy += 0.5 - fract(HOOKED_pos*HOOKED_size);
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [904] 	v.z *= TD;
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [905] 	return SK(length(v)*SS);
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [906] }
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [907] #else
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [908] #define spatial_r(v) (1)
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [909] #endif
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [910] 
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [911] // 2D blur for sharpening
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [912] #if AS
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [913] float spatial_as(vec3 v)
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [914] {
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [915] 	v.xy += 0.5 - fract(HOOKED_pos*HOOKED_size);
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [916] 	return ASK(length(v)*ASS) * int(v.z == 0);
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [917] }
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [918] #endif
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [919] 
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [920] #if PST && P >= PST
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [921] #define spatial_p(v) PSK(length(v)*PSS)
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [922] #define normalize_p(x,expr) DIV((x), (expr))
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [923] #else
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [924] #define spatial_p(v) (1)
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [925] #define normalize_p(x,expr) ((x) * p_scale)
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [926] #endif
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [927] 
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [928] const float pdiff_scale = 1.0/max(EPSILON,POW2(S*0.013));
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [929] val_guide range(val_guide pdiff_sq)
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [930] {
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [931] 	pdiff_sq = sqrt(abs(pdiff_sq - max(EPSILON, RO)) * pdiff_scale);
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [932] 	return RK(pdiff_sq);
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [933] }
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [934] 
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [935] #define GATHER (PD == 0 && NG == 0 && SAMPLE == 0) // never textureGather if any of these conditions are false
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [936] #define REGULAR_ROTATIONS (RI == 0 || RI == 1 || RI == 3 || RI == 7)
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [937] 
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [938] #if (defined(LUMA_gather) || D1W) && ((PS == 0 || ((PS == 3 || PS == 7) && RI != 7) || PS == 8) && P == 3) && REGULAR_ROTATIONS && GATHER
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [939] // 3x3 diamond/plus or square patch_comparison_gather
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [940] const ivec2 offsets_adj[4] = { ivec2(0,-1), ivec2(1,0), ivec2(0,1), ivec2(-1,0) };
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [941] const ivec2 offsets_adj_sf[4] = { ivec2(0,-1) * SF, ivec2(1,0) * SF, ivec2(0,1) * SF, ivec2(-1,0) * SF };
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [942] vec4 poi_patch_adj = gather_offs(0, offsets_adj);
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [943] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [944] const ivec2 offsets_diag[4] = { ivec2(-1,-1), ivec2(1,-1), ivec2(1,1), ivec2(-1,1) };
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [945] const ivec2 offsets_diag_sf[4] = { ivec2(-1,-1) * SF, ivec2(1,-1) * SF, ivec2(1,1) * SF, ivec2(-1,1) * SF };
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [946] vec4 poi_patch_diag = gather_offs(0, offsets_diag);
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [947] #endif
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [948] float patch_comparison_gather(vec3 r)
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [949] {
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [950] 	float min_rot = p_area - 1;
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [951] 	vec4 transformer_adj = gather_offs(r, offsets_adj_sf);
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [952] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [953] 	vec4 transformer_diag = gather_offs(r, offsets_diag_sf);
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [954] #endif
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [955] 	FOR_ROTATION {
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [956] 		FOR_REFLECTION {
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [957] #if RFI
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [958] 			/* xxy
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [959] 			 * w y
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [960] 			 * wzz
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [961] 			 */
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [962] 			switch(rfi) {
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [963] 			case 1:
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [964] 				transformer_adj = transformer_adj.zyxw;
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [965] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [966] 				transformer_diag = transformer_diag.zyxw;
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [967] #endif
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [968] 				break;
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [969] 			case 2:
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [970] 				transformer_adj = transformer_adj.xwzy;
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [971] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [972] 				transformer_diag = transformer_diag.xwzy;
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [973] #endif
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [974] 				break;
[ 100.079][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [975] 			}
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [976] #endif
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [977] 
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [978] 			vec4 pdiff_sq = POW2(poi_patch_adj - transformer_adj) * spatial_p(vec2(1,0));
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [979] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [980] 			pdiff_sq += POW2(poi_patch_diag - transformer_diag) * spatial_p(vec2(1,1));
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [981] #endif
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [982] 			min_rot = min(dot(pdiff_sq, vec4(1)), min_rot);
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [983] 
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [984] // un-reflect
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [985] #if RFI
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [986] 			switch(rfi) {
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [987] 			case 1:
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [988] 				transformer_adj = transformer_adj.zyxw;
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [989] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [990] 				transformer_diag = transformer_diag.zyxw;
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [991] #endif
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [992] 				break;
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [993] 			case 2:
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [994] 				transformer_adj = transformer_adj.xwzy;
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [995] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [996] 				transformer_diag = transformer_diag.xwzy;
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [997] #endif
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [998] 				break;
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [999] 			}
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1000] #endif
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1001] 		} // FOR_REFLECTION
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1002] #if RI == 7
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1003] 		transformer_adj = transformer_adj.wxyz;
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1004] 		// swap adjacents for diagonals
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1005] 		transformer_adj += transformer_diag;
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1006] 		transformer_diag = transformer_adj - transformer_diag;
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1007] 		transformer_adj -= transformer_diag;
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1008] #elif RI == 3
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1009] 		transformer_adj = transformer_adj.wxyz;
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1010] #elif RI == 1
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1011] 		transformer_adj = transformer_adj.zwxy;
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1012] #endif
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1013] #if RI == 3 && (PS == 0 || PS == 8)
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1014] 		transformer_diag = transformer_diag.wxyz;
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1015] #elif RI == 1 && (PS == 0 || PS == 8)
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1016] 		transformer_diag = transformer_diag.zwxy;
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1017] #endif
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1018] 	} // FOR_ROTATION
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1019] 	
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1020] #if PS == 0 || PS == 8
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1021] 	float total_weight = spatial_p(vec2(0,0)) + 4 * spatial_p(vec2(0,1)) + 4 * spatial_p(vec2(1,1));
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1022] #else
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1023] 	float total_weight = spatial_p(vec2(0,0)) + 4 * spatial_p(vec2(0,1));
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1024] #endif
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1025] 
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1026] 	float center_diff = poi2.x - GET_GUIDE(r).x;
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1027] 	return normalize_p(POW2(center_diff) + min_rot, max(EPSILON,total_weight));
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1028] }
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1029] #elif (defined(LUMA_gather) || D1W) && PS == 4 && P == 3 && RI == 0 && RFI == 0 && GATHER
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1030] const ivec2 offsets[4] = { ivec2(0,-1), ivec2(-1,0), ivec2(0,0), ivec2(1,0) };
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1031] const ivec2 offsets_sf[4] = { ivec2(0,-1) * SF, ivec2(-1,0) * SF, ivec2(0,0) * SF, ivec2(1,0) * SF };
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1032] vec4 poi_patch = gather_offs(0, offsets);
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1033] vec4 spatial_p_weights = vec4(spatial_p(vec2(0,-1)), spatial_p(vec2(-1,0)), spatial_p(vec2(0,0)), spatial_p(vec2(1,0)));
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1034] float patch_comparison_gather(vec3 r)
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1035] {
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1036] 	vec4 pdiff = poi_patch - gather_offs(r, offsets_sf);
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1037] 	return normalize_p(
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1038] 		dot(POW2(pdiff) * spatial_p_weights, vec4(1)),
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1039] 		dot(spatial_p_weights, vec4(1))
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1040] 	);
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1041] }
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1042] #elif (defined(LUMA_gather) || D1W) && PS == 6 && RI == 0 && RFI == 0 && GATHER
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1043] // tiled even square patch_comparison_gather
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1044] // XXX extend to support odd square?
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1045] float patch_comparison_gather(vec3 r)
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1046] {
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1047] 	/* gather order:
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1048] 	 * w z
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1049] 	 * x y
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1050] 	 */
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1051] 	vec2 tile;
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1052] 	float pdiff_sq = 0;
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1053] 	float total_weight = 0;
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1054] 	for (tile.x = -hp; tile.x < hp; tile.x+=2) for (tile.y = -hp; tile.y < hp; tile.y+=2) {
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1055] 		vec4 diff = gather(tile + r.xy) - gather(tile);
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1056] 		vec4 weights = vec4(spatial_p(tile+vec2(0,1)), spatial_p(tile+vec2(1,1)), spatial_p(tile+vec2(1,0)), spatial_p(tile+vec2(0,0)));
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1057] 		pdiff_sq += dot(POW2(diff) * weights, vec4(1));
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1058] 		total_weight += dot(weights, vec4(1));
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1059] 	}
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1060] 
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1061] 	return normalize_p(pdiff_sq, max(EPSILON,total_weight));
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1062] }
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1063] #else
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1064] #define patch_comparison_gather patch_comparison
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1065] #define STORE_POI_PATCH 1
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1066] val_guide poi_patch[p_area];
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1067] #endif
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1068] 
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1069] val_guide patch_comparison(vec3 r)
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1070] {
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1071] 	vec3 p;
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1072] 	val_guide min_rot = val_guide(p_area);
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1073] 
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1074] 	FOR_ROTATION FOR_REFLECTION {
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1075] 		val_guide pdiff_sq = val_guide(0);
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1076] 		float total_weight = 0;
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1077] 
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1078] 		int p_index = 0;
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1079] 		FOR_PATCH(p) {
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1080] #ifdef STORE_POI_PATCH
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1081] 			val_guide poi_p = poi_patch[p_index++];
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1082] #else
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1083] 			val_guide poi_p = GET_GUIDE(p);
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1084] #endif
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1085] 			vec3 transformed_p = SF * vec3(ref(rot(p.xy, ri), rfi), p.z);
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1086] 			val_guide diff_sq = poi_p - GET_GUIDE(transformed_p + r);
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1087] 			diff_sq *= diff_sq;
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1088] 
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1089] 			float weight = spatial_p(p.xy);
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1090] 			pdiff_sq += diff_sq * weight;
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1091] 			total_weight += weight;
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1092] 		}
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1093] 
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1094] 		min_rot = min(min_rot, normalize_p(pdiff_sq, max(EPSILON,total_weight)));
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1095] 	}
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1096] 
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1097] 	return min_rot;
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1098] }
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1099] 
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1100] vec4 hook()
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1101] {
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1102] 	val_guide total_weight = val_guide(0);
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1103] 	val sum = val(0);
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1104] 	val result = val(0);
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1105] 
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1106] 	vec3 r = vec3(0);
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1107] 	vec3 me = vec3(0);
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1108] 
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1109] 	float sw = SW * spatial_r(vec3(0));
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1110] 
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1111] #if T && ME == 1 // temporal & motion estimation
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1112] 	vec3 me_tmp = vec3(0);
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1113] 	float maxweight = 0;
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1114] #elif T && ME == 2 // temporal & motion estimation
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1115] 	vec3 me_sum = vec3(0);
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1116] 	float me_weight = 0;
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1117] #endif
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1118] 
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1119] #if AS
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1120] 	float total_weight_as = 0;
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1121] 	val sum_as = val(0);
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1122] #endif
[ 100.080][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1123]

[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1142] 	
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1143] #if WD == 1 // weight discard (moving cumulative average)
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1144] 	int r_iter = 1;
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1145] 	val_guide wd_total_weight = val_guide(0);

[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1148] 
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1149] #if V == 7
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1150] 	vec2 v7cell = floor(HOOKED_size/R * HOOKED_pos) * R + hr;

[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1152] #endif
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1153] 
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1154] 	FOR_FRAME(r) {
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1155] 	// XXX ME is always a frame behind, should have the option to re-research after applying ME (could do it an arbitrary number of times per frame if desired)
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1156] #if T && ME == 1 // temporal & motion estimation max weight
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1157] 	if (r.z > 0) {
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1158] 		me += me_tmp * MEF;
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1159] 		me_tmp = vec3(0);
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1160] 		maxweight = 0;
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1161] 	}
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1162] #elif T && ME == 2 // temporal & motion estimation weighted average
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1163] 	if (r.z > 0) {
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1164] 		me += round(DIV(me_sum, me_weight) * MEF);
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1165] 		me_sum = vec3(0);
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1166] 		me_weight = 0;
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1167] 	}
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1168] #endif
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1169] 	FOR_RESEARCH(r) {
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1170] #if V == 7
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1171] 		r.xy += v7cell_off;
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1172] #endif
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1173] 
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1174] 		// r coords with appropriate transformations applied
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1175] 		vec3 tr = vec3(r.xy + floor(r.xy * RSF), r.z);
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1176] 		tr.xy += me.xy;
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1177] 
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1178] 		val px = GET(tr);
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1179] 
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1180] #if SKIP_PATCH
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1181] 		val weight = val(1);
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1182] #else
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1183] 		val_guide pdiff_sq = (r.z == 0) ? patch_comparison_gather(tr) : patch_comparison(tr);
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1184] 		val_guide weight = range(pdiff_sq);
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1185] #endif
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1186] 
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1187] #if T && ME == 1 // temporal & motion estimation max weight
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1188] 		me_tmp = vec3(tr.xy,0) * step(maxweight, weight.x) + me_tmp * (1 - step(maxweight, weight.x));
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1189] 		maxweight = max(maxweight, weight.x);
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1190] #elif T && ME == 2 // temporal & motion estimation weighted average
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1191] 		me_sum += vec3(tr.xy,0) * weight.x;
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1192] 		me_weight += weight.x;
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1193] #endif
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1194] 
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1195] 		weight *= spatial_r(r);
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1196] 
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1197] #if AS
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1198] 		float spatial_as_weight = spatial_as(tr);
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1199] 		sum_as += px * spatial_as_weight;
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1200] 		total_weight_as += spatial_as_weight;
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1201] #endif
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1202] 
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1203] #if WD == 1 // weight discard (moving cumulative average)
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1204] 		float wd_scale = RECIPROCAL(r_iter);
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1205] 
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1206] 		val_guide below_threshold = WDS * abs(min(val_guide(0.0), weight - (total_weight * wd_scale * WDT * WD1TK(sqrt(wd_scale*WDP)))));
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1207] 		val_guide wdkf = MAP_GUIDE(WDK, below_threshold);
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1208] 
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1209] 		wd_sum += px * weight * wdkf;
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1210] 		wd_total_weight += weight * wdkf;
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1211] 		r_iter++;
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1212] #if STORE_WEIGHTS

[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1214] 		all_pixels[r_index] = val_pack(px);
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1215] 		r_index++;
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1216] #endif
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1217] #elif STORE_WEIGHTS
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1218] 		all_weights[r_index] = val_guide_pack(weight);
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1219] 		all_pixels[r_index] = val_pack(px);
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1220] 		r_index++;
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1221] #endif
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1222] 
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1223] #if V == 7
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1224] 		r.xy -= v7cell_off;
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1225] #endif
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1226] 
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1227] 		sum += px * weight;
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1228] 		total_weight += weight;
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1229] 	} // FOR_RESEARCH
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1230] 	} // FOR_FRAME
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1231] 
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1232] 	val_guide avg_weight = total_weight * r_scale;
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1233] 
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1234] #if defined(LUMA_raw) && V == 4

[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1239] 
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1240] #if C

[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1247] 		r_index = 0;
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1248] 		FOR_FRAME(r) FOR_RESEARCH(r) {
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1249] 			val_guide c_sum = val_guide(0);
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1250] 			vec3 r2 = vec3(0);
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1251] 			int r2_index = 0;
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1252] 			FOR_FRAME(r2) FOR_RESEARCH(r2)
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1253] 				if (distance(r, r2) - sqrt(CD) <= FLT_EPSILON)
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1254] 					c_sum += val_guide_unpack(all_weights[r2_index++]);
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1255] 			if (length(r) - sqrt(CD) <= FLT_EPSILON)
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1256] 				c_sum += sw;

[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1258] 		}
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1259] 
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1260] 		r_index = 0;
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1261] 		FOR_FRAME(r) FOR_RESEARCH(r) {

[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1264] 			val_guide weight = old_weight * RECIPROCAL(max(EPSILON,CS))
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1265] 			                 + old_weight * update * r1_scale * CS;
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1266] 			all_weights[r_index] = val_guide_pack(weight);
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1267] 			if (c == C) { // only need to update this stuff on the final C iteration
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1268] 				val px = val_unpack(all_pixels[r_index]);
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1269] 				sum += px * weight;
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1270] 				total_weight += weight;
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1271] 				all_pixels[r_index] = val_pack(px);
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1272] 			}
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1273] 			r_index++;
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1274] 		}

[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1281] 
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1282] 	r_index = 0;
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1283] 	FOR_FRAME(r) FOR_RESEARCH(r) {

[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1286]

[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1292] #if V == 7

[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1295] #endif
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1296] 		r_index++;
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1297] 	} // FOR_FRAME FOR_RESEARCH
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1298] #endif

[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1301] 	total_weight = wd_total_weight;
[ 100.081][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1302] 	sum = wd_sum;
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1303] #endif
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1304] 
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1305] #if WD // weight discard

[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1310] 	sum += poi * sw;
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1311] 	result = MED_DIV(sum, max(val(EPSILON),val(total_weight)));

[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1327] #endif
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1328] 
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1329] #if ASI == 0

[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1331] #elif ASI == 1
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1332] #define AS_input poi
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1333] #endif
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1334] 
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1335] #if AS // sharpening
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1336] 	val usm = AS_input - MED_DIV(sum_as, max(EPSILON,total_weight_as));
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1337] 	usm = POW(usm, ASP);
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1338] 	const float as_scale_15 = 1.0/1.5;
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1339] 	usm *= ASAK(abs((AS_base + usm - 0.5) * as_scale_15) * ASA);
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1340] 	usm *= ASF;
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1341] 	result = AS_base + usm;
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1342] #endif
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1343] 
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1344] #if EP // extremes preserve
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1345] 	float luminance = EP_texOff(0).x;
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1346] 	float ep_weight = POW(max(EPSILON, min(1-luminance, luminance)*2), (luminance < 0.5 ? DP : BP));
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1347] 	result = mix(poi, result, ep_weight);
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1348] #else
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1349] 	float ep_weight = 0;
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1350] #endif
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1351] 
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1352] #if V == 1
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1353] 	result = clamp(pow(abs(poi - result), val(0.25)), 0.0, 1.0);
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1354] #elif V == 2
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1355] 	result = (poi - result) * 0.5 + 0.5;
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1356] #elif V == 3
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1357] 	result = val(avg_weight);
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1358] #elif V == 5

[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1360] #elif V == 6
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1361] 	result = val(1 - ep_weight);
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1362] #elif V == 7
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1363] 	result = val(0);
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1364] 	r_index = 0;
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1365] 	FOR_FRAME(r) FOR_RESEARCH(r) {
[ 100.082][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [1366] 		if (v7cell_off == r.xy)

[ 109.965][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [108] vec2 base = pos - fcoord * pt - pt * vec2(float(1));
[ 109.965][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [109] vec4 ws;
[ 109.965][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [110] float off;

[ 109.965][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [113]     vec2 lo = vec2(1e9);
[ 109.965][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [114] #pragma unroll 4

[ 109.965][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [116]     if (n % 4u == 0u)

[ 109.965][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [118]     off = float(n);

[ 109.965][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [121]             lo = min(lo, c);
[ 109.965][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [122]             hi = max(hi, c);
[ 109.965][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [123]         }
[ 109.965][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [124]     ca += ws[n % 4u] * c;
[ 109.965][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [125] }
[ 109.965][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [126]     ca = mix(ca, clamp(ca, lo, hi), /*cfg_antiring*/_a00e);

[ 109.965][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [128] }

[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 18] 
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 19] /* This is an implementation of a debanding algorithm where homogeneous regions 
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 20]  * are blurred with neighboring homogeneous regions.
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 21]  *
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 22]  * This should run prior to any other shaders and mpv's built in debanding 
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 23]  * should be disabled by setting deband=no in mpv.conf
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 24]  */
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 25] 
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 26] //!HOOK LUMA
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 27] //!HOOK CHROMA
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 28] //!HOOK RGB
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 29] //!BIND HOOKED
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 30] //!DESC hdeband
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 31] 
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 32] // User variables
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 33] 
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 34] // Lower numbers increase blur over longer distances
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 35] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 36] #define S 0.039716259676045834
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 37] #else
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 38] #define S 0.00245792863046567
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 39] #endif
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 40] 
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 41] // Lower numbers blur more when intensity varies more between bands
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 42] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 43] #define SI 13.401712932601427
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 44] #else
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 45] #define SI 10.923402488160853
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 46] #endif
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 47] 
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 48] // Higher numbers reduce blur for shorter runs
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 49] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 50] #define SR 0.003446736773092952
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 51] #else
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 52] #define SR 0.012925109858034363
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 53] #endif
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 54] 
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 55] // Starting weight, lower values give less weight to the input image
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 56] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 57] #define SW 0.43999145467432316
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 58] #else
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 59] #define SW 0.009466672829458444
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 60] #endif
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 61] 
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 62] // Bigger numbers search further, but slower
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 63] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 64] #define RADIUS 8
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 65] #else
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 66] #define RADIUS 8
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 67] #endif
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 68] 
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 69] // Bigger numbers search further, but less accurate
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 70] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 71] #define SPARSITY 0.0
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 72] #else
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 73] #define SPARSITY 0.0
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 74] #endif
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 75] 
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 76] // Bigger numbers search in more directions, slower (max 8)
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 77] // Only 4 and 8 are symmetrical, everything else blurs directionally
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 78] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 79] #define DIRECTIONS 8
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 80] #else
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 81] #define DIRECTIONS 8
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 82] #endif
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 83] 
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 84] // A region is considered a run if it varies less than this
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 85] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 86] #define TOLERANCE 0.001
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 87] #else
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 88] #define TOLERANCE 0.001
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 89] #endif
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 90] 
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 91] // 0 for avg, 1 for min, 2 for max
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 92] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 93] #define M 0
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 94] #else
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 95] #define M 0
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 96] #endif
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 97] 
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 98] // Shader code
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 99] 
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [100] #define gaussian(x) exp(-1 * (x) * (x))
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [101] 
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [102] // boolean logic w/ vectors
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [103] #define NOT(x) (1 - (x))
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [104] #define AND *
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [105] #define TERNARY(cond, x, y) ((x)*(cond) + (y)*NOT(cond))
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [106] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [107] #define EQ(x,y) val(val(x) == val(y))
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [108] #else
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [109] #define EQ(x,y) val(equal(val(x),val(y)))
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [110] #endif
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [111] 
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [112] // from NLM
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [113] #if defined(LUMA_raw)
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [114] #define val float
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [115] #define val_swizz(v) (v.x)
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [116] #define unval(v) vec4(v.x, 0, 0, poi_.a)
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [117] #define val_packed val
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [118] #define val_pack(v) (v)
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [119] #define val_unpack(v) (v)
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [120] #define MAP(f,param) f(param)
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [121] #elif defined(CHROMA_raw)
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [122] #define val vec2
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [123] #define val_swizz(v) (v.xy)
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [124] #define unval(v) vec4(v.x, v.y, 0, poi_.a)
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [125] #define val_packed uint
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [126] #define val_pack(v) packUnorm2x16(v)
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [127] #define val_unpack(v) unpackUnorm2x16(v)
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [128] #define MAP(f,param) vec2(f(param.x), f(param.y))
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [129] #else
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [130] #define val vec3
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [131] #define val_swizz(v) (v.xyz)
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [132] #define unval(v) vec4(v.x, v.y, v.z, poi_.a)
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [133] #define val_packed val
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [134] #define val_pack(v) (v)
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [135] #define val_unpack(v) (v)
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [136] #define MAP(f,param) vec3(f(param.x), f(param.y), f(param.z))
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [137] #endif
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [138] 
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [139] vec4 poi_ = HOOKED_texOff(0);
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [140] val poi = val_swizz(poi_);
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [141] 
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [142] /* Description of the algorithm:
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [143]  *
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [144]  * 1. For each pixel in the image (pixel-of-interest, POI):
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [145]  *   2. Accumulate its value with a weight of 1
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [146]  *   3. For each direction (adjacent/diagonal):
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [147]  *     4. For each pixel in that direction, originating from the POI and ending at an arbitrary limit, excluding the POI itself:
[3086.624][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [148]  *       5. If this pixel has the same value as the previous pixel (including POI) or the next pixel:
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [149]  *         5a. Accumulate its value with a weight of 1
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [150]  *       5b. Otherwise, stop accumulating in this direction
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [151]  *   6. Return the sum of the accumulated weighted pixel values divided by the sum of their weights
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [152]  *
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [153]  * Things this implementation does to make this algorithm more useful:
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [154]  *   - For steps 2 and 5, better weights should be used:
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [155]  *     - For step 5, multiply the weight by the gaussian of the absolute difference between the pixel's value and the POI value
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [156]  *       - This decreases blur for large shifts in intensity
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [157]  *       - The difference is scaled with a user parameter (SI)
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [158]  *     - For steps 2 and 5, multiply the weight of any pixels with values identical to the POI value by a user-specified value (SW)
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [159]  *       - Decreasing SW increases the amount of blur
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [160]  *     - For step 5, multiply the weight by the gaussian of the Euclidean norm of the pixel coordinates
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [161]  *   - For step 4, a parameter (SPARSITY) is taken which directs pixels to be skipped at a specified interval
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [162]  *     - If the pixel after a skipped pixel has the same value as the previous unskipped pixel then its weight is doubled
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [163]  *     - This works well in big flat banded areas but may result in artifacts elsewhere
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [164]  *   - For step 5 and SW, pixels are considered to have the same value if their absolute difference is within a threshold
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [165]  *   - The number of directions in step 3 are user configurable
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [166]  */
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [167] 
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [168] vec4 hook()
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [169] {
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [170] 	val sum = val(poi * SW);
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [171] #if M == 1 // min
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [172] 	val total_weight = val(RADIUS);
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [173] #elif M == 2 // max
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [174] 	val total_weight = val(0);
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [175] #else // avg
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [176] 	val total_weight = val(SW);
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [177] #endif
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [178] 
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [179] 	for (int dir = 0; dir < DIRECTIONS; dir++) {
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [180] 		vec2 direction;
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [181] 		switch (dir) {
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [182] 		case 0: direction = vec2( 1, 0); break;
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [183] 		case 1: direction = vec2(-1, 0); break;
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [184] 		case 2: direction = vec2( 0, 1); break;
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [185] 		case 3: direction = vec2( 0,-1); break;
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [186] 		case 4: direction = vec2( 1, 1); break;
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [187] 		case 5: direction = vec2(-1,-1); break;
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [188] 		case 6: direction = vec2( 1,-1); break;
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [189] 		case 7: direction = vec2(-1, 1); break;
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [190] 		}
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [191] 
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [192] 		val prev_px = poi;
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [193] 		val prev_was_run = val(0);
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [194] 		val prev_weight = val(1);
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [195] 		val not_done = val(1);
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [196] 		val run = val(1);
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [197] 		val dir_sum = poi * SW;
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [198] 		val dir_total_weight = val(SW);
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [199] 		for (int i = 1; i <= RADIUS; i++) {
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [200] 			float sparsity = floor(i * SPARSITY);
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [201] 			val px = val_swizz(HOOKED_texOff((i + sparsity) * direction));
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [202] 			val is_run = step(abs(prev_px - px), val(TOLERANCE));
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [203] 
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [204] 			// stop blurring after discovering a 1px run
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [205] 			not_done *= step(val(1), prev_was_run + is_run);
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [206] 
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [207] 			// consider skipped pixels as runs if their neighbors are both runs
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [208] 			float sparsity_delta = sparsity - floor((i - 1) * SPARSITY);
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [209] 			float prev_sparsity = floor((i - 1) * SPARSITY);
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [210] 			val weight = val(gaussian(length((i + sparsity) * direction) * max(0.0, S)));
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [211] 			weight = is_run * weight + is_run * prev_weight * sparsity_delta;
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [212] 
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [213] 			// run's 2nd pixel has weight increased to compensate for 1st pixel's weight of 0
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [214] 			// XXX doesn't account for sparsity
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [215] 			weight += prev_weight * NOT(prev_was_run);
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [216] 
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [217] 			weight *= gaussian(abs(poi - px) * max(0.0, SI));
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [218] 
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [219] 			weight *= gaussian((run += is_run) * SR);
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [220] 
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [221] 			dir_sum += prev_px * weight * not_done;
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [222] 			dir_total_weight += weight * not_done;
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [223] 
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [224] 			prev_px = TERNARY(is_run, prev_px, px);
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [225] 			prev_was_run = is_run;
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [226] 			prev_weight = weight;
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [227] 		}
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [228] #if M == 1
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [229] 		sum = TERNARY(step(dir_total_weight, total_weight), dir_sum, sum);
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [230] 		total_weight = min(dir_total_weight, total_weight);
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [231] #elif M == 2
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [232] 		sum = TERNARY(step(total_weight, dir_total_weight), dir_sum, sum);
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [233] 		total_weight = max(dir_total_weight, total_weight);
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [234] #else
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [235] 		sum += dir_sum;
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [236] 		total_weight += dir_total_weight;
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [237] #endif
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [238] 	}
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [239] 
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [240] 	val result = sum / total_weight;
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [241] 	return unval(result);
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [242] }
[3086.625][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [243]

[3086.630][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] (Re)creating 960x540x0 texture with format r8: ../../../../../src_packages/libplacebo/src/utils/upload.c:252

[3086.631][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [  3] #extension GL_ARB_texture_gather : enable
[3086.631][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [  4] layout(binding=0) uniform  sampler2D _2;
[3086.631][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [  5] layout(std140, binding=1) uniform _d {
[3086.631][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [  6]     layout(offset=0) vec2 _4;
[3086.631][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [  7]     layout(offset=8) vec2 _5;
[3086.631][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [  8]     layout(offset=16) int _7;

[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] fragment shader source:
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [  1] #version 450
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [  2] #extension GL_ARB_uniform_buffer_object : enable
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [  3] #extension GL_ARB_texture_gather : enable
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [  4] layout(binding=0) uniform  sampler2D _2;
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [  5] layout(std140, binding=1) uniform _d {
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [  6]     layout(offset=0) vec2 _4;
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [  7]     layout(offset=8) vec2 _5;
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [  8]     layout(offset=16) int _7;
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [  9]     layout(offset=20) float _8;
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 10]     layout(offset=24) vec2 _9;
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 11]     layout(offset=32) vec2 _a;
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 12]     layout(offset=40) vec2 _b;
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 13] };
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 14] layout(location=0) in vec2 _3;
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 15] layout(location=0) out vec4 out_color;
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 16] 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 17] #define LUMA_raw _2 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 18] #define LUMA_pos _3 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 19] #define LUMA_map _3_map 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 20] #define LUMA_size vec2(textureSize(_2, 0)) 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 21] #define LUMA_pt _4 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 22] #define LUMA_off _5 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 23] const float _6 = float(1); 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 24] #define LUMA_mul _6 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 25] #define LUMA_rot mat2(1.0, 0.0, 0.0, 1.0) 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 26] #define LUMA_tex(pos) (_6 * vec4(textureLod(_2, pos, 0.0))) 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 27] #define LUMA_texOff(off) (LUMA_tex(_3 + _4 * vec2(off))) 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 28] #define LUMA_gather(pos, c) (_6 * vec4(textureGather(_2, pos, c))) 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 29] #define HOOKED_raw LUMA_raw 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 30] #define HOOKED_pos LUMA_pos 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 31] #define HOOKED_size LUMA_size 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 32] #define HOOKED_rot LUMA_rot 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 33] #define HOOKED_off LUMA_off 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 34] #define HOOKED_pt LUMA_pt 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 35] #define HOOKED_map LUMA_map 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 36] #define HOOKED_mul LUMA_mul 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 37] #define HOOKED_tex LUMA_tex 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 38] #define HOOKED_texOff LUMA_texOff 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 39] #define HOOKED_gather LUMA_gather 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 40] #define frame _7 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 41] #define random _8 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 42] #define input_size _9 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 43] #define target_size _a 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 44] #define tex_offset _b 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 45] const float _8002 = float(0.8703105449676514); 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 46] const float _8003 = float(0.0595848374068737); 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 47] vec4 _8001(vec4 color) {
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 48] // pl_shader_linearize           
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 49] color.rgb = max(color.rgb, 0.0); 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 50] color.rgb = _8002 * pow(color.rgb + vec3(_8003), vec3(2.4)); 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 51] return color;
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 52] }
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 53] 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 54] #define linearize _8001 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 55] const float _4002 = float(1.149015188217163); 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 56] const float _4003 = float(0.0595848374068737); 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 57] vec4 _4001(vec4 color) {
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 58] // pl_shader_delinearize 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 59] color.rgb = max(color.rgb, 0.0); 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 60] color.rgb = pow(_4002 * color.rgb, vec3(1.0/2.4)) - vec3(_4003); 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 61] return color;
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 62] }
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 63] 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 64] #define delinearize _4001 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 65] 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 66] // User variables
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 67] 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 68] // Lower numbers increase blur over longer distances
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 69] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 70] #define S 0.039716259676045834
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 71] #else
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 72] #define S 0.00245792863046567
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 73] #endif
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 74] 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 75] // Lower numbers blur more when intensity varies more between bands
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 76] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 77] #define SI 13.401712932601427
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 78] #else
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 79] #define SI 10.923402488160853
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 80] #endif
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 81] 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 82] // Higher numbers reduce blur for shorter runs
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 83] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 84] #define SR 0.003446736773092952
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 85] #else
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 86] #define SR 0.012925109858034363
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 87] #endif
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 88] 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 89] // Starting weight, lower values give less weight to the input image
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 90] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 91] #define SW 0.43999145467432316
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 92] #else
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 93] #define SW 0.009466672829458444
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 94] #endif
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 95] 
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 96] // Bigger numbers search further, but slower
[3086.632][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 97] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 98] #define RADIUS 8
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 99] #else
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [100] #define RADIUS 8
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [101] #endif
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [102] 
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [103] // Bigger numbers search further, but less accurate
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [104] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [105] #define SPARSITY 0.0
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [106] #else
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [107] #define SPARSITY 0.0
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [108] #endif
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [109] 
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [110] // Bigger numbers search in more directions, slower (max 8)
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [111] // Only 4 and 8 are symmetrical, everything else blurs directionally
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [112] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [113] #define DIRECTIONS 8
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [114] #else
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [115] #define DIRECTIONS 8
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [116] #endif
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [117] 
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [118] // A region is considered a run if it varies less than this
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [119] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [120] #define TOLERANCE 0.001
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [121] #else
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [122] #define TOLERANCE 0.001
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [123] #endif
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [124] 
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [125] // 0 for avg, 1 for min, 2 for max
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [126] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [127] #define M 0
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [128] #else
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [129] #define M 0
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [130] #endif
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [131] 
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [132] // Shader code
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [133] 
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [134] #define gaussian(x) exp(-1 * (x) * (x))
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [135] 
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [136] // boolean logic w/ vectors
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [137] #define NOT(x) (1 - (x))
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [138] #define AND *
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [139] #define TERNARY(cond, x, y) ((x)*(cond) + (y)*NOT(cond))
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [140] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [141] #define EQ(x,y) val(val(x) == val(y))
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [142] #else
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [143] #define EQ(x,y) val(equal(val(x),val(y)))
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [144] #endif
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [145] 
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [146] // from NLM
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [147] #if defined(LUMA_raw)
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [148] #define val float
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [149] #define val_swizz(v) (v.x)
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [150] #define unval(v) vec4(v.x, 0, 0, poi_.a)
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [151] #define val_packed val
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [152] #define val_pack(v) (v)
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [153] #define val_unpack(v) (v)
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [154] #define MAP(f,param) f(param)
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [155] #elif defined(CHROMA_raw)
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [156] #define val vec2
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [157] #define val_swizz(v) (v.xy)
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [158] #define unval(v) vec4(v.x, v.y, 0, poi_.a)
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [159] #define val_packed uint
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [160] #define val_pack(v) packUnorm2x16(v)
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [161] #define val_unpack(v) unpackUnorm2x16(v)
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [162] #define MAP(f,param) vec2(f(param.x), f(param.y))
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [163] #else
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [164] #define val vec3
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [165] #define val_swizz(v) (v.xyz)
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [166] #define unval(v) vec4(v.x, v.y, v.z, poi_.a)
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [167] #define val_packed val
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [168] #define val_pack(v) (v)
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [169] #define val_unpack(v) (v)
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [170] #define MAP(f,param) vec3(f(param.x), f(param.y), f(param.z))
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [171] #endif
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [172] 
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [173] vec4 poi_ = HOOKED_texOff(0);
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [174] val poi = val_swizz(poi_);
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [175] 
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [176] /* Description of the algorithm:
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [177]  *
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [178]  * 1. For each pixel in the image (pixel-of-interest, POI):
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [179]  *   2. Accumulate its value with a weight of 1
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [180]  *   3. For each direction (adjacent/diagonal):
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [181]  *     4. For each pixel in that direction, originating from the POI and ending at an arbitrary limit, excluding the POI itself:
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [182]  *       5. If this pixel has the same value as the previous pixel (including POI) or the next pixel:
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [183]  *         5a. Accumulate its value with a weight of 1
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [184]  *       5b. Otherwise, stop accumulating in this direction
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [185]  *   6. Return the sum of the accumulated weighted pixel values divided by the sum of their weights
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [186]  *
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [187]  * Things this implementation does to make this algorithm more useful:
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [188]  *   - For steps 2 and 5, better weights should be used:
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [189]  *     - For step 5, multiply the weight by the gaussian of the absolute difference between the pixel's value and the POI value
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [190]  *       - This decreases blur for large shifts in intensity
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [191]  *       - The difference is scaled with a user parameter (SI)
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [192]  *     - For steps 2 and 5, multiply the weight of any pixels with values identical to the POI value by a user-specified value (SW)
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [193]  *       - Decreasing SW increases the amount of blur
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [194]  *     - For step 5, multiply the weight by the gaussian of the Euclidean norm of the pixel coordinates
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [195]  *   - For step 4, a parameter (SPARSITY) is taken which directs pixels to be skipped at a specified interval
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [196]  *     - If the pixel after a skipped pixel has the same value as the previous unskipped pixel then its weight is doubled
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [197]  *     - This works well in big flat banded areas but may result in artifacts elsewhere
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [198]  *   - For step 5 and SW, pixels are considered to have the same value if their absolute difference is within a threshold
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [199]  *   - The number of directions in step 3 are user configurable
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [200]  */
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [201] 
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [202] vec4 hook()
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [203] {
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [204] 	val sum = val(poi * SW);
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [205] #if M == 1 // min
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [206] 	val total_weight = val(RADIUS);
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [207] #elif M == 2 // max
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [208] 	val total_weight = val(0);
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [209] #else // avg
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [210] 	val total_weight = val(SW);
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [211] #endif
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [212] 
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [213] 	for (int dir = 0; dir < DIRECTIONS; dir++) {
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [214] 		vec2 direction;
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [215] 		switch (dir) {
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [216] 		case 0: direction = vec2( 1, 0); break;
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [217] 		case 1: direction = vec2(-1, 0); break;
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [218] 		case 2: direction = vec2( 0, 1); break;
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [219] 		case 3: direction = vec2( 0,-1); break;
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [220] 		case 4: direction = vec2( 1, 1); break;
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [221] 		case 5: direction = vec2(-1,-1); break;
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [222] 		case 6: direction = vec2( 1,-1); break;
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [223] 		case 7: direction = vec2(-1, 1); break;
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [224] 		}
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [225] 
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [226] 		val prev_px = poi;
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [227] 		val prev_was_run = val(0);
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [228] 		val prev_weight = val(1);
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [229] 		val not_done = val(1);
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [230] 		val run = val(1);
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [231] 		val dir_sum = poi * SW;
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [232] 		val dir_total_weight = val(SW);
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [233] 		for (int i = 1; i <= RADIUS; i++) {
[3086.633][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [234] 			float sparsity = floor(i * SPARSITY);
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [235] 			val px = val_swizz(HOOKED_texOff((i + sparsity) * direction));
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [236] 			val is_run = step(abs(prev_px - px), val(TOLERANCE));
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [237] 
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [238] 			// stop blurring after discovering a 1px run
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [239] 			not_done *= step(val(1), prev_was_run + is_run);
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [240] 
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [241] 			// consider skipped pixels as runs if their neighbors are both runs
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [242] 			float sparsity_delta = sparsity - floor((i - 1) * SPARSITY);
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [243] 			float prev_sparsity = floor((i - 1) * SPARSITY);
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [244] 			val weight = val(gaussian(length((i + sparsity) * direction) * max(0.0, S)));
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [245] 			weight = is_run * weight + is_run * prev_weight * sparsity_delta;
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [246] 
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [247] 			// run's 2nd pixel has weight increased to compensate for 1st pixel's weight of 0
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [248] 			// XXX doesn't account for sparsity
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [249] 			weight += prev_weight * NOT(prev_was_run);
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [250] 
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [251] 			weight *= gaussian(abs(poi - px) * max(0.0, SI));
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [252] 
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [253] 			weight *= gaussian((run += is_run) * SR);
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [254] 
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [255] 			dir_sum += prev_px * weight * not_done;
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [256] 			dir_total_weight += weight * not_done;
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [257] 
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [258] 			prev_px = TERNARY(is_run, prev_px, px);
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [259] 			prev_was_run = is_run;
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [260] 			prev_weight = weight;
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [261] 		}
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [262] #if M == 1
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [263] 		sum = TERNARY(step(dir_total_weight, total_weight), dir_sum, sum);
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [264] 		total_weight = min(dir_total_weight, total_weight);
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [265] #elif M == 2
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [266] 		sum = TERNARY(step(total_weight, dir_total_weight), dir_sum, sum);
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [267] 		total_weight = max(dir_total_weight, total_weight);
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [268] #else
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [269] 		sum += dir_sum;
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [270] 		total_weight += dir_total_weight;
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [271] #endif
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [272] 	}
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [273] 
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [274] 	val result = sum / total_weight;
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [275] 	return unval(result);
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [276] }
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [277] 
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [278] vec4 _1() {
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [279] vec4 color = hook(); 
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [280] return color;
[3086.634][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [281] }

[3086.635][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [ 90] #ifdef LUMA_raw

[3086.635][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [101] #endif

[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [104] #ifdef LUMA_raw

[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [106] #else

[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [108] #endif
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [109] 
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [110] // Bigger numbers search in more directions, slower (max 8)
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [111] // Only 4 and 8 are symmetrical, everything else blurs directionally
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [112] #ifdef LUMA_raw

[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [117] 
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [118] // A region is considered a run if it varies less than this
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [119] #ifdef LUMA_raw

[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [124] 
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [125] // 0 for avg, 1 for min, 2 for max
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [126] #ifdef LUMA_raw
