[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [128] #else
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [129] #define M 0
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [130] #endif
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [131] 
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [132] // Shader code
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [133] 
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [134] #define gaussian(x) exp(-1 * (x) * (x))
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [135] 
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [136] // boolean logic w/ vectors
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [137] #define NOT(x) (1 - (x))
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [138] #define AND *
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [139] #define TERNARY(cond, x, y) ((x)*(cond) + (y)*NOT(cond))
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [140] #ifdef LUMA_raw
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [141] #define EQ(x,y) val(val(x) == val(y))
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [142] #else
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [143] #define EQ(x,y) val(equal(val(x),val(y)))
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [144] #endif
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [145] 
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [146] // from NLM
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [147] #if defined(LUMA_raw)
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [148] #define val float
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [149] #define val_swizz(v) (v.x)
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [150] #define unval(v) vec4(v.x, 0, 0, poi_.a)
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [151] #define val_packed val
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [152] #define val_pack(v) (v)
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [153] #define val_unpack(v) (v)
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [154] #define MAP(f,param) f(param)
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [155] #elif defined(CHROMA_raw)
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [156] #define val vec2
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [157] #define val_swizz(v) (v.xy)
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [158] #define unval(v) vec4(v.x, v.y, 0, poi_.a)
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [159] #define val_packed uint
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [160] #define val_pack(v) packUnorm2x16(v)
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [161] #define val_unpack(v) unpackUnorm2x16(v)
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [162] #define MAP(f,param) vec2(f(param.x), f(param.y))
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [163] #else
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [164] #define val vec3
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [165] #define val_swizz(v) (v.xyz)
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [166] #define unval(v) vec4(v.x, v.y, v.z, poi_.a)
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [167] #define val_packed val
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [168] #define val_pack(v) (v)
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [169] #define val_unpack(v) (v)
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [170] #define MAP(f,param) vec3(f(param.x), f(param.y), f(param.z))
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [171] #endif
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [172] 
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [173] vec4 poi_ = HOOKED_texOff(0);
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [174] val poi = val_swizz(poi_);
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [175] 
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [176] /* Description of the algorithm:
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [177]  *
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [178]  * 1. For each pixel in the image (pixel-of-interest, POI):
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [179]  *   2. Accumulate its value with a weight of 1
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [180]  *   3. For each direction (adjacent/diagonal):
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [181]  *     4. For each pixel in that direction, originating from the POI and ending at an arbitrary limit, excluding the POI itself:
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [182]  *       5. If this pixel has the same value as the previous pixel (including POI) or the next pixel:
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [183]  *         5a. Accumulate its value with a weight of 1
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [184]  *       5b. Otherwise, stop accumulating in this direction
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [185]  *   6. Return the sum of the accumulated weighted pixel values divided by the sum of their weights
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [186]  *
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [187]  * Things this implementation does to make this algorithm more useful:
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [188]  *   - For steps 2 and 5, better weights should be used:
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [189]  *     - For step 5, multiply the weight by the gaussian of the absolute difference between the pixel's value and the POI value
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [190]  *       - This decreases blur for large shifts in intensity
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [191]  *       - The difference is scaled with a user parameter (SI)
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [192]  *     - For steps 2 and 5, multiply the weight of any pixels with values identical to the POI value by a user-specified value (SW)
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [193]  *       - Decreasing SW increases the amount of blur
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [194]  *     - For step 5, multiply the weight by the gaussian of the Euclidean norm of the pixel coordinates
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [195]  *   - For step 4, a parameter (SPARSITY) is taken which directs pixels to be skipped at a specified interval
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [196]  *     - If the pixel after a skipped pixel has the same value as the previous unskipped pixel then its weight is doubled
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [197]  *     - This works well in big flat banded areas but may result in artifacts elsewhere
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [198]  *   - For step 5 and SW, pixels are considered to have the same value if their absolute difference is within a threshold
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [199]  *   - The number of directions in step 3 are user configurable
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [200]  */
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [201] 
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [202] vec4 hook()
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [203] {
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [204] 	val sum = val(poi * SW);
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [205] #if M == 1 // min
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [206] 	val total_weight = val(RADIUS);
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [207] #elif M == 2 // max
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [208] 	val total_weight = val(0);
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [209] #else // avg
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [210] 	val total_weight = val(SW);
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [211] #endif
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [212] 
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [213] 	for (int dir = 0; dir < DIRECTIONS; dir++) {
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [214] 		vec2 direction;
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [215] 		switch (dir) {
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [216] 		case 0: direction = vec2( 1, 0); break;
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [217] 		case 1: direction = vec2(-1, 0); break;
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [218] 		case 2: direction = vec2( 0, 1); break;
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [219] 		case 3: direction = vec2( 0,-1); break;
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [220] 		case 4: direction = vec2( 1, 1); break;
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [221] 		case 5: direction = vec2(-1,-1); break;
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [222] 		case 6: direction = vec2( 1,-1); break;
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [223] 		case 7: direction = vec2(-1, 1); break;
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [224] 		}
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [225] 
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [226] 		val prev_px = poi;
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [227] 		val prev_was_run = val(0);
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [228] 		val prev_weight = val(1);
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [229] 		val not_done = val(1);
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [230] 		val run = val(1);
[3086.636][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [231] 		val dir_sum = poi * SW;
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [232] 		val dir_total_weight = val(SW);
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [233] 		for (int i = 1; i <= RADIUS; i++) {
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [234] 			float sparsity = floor(i * SPARSITY);
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [235] 			val px = val_swizz(HOOKED_texOff((i + sparsity) * direction));
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [236] 			val is_run = step(abs(prev_px - px), val(TOLERANCE));
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [237] 
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [238] 			// stop blurring after discovering a 1px run
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [239] 			not_done *= step(val(1), prev_was_run + is_run);
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [240] 
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [241] 			// consider skipped pixels as runs if their neighbors are both runs
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [242] 			float sparsity_delta = sparsity - floor((i - 1) * SPARSITY);
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [243] 			float prev_sparsity = floor((i - 1) * SPARSITY);
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [244] 			val weight = val(gaussian(length((i + sparsity) * direction) * max(0.0, S)));
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [245] 			weight = is_run * weight + is_run * prev_weight * sparsity_delta;
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [246] 
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [247] 			// run's 2nd pixel has weight increased to compensate for 1st pixel's weight of 0
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [248] 			// XXX doesn't account for sparsity
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [249] 			weight += prev_weight * NOT(prev_was_run);
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [250] 
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [251] 			weight *= gaussian(abs(poi - px) * max(0.0, SI));
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [252] 
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [253] 			weight *= gaussian((run += is_run) * SR);
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [254] 
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [255] 			dir_sum += prev_px * weight * not_done;
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [256] 			dir_total_weight += weight * not_done;
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [257] 
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [258] 			prev_px = TERNARY(is_run, prev_px, px);
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [259] 			prev_was_run = is_run;
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [260] 			prev_weight = weight;
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [261] 		}
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [262] #if M == 1
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [263] 		sum = TERNARY(step(dir_total_weight, total_weight), dir_sum, sum);
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [264] 		total_weight = min(dir_total_weight, total_weight);
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [265] #elif M == 2
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [266] 		sum = TERNARY(step(total_weight, dir_total_weight), dir_sum, sum);
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [267] 		total_weight = max(dir_total_weight, total_weight);
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [268] #else
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [269] 		sum += dir_sum;
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [270] 		total_weight += dir_total_weight;
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [271] #endif
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [272] 	}
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [273] 
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [274] 	val result = sum / total_weight;
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [275] 	return unval(result);
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [276] }
[3086.637][d][vo/gpu-next/libplacebo] [277]
